text: RowZone is a full body workout that is highly effective and never boring. Cardio on the ERG, weights and AB exercises make it the most efficient 45 minute workout I have ever done. And, the instructors (Laura in particular) are all professional and motivational. It feels like personalized instruction!

I had spotted Kanella awhile ago when walking through that part of town, never heard of it. Read the reviews on yelp and definitely wanted to try it. We had brunch here at 2pm this past weekend and it was a stellar experience. The restaurant was beyond packed and busy, yet service was still attentive. The smell coming out of this place is intoxicating.

We had a really nice bottle of Stag's Leap Chardonnay and ordered savory brunch items. We shared theTachinosalata Platter to start (tomato salad, warm hummus, pita, felafel).  I had a spiced Mahi over couscous with preserved lemon and varied chopped ingredients. My friend had the clams and mussels penne special. I ordered a dessert that was offered as a special I believe. It was a lemon greek yogurt with a raspberry coulis. It was delicious. 

The dining room is warm and cozy. Yes, it is tight. Yes, it can be loud. The food is the real star here. Everyone sitting around us had amazing looking food as well.

I was really impressed with this place. I cannot wait to go back. It offers something authentic and special.
Sandy is awesome!  1st time here.  I had a great experience!  Sandy didn't rush and really took her time to do a great job!

Tried Chick-Fil-A (CFA) 6 times since opening. First time breakfast sandwich (see previous review), another time breakfast sandwiches for my previous employer, 1 time grilled chicken sandwich, 2 times the fried chicken sandwich solo, and meal, and last time was the chicken tender meal. 

I like the Lemonade (5 stars), small upgrade charge if you buy a meal, and they REFILL the Lemonade! I like the waffle iron fries, when they are cooked longer they are 4 stars, otherwise, 2.75 stars. The chicken, it's good, but the servings seem so small with the best being the fried chicken sandwich. I got the 4 pc tenders, and it's like get 6 McNuggets. If the Chicken was organic, it might make a bit more sense, but still would feel pricey. 

I am not a Fan of CFA, and I think the strongest reason is I am a Caniac, eating there at least 1 time per week, sometimes 2x a week for over 1 year now. I always crave it, and I am always happy with what I get. CFA is just okay, last night after getting my tenders, I looked and tasted, and I was 100% craving Cane's, so I went today. If you read my reviews, I have a place that usually adore, and if I go somewhere that doesn't do it like my #1 spot, I have to get to my #1 and get a fix for the experience that was not up to Par! 

At Cane's you get about 4-5 times as much chicken for a MUCH LOWER price! CFA is still busy, and I am not getting it, unless they are just experiencing. I don't see this current busyness as sustainable, and here's why, they close at 9PM daily, and are CLOSED on SUNDAYS! 

I think that's a cool idea, but that reminds me of 30-40 years ago thinking, and I am sure they are losing SERIOUS $$ with this policy, especially in Nevada. We are 24 hour town and 7 days a week, these hours (close at 9PM) and time (M-Sa) don't work. If they change to 24 hours (drive thru) and open 7 days a week, I can see them being a success permanently. Also they need to create a buyer's or VIP club, especially with the small chicken servings.

Curry chicken salad wrap with crisp veggies and fresh organic fruits.  I actually died.. it was that good.  The coffee is delicious and it is nice to have agave syrup as a sweetener option.  This is my favorite place in Phoenixville  for fresh fast eats.

WOW....

This place has come a long way. We got a suite overlooking the pool. It was fantastic. Huge paintings on the walls, separate shower with multiple shower heads, nice TV'S and great Casino action.

Staff is friendly and they just upgraded the poker room.

Who says the economy is suffering hasn't been here.

DO NOT shop there! Driver decided to drive off with out fridge- after 4 hours on the phone resolution was a 10% coupon and delivery... In 4 days!!
Worst experience ever! Unprofessional and rude! Would never shop there again. Beware!!

I am really glad that I did the Preservation Hall experience during my short time in NOLA as I think it gave me an authentic jazz experience.

They have three shows at night (8pm, 9pm, and 10pm). We arrived for the 10pm show 40 minutes early and barely got in. For 40 minutes, we waited outside. The bar next door lets you use the restroom facilities while you wait. Then you stand in a small room and watch a group play jazz. It was a cool experience.

Warning: You will have to stand 45 minutes for waiting on line + 45 minute show. You can pay extra to sit, but I do believe you have to reserve that before hand.

Peppermill Casino is one of my local favorites. I have been in Reno for about 18 years now, and Peppermill has always been a great spot. Between late-night trips to the café and good times at there club Edge I'm a big fan of this place. Oh, yeah and if you want some good sushi head into Oceano.
Horrible customer service. Major attitude problem. Been to many Starbucks in US and in other countries definitely do not follow the Starbucks great customer service model.
Horrible customer service!!!! Extremely Unprofessional & disrespectful!!!!!  Will NEVER eat at this location again!!
The veggie burgers are just morning stars, and the fry portions are very small. For a vegetarian this is not a good option.

The biggest oysters I have ever seen.  The rule that big oysters don't have the best flavor do not apply to the oysters here.  Sit at the Oyster Bar and watch years of shucking experience in action.  
Must haves are the barbecued shrimp.  The sauce is not a traditional barbecue sauce.. more of a heavenly mix of spices and flavors.  The bread pudding could easily be one of the best in the city.  It's made with a lovely whiskey sauce and the pudding isn't too mushy.

the service tech was knowledgeable and had the parts on her truck.  I really appreciate her calling when she was leaving her previous appointment and telling me exactly what time she arrived.  She called our home warranty provider and tried to get them to cover our repair.  She really went beyond the call

Monon Coffee Company is an artie coffee shop in the hip Broad Ripple area of Indy. They have some relaxing chairs/couches, free wifi, and great coffees and pastries. Although it is a bit small, there seems to be always place, as most people either stay only shortly or take away their coffee. Great to work, read, or simply get a good cup of coffee!
Awesome place!!! Great atmosphere, very good prices, quality barbers! Highly recommend this barbershop!
We got a selection of asada, carnitas, shrimp, and al pastor tacos and they were pretty amazing. They also carry taramind jarritos which is hard to find. Love this little find right off the fwy
The worst! Filled with homeless people. So, they treat everyone like homeless. Very rude service! Even if you're a paying customer.

You know, I keep giving these guys a chance in hopes that they will improve. They have not.

I had to clear my throat loudly to entice someone to come from the back to actually help me.

I was in on a Sunday afternoon and while they weren't busy there were hardly any cupcakes to purchase. I was surprised by the lack of variety despite being there with over 3 hours of business hours left until closing. The two cupcakes I purchased were lemon (for the wife), and a chocolate caramel pretzel combo of some sort. Once I paid for them I was anxious to eat mine. 

I got them home and once we had lunch it was time for dessert. My wife tried hers, one bite was all she took to be done. She said it the icing was too sweet and the cake too dry. I felt the same about my mine. Also, the caramel part in the description was not at all present in my cupcake. It really amounted to overly granulated sugary icing with crushed up pretzel bits on top. The frosting had crusted over so it clearly wasn't fresh. The cake was also dry so it too wasn't fresh. You are a cupcake place, that only makes cupcakes but you can't do that well? Clearly, this just doesn't compute.

Next time, I will save myself from these dry cupcakes and make my own.

First time eating at Crabby Bills...we had the BBQ wings for an appetizer and the meat was tender, sauce was tangy.  For our entree we had the Lobster sandwich and Sea Scallops.  Overall the food was juicy and delicious...service was good in spite of it being packed - our server Kelly was very pleasant and attentive...will definitely return in the future..

I called to inquire about my chipped automobile  window..Sandy was friendly and efficient..within an hour Shawn came to my house and my window was fixed..lifetime guarantee. .courteous and informative. .highly recommend Shawn and this company!!

Last Saturday morning I woke up to my Great Dane eating my glasses for breakfast. I had planned to visit the ophthalmologist during the week to get a new pair but really did not have the time to take off work. After being driven to the mall by a family member for an unrelated errand (could not find my contacts), I stumbled upon SEE and was delighted to find that they could give me an eye exam in store right away. The eye exam was easy peasy and felt like I had gone to my regular ophthalmologist.  Jennifer was so helpful in helping me select glasses that went well with my face (I always struggle with this). She also found a special deal for me to allow me to be able to afford a 2nd pair for backup in case of any future dog incidents, lol. All around it was a pleasant experience that allowed me to save money and get my new glasses ordered over the weekend! I could not be more please and will definitely return. Thanks again, Jennifer!

The owner (? white guy behind counter) was really nice. The bubble tea, however, was not. The bubbles were undercooked and flavorless. He did not ask if I wanted mine blended or over ice and I just assumed it would be over ice. It was not. It was poorly crushed ice (think chunks big enough to clog the massive straw mixed with pellets from an artificial snow machine) blenderized with grainy sugar, over hard tapioca balls. I had a huge craving for bubble tea and this place left me feeling unfulfilled. I do NOT recommend it for bubble tea, but based on the cleanliness, kind owner, and happy expressions of all the people eating there, I will be back to try the food. The tea was almost $5, so I felt it was overpriced too.

What an impressive company! We recently had to replace an old furnace and water heater for my mother. We were totally blown away by the professionalism and the customer service which we received from every point of contact. The helpful people on the phone, Dave, the sales person and the people that came to install the furnace where all wonderful. They turned what could have been a very stressful situation for a senior into something pleasant. When the furnace was installed, we were very impressed with the workmanship  by Nick and Ron. Everything looked like care was taken, it wasn't just slapped together. They were efficient and left the basement clean, we were so impressed! Perhaps the nicest thing was the peace of mind they left my mother with. She now feels comfortable and warm and knows her  furnace is a good one and she doesn't have to worry about it breaking down in mid winter. Thankyou everyone at The Furnace Company!

Great date night spot. Will be coming back again! Thoughtful, unique dishes + attentive service.

Food:
- hand cut truffle parmesan fries: would've preferred it to be a bit more crispy.
- carpaccio of beef tenderloin with house made ravioli: our favorite dish of the meal. fresh carpaccio and the house ravioli stuffed with soft poached egg was a nice touch. 
- roasted mushroom flatbread: second favorite dish. a lot of mushroom and arugula. would definitely order again.
- pulled slow braised short rib fat noodles: creative dish; loved the braised short rib with fresh pasta combo. but a tad too sweet and too salty for my taste.

Can't wait to come back and try all the other dishes!

Excellent breakfast/brunch spot in Tucson. Menu consists of various pastries (croissants, Danishes, scones, etc.), pancakes, egg dishes, etc as well as an extensive drink list (specialty mimosas, teas, coffees). This morning I ordered the fruit granola parfait which consisted of a large serving of organic vanilla yogurt smothered in fruits (blackberries, apples, strawberries, raisins, cranberries) and nuts (pine nuts, almonds). I ordered a side of walnut bread which came with fresh whipped butter and fresh jam on the side. It was delicious. My sister ordered two eggs with homefries and toast which she enjoyed and finished the whole plate. Perhaps the best part of the meal was the freshly squeezed orange juice- the freshest and tastiest I have ever had. Coffees and waters were continually refreshed. They really aced it.

After trying a few ramen places with crazy variety in their selections and stellar broth, I was not too excited about the ramen I got at Cheu.  Maybe it's a matter of taste, but personally, I was not a fan of their thick noodles, and extremely salty broth.  

The service was great, and they had a nice selection of beers!  The friend I went with loved it, and has been many times.  Honestly, I'm just sorry I wasn't a bigger fan.  But I hope others try it for themselves.  I might just be an oddball out on this one.

First time my wife and I dined there. It was last Thursday night. The place was half full. Nice environment - we sat in the back room where it was quiet. 

I had the broccoli soup and had to send it back. It was not enough broccoli and too much chicken broth. My wife unselfishly share her salad with me - don't know what it was but it was very good. I had the linguine and my wife the salmon. The linguine was fairly greasy and not very tasty. I ate 25% and took the rest home; I didn't eat eat later. The salmon was good. I guess I was having bad luck! The creme brulee was nice. I noticed that I was charged for french fries the waiter forgot to serve us, it was taken off.

All in all a fair but not good dining experience. 2 glasses of wine, appetizer, entree, desert and 2 coffees came to around $80 without a tip. Limited menu. I'll go somewhere else next time.

I gave it 2 stars but it should be 2 1/2 stars.

I love Panera and I eat there regularly in Texas. But this was the worst experience I've ever had at any Panera. Took over 25 minutes to get two orders of oatmeal. After 20 minutes we went to ask what the status was and the employees laughed as they told us they forgot we were here and had ordered anything.

Since I moved to Philly a few years ago, I have been on the search for a yoga studio that feels like another "home" to me. I found it at Yoga Garden on South St. The owner, Mark, has taught many of the classes I have taken so far. He embodies what I feel yoga is all about: being centered, compassion, and emphasizing balance. In his classes, he is "hands on" (with permission) on guides everyone through energetic sequences that invigorate the body and spirit.

The studio is always clean the ambiance is calming. Classes I have been to have never been so packed that I feel uncomfortable (like a canned sardine). The manager & receptionists are welcoming and polite. I have taken both "all levels" and "intermediate" classes, and I always get the level of challenge I'm seeking there. What more can I ask for? I found my new Yoga Home. Namaste!

I wanted to love it so bad, but it fell short of my expectations.
PROS:
Bread presentation was amazing
Pork loin was so yummy. All the flavors on the plate complemented each other very well and you're filled without being stuffed
Drinks were phenomenal.
Desserts were a perfect portion and, although not unforgettable,  were a nice end to the meal. 

CONS: Service was not what I expected for the restaurant. It wasn't bad service,  but it wasn't outstanding either. Though I never felt rushed, I did feel intimidated by the waitress and she was very to thr point. It threw me off. I asked about different drinks and got short, brisk answers. 
The steak frittes: steak was chewy, in a full of fat and nerves way and seasoned poorly.
Great place for breakfast! I had the waffle, which was fluffy and perfect, and home fries which were nice and smashed and crunchy. Friendly waitstaff. Will definitely be back!
Was quite impressed with this little place. Unique and yet charming. The food was delicious! Grass-fed meats and great choice of fabulous cheeses!!! We really enjoyed....definitely try the fries!!!

I have a finicky dog and One Lucky Dog has the only treats my little girl will eat.   The staff are always so warm, friendly, and helpful.    I especially love Heather who grooms Rosie.  She comes back to me so soft, clean, and beautiful.  And the prices, I feel are very reasonably.

Voree did a great job repairing a laptop for me - fast, reasonable, and effective service.  I used them again for two other laptops.  Don't ask me why I keep having trouble with my laptops.  On one of them my granddaughter broke the display screen and Voree fixed it quickly.

It wont blow u away but it's a decent lunch spot. U wont have anything undercooked. The sesame bread is pretty good. I recommend sticking with egg drop soup unless you are used to the flavors of the other two. Option between white and brown rice, i feel like they missed out on the opportunity to have fried rice as an option. Overall i enjoyed it.

ADT installed a faulty transformer, which was discovered when our entire system went down.  A tech wasn't available for over a week, leaving us with no fire, co2 and alarm protection.  We were finally told that someone would be available the next day if we wanted to pay OT - a minimum of $400.  They offered to reimburse us for 3 months of service - less than half the cost.  We asked what constituted an emergency to get someone out at no charge and were told the transformer blowing up and starting a fire.  No logic worked.  If we didn't have a contract we would cancel our service immediately.  Unfortunately we are stuck.

Sharen's took my order for delivery and a beautiful arrangement was delivered within an hour and a half.  
Great customer service and beautiful flowers!!!
Thanks again Sharen's for making my friends day.  :)

Literally the best sushi known to mankind. 
The Yellowtail Melt is a veritable cornucopia of flavor that will undoubtedly give you a mouthgasm. 
Try out the Champagne Fluke for a tender, rich taste that will make your eyes roll back.
The merry-go-round will feel like tiny mystical creatures dancing a magical jig on your taste buds.
And always end the night with another yellowtail melt, it's just the morally right thing to do.

You won't be sorry.

P.S. Legend has it that every bite of Nao's Sushi will add an extra hour to your life.

I hope that is true... I go here so much, I'm probably just about immortal.

The woman behind the counter was very helpful and friendly. I was looking for a saw and she showed me their bargain bin saw as well as a sturdier if pricer option. They have all the basic DIY stuff for home and garden. I will definitely shop here before I head to one of the big box stores!

Not sure what all the hype is about. We came in at 8 am got seated right away. My husband and I ordered a pretty simple breakfast. 2 eggs bacon for me sausage for him, and fried potatoes and toast.  I did ask for fried onion in my potatoes. A 50 cent up charge for a scantily amount of fried onion thrown on cold potatoes that tasted as though they were fried the day before. My eggs were ordered over easy, one was and one was hard. My bacon was cold and burnt.  My husband's sausage was spicy, I like spicy, but was too spicy for my breakfast. Toast was cold and dry. You have to butter your own at the table, so hope it arrives promptly. Our bill was $18 and some change. You decide. I will go elsewhere for my money.

Antiques everywhere!

I've seen some pretty unique items here. There's a little something for everyone, and the prices are decent. I wouldn't advise bringing young children inside, though. This is a very small store, and even an adult like myself gets nervous about the chance of knocking something off of a shelf.

If you can keep your hands, and randomly flailing accessories, to yourself (that  heavy purse can turn into a wrecking ball real quick) then this is a neat place to visit.

Garlic and cheese chips. That's it. I crave and rave about these things all the time. Goes great with my St. George's Philly.  It's a wonderful pub feel, very chill, non-pretentious, great price and----as previously mentioned----I love the food. If I still lived downtown I'd go more often but when I'm in the area I make a point to stop. If you're a fan of English brews, they have some interesting ones (and specials). Sit outside and enjoy.
The Dan Dan noodles are great, any meat product is horrible. The meat is tenderized into a disgusting gelatinous consistency. It is truly nasty.

Overall, very good and worth visiting. Sort of a nondescript little restaurant on a corner full of locals. The muffaleta (on poboy bread) was totally delicious, if not traditionally served. Their oyster poboys were run-of-the-mill New Orleans great. In other words, not 'special' but up to par with top quality oyster sandwiches everywhere. The gumbo was a little watery and average. Definitely worth stopping in for a bite if you're nearby. The inside is full of picnic-like tables. Comfortable and casual, and the sandwiches are fairly priced.

Definitely one of my favorite Chinese places in the city. I have been going for many years and it's never disappointed. 

Something not to miss are the soups for two - there are multiple interesting and delicious options. The duck soup is great as well as the chicken and vegetables. They are rich and satisfying. 

I usually always get the same entree because it is so tasty - beef with black bean sauce and pan fried noodles. The beef and chinese greens are done perfectly and the egg noodles are buttery and satisfying. One order is enough for at least two and possibly three meals, depending on how hungry you are, so be prepped for leftovers.

It's BYOB and inexpensive. Gets very crowded on weekend eveningsl. So worth it!
The food is very good. The serves very good. Portion kind of small. Spicy sauce is very good. In a word, it is a good place to have Indian good.

Never had a bad time here! Everyone is very kind, beers are diverse and tasty and bartenders are knowledgeable. I just ate the Ave Frohmann sandwich off their seasonal menu and it was delicious! The bread, spicy mustard, kraut and sausage... Yummm.

This place is a good hang out for Vanderbilt students after class. The tacos are okay, not a lot of variety but the quality is good. However, this is just a great place to relax on the patio with a bunch of friends and the buckets of beer that you can get here. The atmosphere is fun and friendly.

This is my happy food! The outside of the building and interior are nothing special, but don't let that throw you off. The food in incredible. I have eaten in and had take out from the steam table. Both are very good, but I agree with Brian R try the Hung ray curry and the disco chicken are not to be missed.

The staff is very friendly and attentive. The prices are also very reasonable.
I didn't get the server's name down, but he was awesome possum LOL. He was super attentive and made sure we had everything. The food is good but the service made it better!

Popped in for "all-day breakfast" recently & realized it's a very limited breakfast menu. Wish it was the full menu all day! The manager was very helpful & attentive. The other employees weren't great. The main dining area was clean & tidy but the side area was messy & not very clean. My food came out hot & fresh though, so I'm happy about that!
Food and service is okay. I would say it is a better place if you do not want all that unstable food quality and hustle and bustle in Minado.
Beautiful building bar and restaurant.  Shared food with friends at a long bar table and everything was delicious.  Cesar salad. Brussel Sprouts,  Shrimp tacos.  Good beer too.

Most amazing deli ever. Sandwichs are mind blowing.  Every week my boyfriend & I go, we always get the daily special & a regular sandwich off the menu. The "Roberto", "Benton Park", "Mike's Beef & Cheddar", & "Turkey Supreme" are my top 4 favs. All DELICIOUS. Great little spot & staff is the best. Definitely A+++

City Parkの近くにある激安かき氷屋さん。シェーブドアイスっていったほうがいいね！
特に夏のニューオーリンズはジメジメして暑いから、公園に行った後にここでかき氷とか最高だと思う！

味の種類は半端なく多いです！50以上はあったはず！
そしてなんといっても安い！ぼくは一番安いチョイスのレギュラーかき氷のスモールを頼みましたが、スモールでも結構十分だと思います。そして値段はたったの$1.50. 安い！！

トッピングをしても５ドル以上はいかないはず。
夏のうだる暑さには、最高のチョイスだと思います！

I recently purchased a mattress here from CJ and he was absolutely wonderful while purchasing the mattress. Customer service was fabulous, all of my questions were answered with honesty, and he was friendly, all without being overly pushy. I went in on a Saturday with a time limit on when I needed the mattress by due to family coming in to town, and my specific mattress had to be ordered. I was promised it would be here in the morning the coming Friday. Well I hadn't heard anything when I had gotten off by 1pm that Friday, called, happened to be CJ there and was informed he had,t heard from the delivery truck. Well okay fine. However, I was holding off doing anything pending this mattress being delivered that day since its delivery on that day was quite important, as well as being what was contractually agreed upon. By 5pm still hadn't heard anything and was quite unhappy. Called again and was told yet again "don't know, haven't heard." Nothing to help me. After another hour I called still having heard nothing from the store, and was very upset at this point. To get any sort of response and help, I had to threaten to come get my money back and take it elsewhere to. Suddenly, it was to be delivered within the next 15 minutes. Once we finally got to pick it up he was not friendly, barely helped get it in my truck, and didn't say thank you and shut the back door without so much as saying two words, or apologizing for the inconvenience. An apology goes a long way, and it left a bad taste in my mouth. I love my new mattress and purchasing it and picking it out was a breeze, but everything after that was a big let down; especially after such raving reviews.

There's nothing fancy about this place, but you can expect great tasting comfort food at reasonable prices.  There is a different homemade soup every night, and they're all delicious. Meals include soup or salad, two sides and dessert. They also have daily and AYCE specials.

Overall, good food, friendly staff, and good value for your money. I highly recommend it.

Garces has done it yet again with his newest taco installation in Philly. This is my new go to and I cannot stop talking about! 

Located perfectly in the art museum area, next to my favorite pizza place (pizzeria vietri!), parking can be tricky, but sometimes I'll buy a water from whole foods then walk over. If not, if you drive around a couple times, you should find something. 

There is usually a line, but it goes by fast, as they give you free samples of beer while you're waiting. If you feel like sitting faster, to the right of the counter there is a full service bar, which is nice..

I have only tried the fish tacos because I never felt the need to venture through their menu since I am always so satisfied. I get the same tacos every single time --the fried mahi and the grilled lime shrimp. Ugh. So. Darn. Good. Paired perfectly with a corona! The tacos are only priced at 3.50! Go try this place ASAP before the lines get even longer!!!!!

Graces never fails!!!!

Problem with seating,the host was not attentive but the manager was nice and gave us a round of drinks. We might give them a second chance since our waiter was so friendlyl and of course very refreshing cocktails!!! The pizza was excellent.

The ambiance is definitely the best part of the restaurant.  It's a very social, but intimate vibe, with an excellent drink menu.  The cocktails are a bit sweet for my taste.  The tables are a little too close together for my taste, but there's a nice buzz to the restaurant.  The food was good.  It wasn't stellar.  And at that price, especially in Philadelphia (where there are really amazing restaurants), it should be better.  The brussell sprouts are heavy and delicious.  The salmon tartare left much to be desired.  The salmon latke dish was good, but there was nothing interesting about it.  Ultimately, it was a good date spot, but nothing to write home about

Had a cappucino, that was pretty great. The coffeeshop was way too loud. They were blasting the music, made it hard to study and even have conversations. The staff seemed like they were messing around the whole time, and not really concerned with the customer.

Unsure if will come back. Just not a typical coffeeshop atmosphere. Staff seemed more concerned with having fun and playing really loud music than their customers.

This hotel is one of 4 in a couple block radius. I usually stay at the Residence Inn but tried this one instead. It was ok. There was a ton of construction going on at the hotel because sadly they were hit very hard by hurricane irma and sustained a lot of damage. 

The rooms are quite big and you get a sleeping area AND a little living room with couch, desk and TV.  Free coffee maker in room. Nutragena toiletries. Small workout room which I used once and has good equipment.

However the water pressure is HORRIBLE. And you know me my friends....i like some good water pressure. I did not encounter bed bugs, but I did see these tiny little ants on my table. Which I thought was weird but given the construction I shrugged it off. 

I was pleased with the buffet breakfast which was very affordable and everyone who worked there was quite pleasant and accommodating.  

Overall a good stay.

This restaurant was a fantastic experience! We came during a visit to SB and were looking for a fresh seafood dinner. We signed up for a table on the waiting list and accidentally missed our first call. They put us right back into line and we got the next table. 

Our server was so helpful and enthusiastic. We couldn't decide on which entrees to get, which crab to pick and he gave fantastic advice. 

We got sea urchin and the presentation was so cool. The chowder was delicious and the onion rings were perfectly crispy. We got the rock crab meal and got it served with the mustard. Really a great meal!

This place is perfect for any meal. The owner is the sweetest and most personable lady you will ever meet and the new Korean additions to the menu are out of this world. If you have the chance to go here please do so.

There are some mighty fine donuts at Eddie's Southtown Donuts.  At a lot of places some donuts are great, others not so good, but everything I sampled here were delicious.  

It's in a pretty unassuming location so I don't think it's easy to notice this great place.
This place was ok. I saw mold on a cheese that shouldn't have mold on. I'd recommend going to Clearwater euro food and deli, that one was better.

This is only one In-N-Out in Santa Barbara. Although it's popular, the cost was so cheap, which surprised me! It has four burgers. But I guess, for most people, each regular burger is not enough to get full. So, I wanna the double next time.

I have to say o was quite impressed with this restaurant. I'm from CA so I'm pretty picky when it comes to pho but dang this place taste white authentic! The broth was delish! We ordered quite a lot a of few and was very satisfied! Great joint in random ass Indy!

Wonderful room. Clean showers and bed. Quite. Very nice staff. Just enough out of the French quarter to be out of the mess but easy to walk too. Would love to come back. And I highly recommend this place.

Very very poor communication, posts on social media of my dog clearly not happy and harness on wrong, set off security system and did not notify me--I found out from the alarm company first, brought in new walker without telling me, didn't tell me my dog was peeing on the floor and sofa out of fear when she was greeted by them--had to find out from roommates (thank god for them or I would never even know of these issues). I work in a stressful ICU and want to be sure my dog is safe and happy, but these walkers only added more stress.

3.5 stars total. 

If you're used to Philly brunch this is not going to be entirely comparable.  However,  other than diners this is a great breakfast choice in the area. 

You may need to wait 10-15 minutes for a table on Saturday and Sunday.  There is outdoor seating available for when the weather is nice. 

The coffee menu is amazing.  This is the only restaurant that I know of (other than coffee houses) that brings a French press to your table.  Variety of beans including Costa Rican,  Hawaiian,  and Jamaican.  Gourmet iced coffee with coffee iced cubes- hell yes! Plus refills free to go. 

The menu is simple focusing on eggs, hot cakes,  and sandwiches.  Nothing has totally blown me away but the food is good and fresh. Random sidenote obsessed with the red pepper soup.

Definitely one of my to go to breakfast spots in south Jersey - recommend.

Service is top notch. Elizabeth, Teddy and Jimmy are the best baristas ever. The space is open and airy with a great patio. I like visiting this location more than any of the others in the Nashville area.
Great prices for some creative donuts. Wish we could have also tried the fried chicken as it seems  to be famous around here. Loved the spicy PB and J donut.

Bubble tea is one of my (many) vices. It's delicious and I'll never turn down the opportunity for a honeydew bubble tea with tapioca and lychee pieces. So great. Anyways, a friend and I came here for our bubble tea fix and it was a pretty decent experience. I'd come back, but it wasn't anything extraordinary. 

It was busy in there- like every single table was full type busy. People playing games, eating food, drinking tea, the whole thing. That being said, it was also quite loud but that's what you expect when a place is this popular! I'd like to come back and sit and enjoy myself since I only stayed in there for about 10 minutes. 

I got a honeydew bubble tea and it was good! I also ordered the spring rolls and they were actually really good as well. The price is decent for what you pay for and they have special deals on different days of the week, so on Tuesdays you get cheap green onion cakes if you buy a bubble tea, on Wednesdays you get cheap spring rolls, etc etc. You get the idea. 

The menu is huge and there are tons of options for bubble tea- you can also get iced teas, shaved ice, hot tea. There is an endless amount of options, really. I was also surprised at the amount of food they had on the menu as well! Also, you can get a stamp card here, when you buy nine bubble tea you get the tenth for free which is great for addicts like myself! 

Lots of parking in the parking lot even though it may get quite busy, depending on the time you go. There are quite a few other shops in the complex, which probably contributes to the craziness. If you don't want to bother with the crazy parking lot there's an abundance of street parking close by. 

The service wasn't that great when I went, the girls at the till weren't that friendly but I wasn't super bothered by it since they were so incredibly busy. It took a while for my spring rolls and I went up to the counter to ask for them, and they were sitting behind the counter not being called out. The girl was kind of snippy about it but I didn't really care since I just wanted my food. 

Overall, not bad. Was worth the visit because the bubble tea was delicious, and I'll probably come back some other time, maybe to enjoy a bigger dish or a game. I take experiences like this as a grain of salt- hopefully I come next time and they're friendlier. If not, I know I can always leave with a delicious drink that I came for.

Absolutely love this place, my son is a VERY picky eater and I ordered him a fish plate and he ate every bit of it then asked me to go buy him another one. The breakfast is the best. Those grits are so creamy and delicious. And lord let's not forget about the sweets

One of my favorite ballparks. Almost every seat has a decent view, and the way the upper decks are set up you feel close to all the action.  
I usuly get to the park when the gates open so I can watch BP, so parking is never really an issue. But if you stay for the who game get back to 95 south can be a bitch.
Great restaurant. The manager and staff was genuinely concerned with wait times and very accommodating. The food was excellent. 5 star rating.

Ordered 6 rolls, 4 miso soups, 1 edamame, and 1 yakatori for 4 people for lunch. The sushi was fresh and tasty but we were all starving when the food was finished.  Pathetically tiny portion sizes for the $60 cost.  Would easily have been $120 to feed the 4 normal humans. Just not worth the cost.
Their "make your own hash" is worth the long line. Quality ingredients, hearty food, healthy + vegetarian options.

2 stars for gumbo, 1 for the blandest, bleakest serving of red beans & rice ever! Really how hard is it to make red beans & why would you serve this NO fare without any seasoning at all? Don't waste time or money on this place
Kim was great! Very helpful, explained everything clearly & gave me tons of detail. I trust her advice & appreciate the education she gave me about my car, service & parts.
We tried Lasagna and More for the first time tonight and it was delicious! We will definitely be back- gonna be a regular for us. Glad to know it's here!  Excellent!

Love these guys. I've been here twice now for two completely different experiences and both were wonderful. The first was as a guest at a wedding shower. They were helpful and courteous and the food they served was amazing. 

Second visit was to bring my sister to a place that she could hopefully eat something at without worrying. She has lots of food allergies (dairy, gluten, soy) that really limit her ability to go out anywhere. She loved her food choices here. We came for breakfast and sat outside and were visited by "Henry" a big white bird that frequently hangs around. One of the staff (maybe the owner) came out when they saw a little boy trying to get close to Henry and helped him go across the parking lot away from where we were eating to feed him special food they brought out front. This was adorable and helped to teach Henry to learn that he gets food away from the people outside eating. And you should have seen how happy the little boy was. Excellent experience (both times!).
Arcadia Landscape is a great locally owned company. I would recommend this company to family, friends, and any local business owners. Their work is high quality, and they stand behind their product.

This place was hopping around 4 pm on a Wed and very rainy summer afternoon.  We saw so many cars in the lot that we just had to check it out.  I don't usually like Lone Star or Outback type places, but this place was so loud, lively, and fun that I would love if they had it in the D.C. area.  There were a lot of older folks doing the the BOGO free fajitas, which we also got.  It was all right/nothing fabulous, but I was so full from eating the delicious onion ring stack and free peanuts that I could not eat all of the fajitas.  Good service and a lot of regulars for 4 pm!  When we left there were tons of people in the waiting area.  Amazing for a very recession/unemployed/foreclosure & weary part of Florida.  This place takes away all your troubles and you can feel happy for a moment.  With all the misery taking place in recent news events, this place is somewhere you can go to wash away your sorrows with a nice tall glass of Coca Cola and delicious onion rings.

Service was less than par, the Tater tot fondue was NOT good, both of the burgers my table ordered were so greasy we couldn't eat the bottom bun- the location and decor was great but I wouldn't go back.

I have been coming here for 15 years and have NEVER had a bad experience! I used to come here on lunch break in high school with friends and get a few slices. And I've also had their finer dishes. Some favorites are the Sicilian pizza, chicken escarole soup, spinach ricotta pizza, and chicken and broccoli. Yum!

A very small, cute shop with excellent tacos and margs. It's almost never too busy to find a table. Service can be a bit slow because there are usually not quite enough servers, but it's worth it. The taco specials are usually fantastic. And the most important criteria is that the guacamole is hella good!

I went to Silver Bullet Gun Works last Monday to pick up some 200 grain 10mm hunting ammo and noticed an old Savage 12 gauge shotgun on their discount rack.  It is now the gem of my collection.  Took it to the range yesterday and it functioned flawlessly.  Big thanks to Mark and the rest of his staff for the great experience.

My husband and I live close to 312 so we come here often for take out. Their pizza is pretty good, but not great and certainly not consistent.  We like the Nashago pizza, but it tastes different every time.  The service isn't the best either.  The pizzas take a long time to make, which is understandable, but it takes too long even to get a drink.  We come here because it's local, but that's the only reason. 

If you do make the trip to 312, I would definitely recommend the pretzels as the dipping sauce is the best.

Excellent.  Food looks and tastes fresh, and prepared with care.  Service was friendly.  We recommend the verde spaghetti squash, tofu tacos, and black bean sweet potato empanadas.  Portions are large.
One word, delicious! Had the braised beef tripe and the beef pancake, can't go wrong! Next time I'm in Reno I'll be back!

Very upsetting experience today. I drove 30 minutes to come here and was informed they were out of the ingredients to make quite a few sandwiches. I then asked where the next Quiznos was and they listed off a bunch that have recently closed. So I asked where subway is and they stated they didn't know because they aren't from the area. You work here. You know. Terrible experience.
What a cute, quaint place!  The service was fantastic and the coffee was fantastic.  I went with an iced coffee that tasted very nice and wasn't bitter at all.  Will definitely be back for more!
Not sure if they're still open, phone number listed disconnected. Went by for lunch today (Monday) and they were locked up tight. No sign with hours...draw your own conclusions.

I really like the simplicity of La Colombe, it has a quiet buzz about it and the baristas know what they are doing. There are no sizes and no menu present, but the prices are fair and you will not see the starbucks spoon foaming done on your cappuccino here at all. Can you really hate on simplicity?

I haven't experienced snotty-ness as all, as others have mentioned either. I've witnessed customers explaining what they'd like in a drink and suggestions being made. Again, this place is about classic simple drinks- why break what's not broken?

With weather like we have been having, I know I'll be around more to grab the double latte I have become used to here.

Very disappointed with the experience I had last evening. My friends and I decided on a girls night that began with dinner at Friendlys and ended with a movie close by. We ordered our food at 6pm- so we could leave by 7, for a movie that started at 7:20. None of us ordered anything fancy- chicken fingers, a wrap, a sandwich. At 6:50 our food finally came, and we quickly had to scarf it down in order to leave. (We did let our server know we were headed to the movies after dinner, there was only 5 of us) This was extremely disappointing, even though they offered is boxes to take with us...which honestly, we couldn't even do since we would be at a movie for a few hours. 


We expressed our disappointment to the "Manager," who never even looked up, made eye contact, or engaged in a conversation when we shared with her our experience. All she said was "I gave you a little something off"- Which was $1.50 off the entire check. It wasn't even the discount that irked me- We were looking for someone to validate and at least pretend they were concerned about our experience, and even that was too difficult to do. 

I would just eat at the theater or head to Red Robbins if you're looking for a quick bite to eat. Apparently, the fry times for Friendlies chicken fingers, fries, etc exceed over 20 minutes.

The buffet had a lot of food, with crab legs, prime rib, roast pork, shrimp, calamari, and steak as the main meat items. It has a selection from various cuisines, Chinese, Mexican and Indian. They kept all the areas well stocked with food.

The meat was not bad and also liked the roasted vegetables. The rest of the food was at best okay, the salad bar's vegetables and fruit were pretty sad looking. The fruits were rather disappointing, with only pineapple and Cantaloupe.

The dessert selection had cakes, gelato, creme brûlée and pies. I liked the gelato a lot, while the cakes and brûlée a were extremely sweet. 

For the $30 (post tax) on a Saturday night, it's not a bad value, but nothing amazing.

I was very excited to find a Taiwanese place that also served milk tea in Reno. Being in the Bay area has certainly spoiled me and my milk tea craze. There are so many different places to choose from. 

They are nice people. Overall their food is just okay. I do love their daily soups. They are some legit Chinese soups, which I simply ADORE and cannot get enough of. Their Zha Jiang Mien tasted like Taiwanese spaghetti, which they do advertise as in fine print. Their popcorn chicken tastes like every other popcorn chicken out there. So it was satisfying. 

They only serve black milk teas which was a little bit disappointing to me since I prefer jasmine green milk tea. 

Overall, 3 STARS just because there's no other milk tea place in Reno. Would I come back? Yea, I guess. It's nice that they have a check-in discount offer though.

This restaurant is one of the very few Indian restaurants that we have tried so far and I should say that it's the best taste by far!! The only concern we had is their spice level was too high. Other than they had a great taste and creativity in making modern Indian food.

I usually don't leave bad reviews but if I can save someone a bad experience, why not?
I visited this establishment one Friday afternoon, the employees were nice enough. There was one guy in particular who went out of his way to make conversation and was really nice and it was appreciated. By day three after my visit, two nails of my nails had already broken leaving me super frustrated and annoyed. I work constantly, hours varying and its tough to find time to even get to a nail salon. Never the less I return the following Friday with intentions on getting my nails fixed and a refill because I was already there. Long story short, I was accused of "lying" In front of an entire salon full of people. I had to provide my previous receipt bc no one apparently remembered me. That's fair enough, I'm not a regular and I'm not so naive to believe that everyone I encounter will remember me but to be accused of lying in front of everyone in the salon was mortifying and I vowed to never return. I wasn't trying to get over on them or anything of the sort considering I STILL got a refill on my nails and paid full price.
Last but not least, 4 days after my second visit another nail has broken. I will NOT be returning.

I'm going to start off by saying we are in the service industry and are therefore, pretty understanding and forgiving. However, this joint seems to have been slapped together with an trendy concept and not much else. Bad food and bad service is a no-go for me. We were in Philly for my 30th birthday and had drinks here Saturday night and then came back for brunch. I was hesitant but the brunch came recommended by a local. I'd say skip it for both. There's too much good food in Philly and better service. 

The PM experience was fine apart from higher prices than other whiskey joints in town and bus staff that will take your half full drink more than once. The server didn't want to replace them when he was alerted. It was definitely off-putting.  

The brunch service was less than stellar. The eggs - poached and fried - were a soupy, half raw mess. You always take a gamble with mods but when I ordered the crab benny sans the crab cake because my hungover stomach wasn't particularly feeling seafood, the sever neglected to tell me that he would be bringing me a $10 plate of two soupy poached eggs with sauce. I had to ask for the toast that came with the next two benny plates I saw come out of the kitchen. No idea what happened there. The place wasn't busy by any means  (considering the volume the PM staff has to wrangle) but getting a cup of coffee and food took a small eternity. The server seemed unable to take stock and attempt to turn the experience around.

I really enjoy the flavor of all of their food! But the portion size is small compared to all the other good bbq places in town. You only get one slice of brisket on the dinner plate. Everywhere else gives you at least 3.. So I would stick to getting wings cause man those are just killer. Also during happy hour you get 10 wings for 7 bucks :) But the manager is super nice, our server was very nice and attentive and the hostess greeted us with a smile and a hello immediately. So we will definitely go back.

WOB seems to have gone through a few owners over the last decade.  What was a hole in the wall wing place writh very few customers here and there is now a bustling wing joint. Wings are always cooked right,  never over done,  sauces are unique and tasty and if you don't get the baked potato fries you're really missing out. The servers are generally friendly and efficient. The only down side is it can get very busy which slows down service quite a bit.  So of you're in a hurry during a rush, you might want to try to come back another time.  This is my new wing joint,  check it out. .. if you don't love it,  you have no soul.

Cheap, delicious Indonesian food that is easy on the pocketbook.

You know an Indonesian restaurant is truly legit when 2/3 of the customers eating there are Indonesians and nothing on the menu is over $6. They only had one server. However, he was speedy and extra friendly. 

The fried wontons were excellent. Real crispy on the outside, soft and flavorful inside. The #1 item on the menu, the homemade noodle dish, Mie Komplit was tasty and satisfying ($5). The noodles and soup came separately. When asked our affable server if we should pour the soup into the noodles, he answered politely and gave us his honest opinion (eat separately).  We also ordered the pork platter ($6). It came with several vegetables and different types of cooked pork. It was very palatable and enjoyable to eat.

Insanely delicious hole in the wall.
Lost the key to my ford and they were able to make me two new keys at a really great price!!

The food is good, service is ok but the owner is NOT a human being. I saw a homeless guy and wanted to buy him some food so the owner wouldn't let him in, even though the homeless wasn't dirty he just had a sign on his hand. Never coming back

Slamming fries and killer service! My best friend ordered a burger which was sufficiently juicy considering it was well done. On the downside, they charged for selzer and the prices over all were a few dollars above normal per item but in my humble opinion well with it.

Came here with my boyfriend for lunch because we had a Groupon. The homemade chips and sauce they served us were delicious. The chips were so crunchy and warm! We ordered the Sweet Chili Wings, Garlic Parmesan Wings, and Eats! Original Chicken Burger. My favorite item was the Garlic Parmesan Wings which were really crispy and buttery. The Sweet Chili Wings tasted like they just poured a bottled sweet chili sauce over it. The Chicken Burger was cooked well; not dry at all. Our food came out at a reasonable time. I will definitely be back.

First visit tonight. Nice, clean place. Reasonably priced. Friendly staff. Excellent presentation of extremely bland, mediocre food. I ordered the chicken fajitas. Onions and pepper base (warm) on a tepid fajita platter. Meat, room temperature. Pico, cheese, sour cream, tortillas were nothing special. I was underwhelmed. I don't think I'll be back.
Good food, great milkshakes!! Loved it! I will definitely be back next time I am in town!!
i really only come here because i work so close by. aside from their delicious affogato, i've also had good lunches here (try their anti-pasti salad bowl!). oh, and the gelato is good here *duh!

Really good food. We ordered the appetizer for four which would feed 8. Don't order the large one I'm afraid how big it would be. We then had stuffed crab with greens and Mac and cheese. Food was very good. Service was excellent

I gave this place four stars (even though quality wise it probably deserves a 3) just because I have a special place in my heart for the lunch runs we did here when I worked at the travel agency around the corner. It's not-the-best-omg-amazing sushi, but it is solid, edible, and cheap. Also, it's BYOB but I don't recommend this place for a cozy, intimate BYOB dinner night with your S.O. It's more of a "get boozy with your girlfriends post-work dinner" or boozy lunch with co-workers kind of place, as the inside is not super nice, and the tables are kind of rickety. But the staff are so, so friendly and accommodating.

I went in July 2016 with my family. They ordered sandwiches which were okay, no rave. One salad order wrong. I ordered a chicken quesadilla. Horrible. I had to hunt for the few pieces of chicken and they used a yellow cheese, not real sure but I think cheddar. Clumpy and cold. And no ocean view. Parked WAY down the road so forget handicap or elderly. There was a tiki bar that had 'stay out' yellow tape and a sign warning 'no kids'. Of course children kept going in and one of my party rescued them until the parents noticed. Poor way to insure customer safety.

A friend suggested this cafe for a lunch date a while back and I cannot stay away. My husband is obsessed with their Peanut Butter Deluxe smoothie. And while Its an obsession I cannot afford to indulge - their bread is what dreams are made of. I love to get their soup due jour over brown rice. Yum! Whether its Breakfast or Lunch - you can't go wrong at Cafe Deluxe.

This place is so yum! I came here while visiting Nashville and I really wish we had this place in Chicago.

I ordered a Build Your Own Salad with arugula, chicken, goat cheese, strawberries, and vanilla-poached pears. Super fresh and healthy. They do cram the salad into this jam-packed plastic container, and when you open the container, your salad contents will likely overflow out of the container. Why is it not socially acceptable to eat salad out of a huge basin-like serving bowl?? :)

They also had this amazing-looking section of desserts. I ordered the peach carrot cake, which unfortunately was just okay. The frosting was buttercream; it probably would have been better with cream cheese frosting. It's a definite pass, so only deducting one star due to the sub-par dessert. But I would definitely return!

I was really excited to try this restaurant. I heard they made everything from scratch including buns and condiments. But after trying to seemed like a hip restaurant to be at, but burgers were very bland. I've had better burgers elsewhere. It very popular and we waited a long time to eat but wasn't worth it in the end.

Beautiful.  What a facility!  

A little too much nickel and dime...for everything

Some poor service.  Waiter Rudy at Wasabi's sucked and got a weak tip for it.   Dawn at front desk sent me the long way through the Cascades to where my room was supposed to be.  It was actually at the other end and the hall right next the registration was way shorter which I would have appreciated when I was toting all my luggage and supplies.  She was also difficult about giving the room I reserved and tried to get me to take "a bigger room but it has a pull out bed".  Ended up giving me a room with a parking lot view.  Nice Dawn- way to try and spoil my experience.  Everyone else was very nice and helpful

"Gluten free" is used loosely in this restaurant, there are many options, however it's all made on the same equipment, so cross contamination is a guarantee. If GF is your preference, this is a tasty place; if you're allergic or intolerant to Gluten, it's not so great.
Best Indian food in Boise, bar none. Interesting atmosphere, fresh ingredients, lunch buffet every day. Varied menu. Large selection of beer.

I really adore this place if it weren't for the ridiculous prices and small portions. The atmosphere is great and filled with Arabic music. I love the seating and the layout of everything which gives it a strong Middle Eastern vibe. The service is not so great because they do not check up on you at all. You have to call them over if you need anything. Also, the hookah is way overpriced for $25...though it is delicious. I haven't eaten there before but I have seen what my friends have ordered and they barely give any food and charge way too much. Another downer is that there's only people there on weekends. On weekdays it is completely empty. 
Oh how could I forget? I love that there's a belly dancer, though they could find better. I'd only come to this place again if I had a lot moola and didn't mind spending it.

Hmmm, went here for a conference and they seemed unprepared for the said conference. How does that happen? We couldn't check in and had to wait hours for a room to be ready. The rooms are definitely spacious but they need some rehab, especially the bathrooms. Also, if you're having a conference, good wifi would be an added benefit. Maybe they were having and off week. Breakfast was a nice bonus.

We went here for dinner last night.  The service was very good.  Gave us as much time as we needed with the menu.  Ordered salad, appetizers and entrees.  Each plate was better than the last.  There were 5 of us.  We tried each other's plates.  Amazing.  I would highly recommend this restaurant.
We had Tostones, Nachos, Fingerling Salad, Med Plate.  We also had Blue Corn Tacos, Empanadas, Tacos.  And my friend from California, used to live in the area, brought us here for the Hazelnut Toffee basket.  Nothing disappointed.  All so good.

The Vault of Souls experience was a great evening, and I would highly recommend it.  Every part of the performance was cleverly orchestrated with a great attention to detail.  The Arrival was pleasant, and the Ventilater drink was refreshing and yummy!  Without saying too much about the Ritual itself, I would say to take your time and explore everything.  The actors were wonderful!  The decor everywhere from beginning to end was absolutely fabulous.  The place oozes with real history which we loved.

We got what we came for which was an upscale, spooky experience which was "night and day" from Howl-o-Scream which we did the night before.

If I had any constructive criticism it would be that it was a little difficult to follow the plot and "solve" whatever the puzzles were leading to "escape."  We've done many escape rooms and we are generally good at those sorts of experiences but Vault of Souls might benefit from a little more direction on what is the goal.  

The book of poetry was very nice, and we really enjoyed hanging out in the Gin Joint. will definitely be back next year as this was a value-filled experience!

This place had a long line, and we went on a Monday! Worth the wait, though. While there was parking behind the building we had to circle a few times bc it was still so busy!

While I don't have any other hot chicken to compare this to, I was impressed and found everything on my plate to be delicious. The brisket tacos were also very yummy! The sides weren't anything special.

After we ate we walked around this neighborhood, which was really fun.

Best Chinese/Taiwanese  food in Reno! My daughter wolfed down the braised beef noodle soup in minutes. I did not even have a chance to try it. My other kid cleaned out the fried rice too.  I ordered the chicken bento box. It was delicious. We all shared the tasty and crunchy popcorn chicken. We had no left-over. Definitely will return for more tasty food.

This is not a character assassination. The servers at the Jamaican Jerk Hut all seemed very lovely. But my first (and likely only) dining experience there was one of those that was tainted by the haze of mood-altering blood sugar levels from ridiculously long wait times which were compounded by loud and obnoxious clientele* that I think the management are letting ruin their establishment. 

In most cases any place is worth a second chance since I know there are always extenuating circumstances: their top server has mono, a shipment of Jerk seasoning is stuck on route 95, they had to physically go slaughter our dinners and the chickens were riled up from the flash mob on South St. But after reading past reviews apparently deplorable service has been the norm since they started riding the coattails of being in the film In Her Shoes. Additionally, even though the curry goat was pretty tasty two hours after I ordered it, I consider the pains I'm still having in my gut 8 hours later as punishment for not trusting my instincts and getting the hell out of there when we first arrived. The back of the house told us to check-in up front, the front told us to check-in out back, a reservation book inside had nothing written in it (funny, considering we all had a few to contribute by then.) All of this should have been a big warning sign.

*In hindsight I realize that the additional charges (listed below) mentioned on page 2 of the menu were most likely created to discourage college kids from coming in to take advantage of the BYOB and 'drinking under the radar' (made obvious by the overly drunk girl who needed help both walking to the bathroom and holding her hair back.) Not only does it ruin the experience for the grown ups who can hold their liquor but it's ineffective and unnerving, especially in a place that seats at least 50 people and has only one bathroom. It's also absurd for already overpriced food, less-than-stellar service, wait times, plastic cups, etc. Then they don't even honor their own fees since the only add-on we were charged was 4 $3 corkage fees, which didn't even add up to what we actually consumed!
- $12 minimum to sit on the patio, 
- 20% gratuity for parties of 6 or more, 
- $4 entertainment fee on Fri and Sat nights and a 
- $4 corkage fee for each bottle of wine and six pack

Thank god I have generous Jamaican neighbors with a patio. I'll visit them the next time I want to eat jerk chicken and sit outside with my own alcohol.

This is what be of my new favorite places for dinner. Nashville has so many great restaurants but I'd rate Butcher & Bee bear the top. Everything we had was fantastic and well worth the price. The whipped feta was amazing!
These guys do good work, on time, and warranty their work.  I would highly recommend them!

I absolutely love the location. I live on the north side of Indianapolis so its great to find a conveniently located range. Overall, the staff is incredibly helpful and knowledgeable. I took y mom shooting for the first time and she had plenty of questions and the staff was able to answer all of them in a way that was reassuring for a first timer. The prices for pistol and lane rentals are well within reason and the range itself is clean and accommodating. Really can't say enough good thing about this place.

My husband and I were walking downtown and stumbled upon this little gem. While walking around the building I kept thinking this can NOT be a courthouse. It's way too pretty! Where am I? I was really confused as I walked around the garden, the room with the gorgeous mural, admired the beautiful tiles, the interesting architecture, and trekked up the stairs to the observation deck. The best part it's all completely free!

The lunch buffet is excellent.  Always being refilled by cooks who are proud of their food.  The writer has lunch there about once a week and always wants a nap in the afternoon because of the good food.

One slight word of caution - this restaurant is located in a typical Tucson mall.  To call the mall "run-down" would be a compliment.

The greatest work DeGrazia created, in my opinion, was his home.  Never finished, always changing, the artist built his combination work space/gallery/home from materials found in the desert and continued to build and improve on it until his death.  

The main buildings now house a free museum of DeGrazia's work, including a "for-sale" room of art as well as a gift shop.  

Nestled in the upper desert of Tucson, the property feels like sacred ground. DeGrazia was very devout and built a chapel near the house which can also be viewed and which has become a sort of shrine to the artist.  

This is well worth a visit, from the soda cans turned into flowers to the hand made detailing including cactus inlays and shell borders of the rooms to the rambling gardens.  Truly a unique experience.

I really don't bother with negative reviews, but this time an exception has to be made.

I'd like to follow up on Elsa H.'s review of this place, since I was a member of the family being threatened with police action over trying to purchase a lamp.  I've visited this store many times (it's only a few blocks from our house--we live in the Garden District / Irish Channel), and have had no small share of weird or rude encounters.  Previously, it was decidedly unfriendly looks from the staff, noting encounters with patrons who wanted to keep their purses rather than surrender them at the front counter, etc.  I continued to visit, however, because there's a certain sort of eclectic "junk pile" vibe here and some genuinely interesting stuff. This time, the epic unfriendliness of the staff was directed squarely at us, however.

One detail omitted from the previous description of this encounter is when Elsa tried to diffuse the situation with the female owner, the husband (?), rather than trying to also diffuse the situation and (perhaps?) sell something, immediately not only made the "tell the police to hurry up" remark  but also tried to throw additional and unrelated fuel on the fire, and blame the kids for breaking things.  Since they were picking vintage comic books for purchase with me, in a different area of the store, and the lamp was on a high shelf elsewhere, that's a little hard to digest.

I'd also like to reinforce how nice it was to have other patrons who were also going to buy things simply leave the store and follow us next door to La Davina (highly recommended gelato) to discuss what happened.

If you're visiting New Orleans and looking for antiques, I strongly encourage you to check out the other offerings on Magazine St.  If you're a local, I think it's obvious that except possibly as an anti-gentrification move, we really don't want a visitor's experience on the otherwise fantastic Magazine St. stretch to include this sort of abuse.  And finally, if you're considering consigning your merchandise to be sold by this store, I encourage you to first be an observant "customer", and decide if you believe anything will actually be sold at all, given the attitude of the owners.  There are better choices. 

Please don't support this horrible store.  And in summary, it's unfortunate that Yelp doesn't allow zero-star reviews.

Well made, tasty, good portion sizes, ready for pickup on time. Many more offerings than Tiffin, our previous go to in Wynnewood. "Medium" spice level might be a bit hotter than some are accustomed to.

Don't order unless you have over 40 mins for a couple smoothies and 2 aloe shots. Then they just hand your stuff over and walk away. Then when we finished the aloe shot the employee walks up and reaches in front of my face a the window counter the grab the tray without saying excuse me or sorry for the wait or anything. That was a very bad first and last experience.

Where to begin.  First off they don't tell you about the $35 per day incidental charge until you check in.  Then i asked them for towels as I didn't receive new ones on three different occasions.  Third, they only had two people working the coffee shop when they should've had double or more with the traffic. I had to wait 15 minutes for a latte which was way too hot. Lastly they charged me an additional 19.25 saying I went over my incidental charge when I did not go over.  When I asked the front desk lady she acted like she didn't care and didn't do anything to get my money back.  If it wasn't for the fact that my conference was at this hotel I would've stayed here to begin with. Now I know even if I come back for future conferences, I'll stay at another hotel.
Take advantage of your local vendorsand  agricultural amenities and come to King of Prussia. Located behind the police barracks in their parking lot.

Tried the crawfish beignet during Sunday brunch. Great flavor, a lot of cheese but loved the spice! A Must try!

Cute neighborhood restaurant. Bartender was busy, but nice enough!

June 12, 2014-
I am on disability and am struggling financially, and had no cooling device in my home. As the days were getting warmer, I contacted my energy assistance person and asked for advice on the situation. She suggested I contact Sierra Air as they assist people in need. So I did, and was called back almost immediately. After a short conversation, Ron, the president informed me that they would be very happy to help me out. I was put in touch with Todd the service manager and within days (today) my AC was installed!
This company has restored my faith in the goodness of the human race. I am so glad to live in Northern Nevada and so grateful to Sierra Air. This community is in very good hands. thank you Sierra Air.
Joanie Wenger
Yerington, NV

We have had nothing short of a wonderful experience here. The office staff is amazing, as well as the maintenance workers. The pools are beautiful as well are the grounds. Love you Wendy, and thanks for everything

The place gets better and better.  I feel like I've grown up a bit with Vincent's.  It's all about family here.  Bring the kids if you have em.  By the slice or by the pie it's the best and always busy.  Fresh out of the oven it's a Crispy crust, the cheese just keeps pullin with as you bite and the sauce is never enough.  Such a good slice of pizza day or night.

Friendly welcoming staff. They will offer samples of just about anything,  even wine! We got a pre-made portion of lasagna to take home for dinner. Delicious! The best lasagna I have had in a long time.

This place sucks
Worse than Shenanigans

Food.....so so
Service.....Horrible
Management.....Clueless

New owner, same garbage

Under new management. Chris and his team are definitely going the extra mile to make you happy. The food is good, the standard O'Charley's fare. Served hot and fresh, I've never had a bad meal here. And now it comes with better service. I'll take it!

Thursday lunch blue plate special:

best fried chicken I've ever eaten
mac and cheese
taters
salad
tea
10 bucks

Do it.
Delicious. Very reasonable prices. Good portion sizes. Friendly service. Three of us went to dinner and paid $30!  The only complaint I have is that I wish there were more vegetarian options.

Everything here is super good and relatively affordable.  They have stamp cards and students get discounts.  If you're super hungry, you can get a bowl but it's great for even snacking.  I love to order even just a side of rice and put the little spicy teriyaki on it.  The employees are super welcoming and enthusiastic and the entire environment of the restaurant is overall wonderful.

Great place! Tuna, Edamame, Antipasto, Pork Belly all delicious! Lobster Ravioli flavors were also very nice; however, pasta itself was chewy and no real sign of lobster :( Menu stated tarragon and got sage luckily I love sage! Definitely coming back for more stuff!!! Oh , and don't forget about the music !!!!
Service is a bit strange but wasn't bothered by it

Great addition to the neighborhood.  Friendly employees, light and open space and an extensive menu.  Bonus for Cycle beer on draft.  I haven't tried the pizza yet, but everyone I have spoken to has given it positive reviews.  Enjoy the ability to share small plates and try various items.

We got a couple of cheese pizzas. Extremely thin. Like cheese on a cracker. They say the cheese is a mix of Swiss provolone and mozzarella, but it tastes like velveeta. Plates are plastic and cups for water. The eating space was nice and comfortable, but this is probably the worst pizza I have ever eaten. We gave our extra pizza to a homeless guy in the park. Caesar salad was ok. Cannoli had little flavor. Tax rate over 11%.

What a great day with Shawn!!! And a great way to spend a special occasion. I appreciate the prompt text confirmation and on time pick up. We spent 4+ glorious hours touring 4 different wineries, all with unique atmospheres. We had a lovely lunch on the patio overlooking the vines. Shawn was super fun and explained the grape growing and wine making process and tolerated all my questions with a smile. He even put up with my boyfriend's endless "Sideways" references. I give him 5 stars just for that! Thanks for a great day. We'll be back!

Best donuts in West Chester. Can't speak to many of their other offerings because I can't tear myself away from the donuts! But I have enjoyed the croissants and chocolate croissants, and they are a passing substitute on days that the French bakery is closed. (Really good - just Americanized.) Staff is always friendly, and the place smells amazing! We go again and again.

Winter cabs flight! Just as good a US Air flights. May be a little better. May be a lot better. 
"Cab-bing" a business trip at Vino Volo is a lot of fun. 

Beware though that the Terminal A location closes at 9 PM. If you are on a late flight, make sure you get your fix in time.
Great food with affordable price. Homemade feeling. Had the seafood basket and it was great.

We went in for lunch and the food was tasty but our waitress ignored us the whole time we were there. We had to pull over other waitstaff to assist us while our waitress chatted with bar staff with her back to us for the entire hour we were there. We couldn't even get our drinks refilled. Even though we returned to many NOLA restaurants for a repeat visit this was not one of them.

Well. It used to be great. But The service has changed.  The last two times we ate there, service was not good at all.  Undercooked fish.  Watery macaroni. Cold onion rings.  Very disappointing.  We stayed away for a few months then tried again.  This time service was poor, prices raised, and smaller portions.  Sorry top hog.  That's it for our group.  Won't be back.

As hotels go...the gaylord opryland is wonderful. The rooms were very clean and quiet. Air conditioning worked well. Only a few suggestions. As a gardener...labeling the plants would have been nice. Even though I knew most of the plants  there were a few I could not  idenyify. Also...breakfast was not easily found. If you didn't catch the quick changing sign in the lobby...you didn't think there was breakfast there. The water park will be an added improvement. It could also use things like mini golf, bocci, horseshoes, shuffleboard as there was not really much to do to keep kids busy except swim. I'm sure they want you to go into nashville..but I was disappointed with downtown.

AVOID AT ALL COSTS! There are many other much better hotels in the area. This hotel will cost you almost double the room rate in "added fees" that you don't see till the end, like $50 a night for room service in addition to the per night charge as well as $25 a night for parking even if you don't choose to park there. The AC also barely works so it's always hot and muggy. Also their "Free" breakfast is free because it's worth nothing, worst breakfast ever that I just ended up buying breakfast elsewhere. Embassy Suites is usually good but NOT this one.

Got the apple and bacon pizza. It was really delicious, but the toppings slid off the pizza really easy, so you had to hold it really well to avoid that. The outdoor seating was very nice and the heaters worked well. The waitress seemed a little annoyed, but it was not a big problem. There was no wait on a Sunday night, so we were seated very quickly. Overall a nice experience.

We seen this place on Bizarre Foods where Andrew had the menudo and said he liked it.  We were headed to Phoenix so we made it a point to stop off there.  Big Mistake!  It was during the week so I don't think they had menudo so I ordered carnitas and cabeza tacos.  Probably some of the worst tacos I've ever ate.  The meat was dried out overly shredded.  It's like they had it for days and just re-heated it in a pan... just bad.  There is no inside seating and you have to battle the flies outside.  For a place to get air time on a national tv program and be empty at lunch time, you know it's bad.

Can we talk crust? Yup, crust is great. Part whole wheat, not too thin, not too thick, umm just right. Great flavour and not so filling.

Try it!

We decided to get a taste of jazz and history in one fell swoop! Wow. How amazing to here live jazz nightly. Preservation Hall continues to preserve and showcase fresh jazz musicians, who pay homage to the jazz greats of yesteryear. 

The have shows nightly at 8, 9 & 10. They also have special showtimes, like when I attended, at 6pm. Tickets are $30 and $40 for VIP seats, which can be purchased in advance on their website. Alternatively, you can get General Admission seating for only $15 (once doors open only). However, here's the real deal: to get the "cheap seats" you should arrive at least 30 minutes prior to showtime. That's when the line starts forming for those tickets. Plus, you're not guaranteed a seat, and most likely, you'll be standing. But for $15 and great, live music, it's totally worth it for the 45 minute show. 

The good news is that the music sounds the same, whether seated or not. My preference is General Admission seating. Once I'm in, I sit on the window sill at the very back of the room. This hidden seating also doubles as a place to stand to see it all, when the band is really jamming. 

Although they do not serve any food or drinks, they permit you to bring drinks in. Also, with no bathroom, be sure to stop by Pat O's next door to use their facilities. (They have a gentleman's agreement)

I absolutely recommend this piece of living musical history to the young and old. You will never be disappointed by the music, though the limited seating may be a bit of a turnoff.

I've always been against big chain BBQ, but sometimes you can be pleasantly surprised. I ordered a St. Louis Style Ribs and Brisket and Mac N Cheese.
