The Ribs were tasty, with a nice bark and smokey flavor, but were a little on the puny side as far as meat. I opted for the St. Louis style instead of the Baby Back's just for that reason. The brisket was very tender, but didn't have a deep flavor that i was looking for.  It helps they have 6 different sauces to choose from. The mac n cheese was good too, and it had corn in it, which was very unexpected, but tasty none the less. Overall the ribs are thing to get here....

Always tasty food here at Three Muses.  Chef Dan Esses does a lovely job.  I also love the cocktail menu.  The bar manager does a "today's riff" every day and keeps the drinks interesting and laden with fresh ideas.  If you're a whiskey lover, this is one of the top two places on Frenchmen Street to get your fill, as they have a DEEP selection of great whiskies...even some bottles you won't find at any other bar in New Orleans, like Orphan Barrel's 28 Year Whoop and Holler.  One of the best parts is that the people who work here know New Orleans and will give the you the real deal scoop on where to hang out and what to see, which feels more "real" to me than some corporate chain that is focused on distant politeness with no substance.  Good food, live music, and great cocktails all served up by locals who know the city...winning combination.
They really do have the best breakfast sandwich!! Everything is delicious and the staff is very friendly and helpful. This is the perfect place for a nice lunch date.

This was chosen because it started raining and it was near, lol. But turned out they sure know how to fry chicken and make delicious food! We shared a chicken tender basket and I funny think I'll soon forget the honey butter biscuits.  *drool*.  They have several sauces that we tried and all were tasty. Note, you seem to have to have a code to access the restroom, so stalk someone when they enter, so you can catch the door.
good atmosphere, in a library. one an get their work done very easily. the staff is friendly and its just a nice place to be :)
We ate at Cava twice over the Labor Day weekend and absolutely loved it. The food was authentic and the staff very friendly and attentive. Can't wait to go back !!
Everytime i visit New orleans my must go place!!! Calm and kind server. Love beignet+cafe aulait+iced coffee!

I've always liked banana pudding, but the Sweet Life Bakeshop made me a believer! I had a craving for something sweet after visiting the Liberty Bell, so quick yelp search led me here. It's a small bakery with seating for about five, so many people probably get sweets to go and enjoy them in a nearby park.

All of the banana pudding options looked amazing and I was having a really hard time deciding what to get, but there was a friendly woman working there who patiently described each of the puddings to me. I decided to go with the sundae pudding, which was so tasty! It wasn't overly sweet which was perfect for me. I wish I lived in Philly so I could come here all the time! If you're in the area be sure to stop by! And don't forget to check in on yelp because you get 20% off of your order.
Had lunch here several times, prices are fair and the food is great. I suggest the grilled fish tacos...

Love their pizza and their baked goods even more. Their seeing spots cake is delicious. I love their white mushroom pizza. It's a pick up pizza joint and the service is always friendly. I also enjoy their soups!

The Whitman Roast Beef is a solid sandwich bc it includes fried oysters tenderloin tips, and cheese. This seems like a good spot to grab a drink. Interesting decorations with old typewriters, a cozy fireplace, friendly bartenders and it's much cleaner than neighboring spots. Check it out!

We went there as a group. Our meetup group chose this place for dinner & a show. They had a package with the Sketch Players. It's a great idea dinner & a show. It was not understood exactly at first that the show wasn't there we had to go someplace else but that was ok. 

All the people that were there for the dinner & show made it rather loud. It has a quaint ambiance hence the name it was a train station. With the old fashioned high ceilings & tile floors made it hard for conversation. Also the large glass windows made it unbearable to see with a low setting bright sun. So if any thought could be put into some acoustical tiles or some sun glare help with the glass without taking away from the charm it would be a bonus.

Onto the food....
I had the Herb Encrusted Sirloin of Beef 
Sliced tenderloin served on a bed of wild mushrooms topped with the chef's signature béarnaise sauce it was very good. The beef was tender but could have used a few more potatoes. I got 2 wedges. Maybe even a mashed potatoes??

My husband had Stuffed Salmon Florentine 
Fresh farm raised salmon stuffed with crabmeat and baby spinach, lightly dusted with ritz crackers and topped with hollandaise sauce. He said it was ehhh ok I tasted it,  It was awful according to me. It was like a Mrs Paul's frozen something or other.
I would think even if they did a fried flounder or something there it would be better then this frozen item they just stuck in the oven.
There was a mix up with our order. We were there for this large event so the restaurant was packed with trying to get us to the show on time they somehow missed our ticket. The manager came over & apologized & then our order came out quickly. Which may or may not have attributed to the fish maybe not being done. It wasn't hot it was only room temperature. We would try it again on a less busy night to consider possibly a better rating. However, we probably still wouldn't recommend the fish!
Service has improved over the last few weeks so I have updated my review from 2 to 5 stars. Good food great atmosphere.

I was excited to try this restaurant because I love dosa, but in the end was very disappointed. We walked in the door and while we were looking for a hostess, one of the waiters jerked his head to indicate where we should sit. Now I'm not normally picky about ambiance, but the floors were covered in something slick and the place just looked dirty. A trip to the restroom to wash up sealed the deal. It was filthy. 
We ordered the vegetable samosas, which were quite good, but we only got two, with no plates on which to eat them. Next came the Bollywood dosa and Grandma's dosa. I guess I'm just used to a different style of dosa, but these barely had any filling, and the bread was not as crispy as I'm used to. 
After waiting for about ten minutes for our check, a waiter finally came and we had to ask for a check before he told us that we should pay up front. At least, that's what I think he said. 
Sadly, I don't think I will be back unless they make some changes.

I have to say this place is a fabulous old school Italian restaurant.  I always judge Italian on how good their red sauce is and this place is up there at the top. My date had the Branzino, Branzino is the Italian name for Mediterranean sea bass, and they cooked the whole fish and de-boned it table-side - awesome.  Someone complained about valet parking but I kind of like it especially dealing with Manayunk parking all the time, and it is a little pricey but well worth it.

Decided to try the lunch buffet here after not having eaten at a Godfathers in about 12 years and was sadly disappointed, the pizza was fine but the salad was soggy and we felt rushed even though it was not busy. The busser came and stared at us halfway through our meal and when we got up to play the games our table was quickly cleared even though our belongings remained at the table as we were not quite finished.

first off the service is absolutely terrible. the waiter only came over to take our order and bring us our drinks and food. after that when we needed something we practically had to look around to hunt him down during our entire meal. he never bothered to come over to check on us to see if we needed drink refills or how our food was. even when we wanted our check he was no where to be found. 
as for the food; my sister had ordered the clam chowder and she had to send it back and asked them to reheat it because it wasn't even warm, it was room tempature. than between the 5 of us we had ordered other dishes and 20 wings (4/person) well there was definitely 20 piece of chicken on the plate; if you count the one tiny piece that looks like the very tip of the chicken wing that usually gets thrown out. 
when we brought it up to the waiters attention; after having to look for him for 15 mins, his response was the chefs usually cooks a big batch at a time so they probably miscounted so he'll bring us another wing. we waited another 15 minutes before finally getting his attention to ask for our check and a couple boxes. so by now we have leftovers all packed up and money in the check sleeve ready for the waiter to take. i wanted to leave a feedback with the manager on duty there about our meal so I asked a waitress to get the manager for me since our waiter wasn't around. now we are pretty much ready to leave and the one piece of wing never came out; that is until our waiter overheard us asking for the manager. because as soon as the manager got to our table so did the one piece of chicken wing soaked in oil. 
when we told the manager about the wings he pretty much brushed it off and laughed in our face and said "I guarantee the chefs didn't count this as a wing" and that "they probably just shorted you guys a wing and so someone else here got that extra wing". it was 20 wings for $20 so his solution was telling us he'll take a dollar off our bill if we wanted. 
i felt like that was a slap to my face and I felt a little discriminated, like if I wasn't asian things would've been different. I wasn't looking for any type of discount or freebie, all i wanted to do was give a feedback to the manager so he knows they should be more careful since this wasn't the first time they "miscounted" (in the past I've been shorted on wings and shrimps)
tonight is the last time I'm ever eating/drinking here and i will no longer be recommending people to come here.
Had the mac n cheese and fries. Delicious. Not too pricey and lots to choose from on the menu. Good service and cool vibes.

I made a reservation online 2 or 3 days prior, then the day of I called to confirm.  No problem.  It was a business dinner with clients, I wanted to show them a bit of history of Reno, and according to Yelp; good reviews.

I would give a zero for the service, in particular the 20 something girl at the front.  She is useless, and if that is the first face you see coming in - forget it.  I will never setup another business dinner or lunch there because of this young lady.  She argued, said there was no reservation, rolled her eyes, looked bored, wasn't helpful, and then when all was said and done the reservation WAS there, but she didn't "see" it.  Meanwhile the people are piling up at the door!  

Now are they SO busy on a week night that they can afford to turn a party of 8 away?  Are there really no tables available?  Really?  Or, is the hostess lazy and didn't want to do her JOB?!!  

Never going back, never going to recommend.
This place is top notch. Every time I go the food is amazing and service is great.

The carousel bar is absolutely awesome! You will more than likely have to sit and wait a while, if you're lucky someone might offer you their seat before they get up! It is cool to see no matter where you sit! I recommend the sazerac, it was my favorite I had while I was in NOLA. Unique and fun bar with a nice change of pace from the typical bourbon street bar scene.

This place is wayyy overpriced and the sushi isnt all that great. Ordered the spider rolls tempura, and an eel roll.Service was alright and nice setting.  I've had better at smaller sushi places such as  Terryinn. I wouldnt bother coming here again. Only reason was of the outside seating next to the fountain and because i live in walking distance.

Awesome place! Very friendly staff & attentive! The thing I like best is the ability to order the dishes to your own desired spice level! Other Thai places have not been so accommodating! It's always busy & not a lot of seating space...could be a good idea to call first! Their wines are nearly all from the Santa Barbara Winery & very good with Thai cuisine! A must if in the Mesa area!!
Best lil dogs just piled with chili and the finest shredded cheddar cheese! Chili cheese fries are also fantastic!
Just had the blue Duck tonight. The food is over priced for what they have, food tends to be bland and not consistent. The waitress was alright, the Duck Fries are very good though.

Don't know what it is but If my tummy's feeling icky, I can count on Chipotle's stake to fix me up. I just have to remember not to go during full on lunch time. I usually go between 2 & 4 when it's peaceful and calm. Busy or not the service is always friendly and fast!

Beautiful! I will come back again! I loved it here! Stopped by on a Monday and it wasn't crowded. There is a restaurant on the park overlooking the water. The boardwalk is fairly long and ends at a big gazebo. We didn't get to go into the gazebo since there were 2 drunks on the floor! Awful! No security guards apparently.  I paid top dollar to stay in a waterfront hotel and these 2 drunks got the best views in town for free......
Best authentic Mexican food I've had it's the best Mexican restaurant in the city you gotta try "Panchos nachos" secret menu ask the owner for them

I wish I could select 6 stars. I wish I could stay here all day. Visiting Nash for the weekend and chose this as a brunch spot. The service was on point -- thanks, Malcolm. He recommended the Cinnamonbon French Toast with strawberries and it was un-freaking-believable. Would absolutely recommend this place.

Great place to drink and eat delicious oysters!
Great service and menu has options for all.

The 1 and 2 Star yelp reviews are EXACTLY why I love coming here.

ATTENTION: There is a HISTER WATCH in effect for SATURDAY NIGHT.

Four Words:
PBR. MUSIC. HIPSTERS. BLACKOUT.

Trais and Jones West Ford in Reno did an excellent job helping with new tires at the last minute during a nail incident on recent trip from the Bay Area to Reno. We called on the same day and even though they were busy Jones West Ford was able to change the tires and provided great service. High marks to Jones-West and their 5star service department. Highly recommend you ask for Trais in the Service Dept. Great guy to have help you. Keep up the great work and thank you.

There isn't a physical wait at this place but you might be sitting waiting for up to 15 minutes because this place seems to always be crowded for dinner. Food is delicious, props to the waiter for saying 'no' when I pointed to a menu item and asked "is this good?"

Fun local place with cigar city jai alai on tap!  Food is pretty good.  Barmaids are the best.  They offer karaoke almost every night which drives me nuts but it is very popular and the house is always packed.  Go check it out
Delicious!!!!!  Friendly staff. Exceptional food.  Always looking for a good flan, they didn't disappoint.  Everything was very well seasoned.

Unfortunately we had a bad experience here...we actually ate outside on the "to go" portion of this restaurant and I don't know if they put less care into their to go orders or not but it tasted bad. We got the coconut shrimp which was ok...definitely over fried. We got the lobster tacos which were literally awful. Tasted like rubber on bitter cabbage with a squeeze of lemon...and the worst of it was that it was $18.95. To be honest the clam chowder was really good as well as their Arnold Palmer to drink and that's about it. Not worth the price or the wait at all for us.

Food was OK, nothing special.  Overpriced.  Service is incredibly SLOW, whether they are busy or not.

Looks nice from the outside, as you are driving by.  Ends the minute you actually walk in.

Definitely a better experience this time! Yes there were a few things that could have went smoother but overall I had a pretty pleasant experience at this hotel, the only complaint I have is an experience I had at Bimini Steakhouse. Overall third times a charm!

Initially liked the place and thought I liked the burger until I took a good look at it in the dark place and saw that it was extremely undercooked. It's almost 3 days and 3 IV bags later that I am finally recovering from the worst food poisoning I've ever had. Thankyou, Bayou burger.

Finally made it! The outside is worth stopping for. You can see where they brew their yummy beer as you pull in the parking lot. To the left of the building it looks like there's a place for covered outdoor seating. 
We went at 5:30 and got seated right away. 
Great selection of beers! Out table got the Christmas beer, white lager, hard cider and milk chocolate beers. All of which were great! The white lager was excellent! Wish I would have had a second. 
I ordered the burger and potato wedges. This has to be one of the best burgers in the Lou. 
Families were there so don't worry about that. Go and enjoy for a family dinner!

Excellent happy hour. Half off pizza and dollar off beers and cocktails from 4-8. Service was very good and so friendly. 90% of food is made in.horse, rest is locally sourced. And you can tell.

Me and my friend sat at the bar for 3 hours. Music was great too. I will be returning!

The new manager  tends to run a super tight ship (like the military) in that he wants to control what goes on outside his store. Control freak?  I suppose this is only natural, but he needs to be  much nicer to the homeless people and others asking for spare change in front of the store. In this economy, beggars are all over the place. I give when I can, and so should others (as long as you are not giving money to an addict). A little compassion helps. Lighten up, Mr. New Manager and stop playing Police Chief!

Another thing: this store was much nicer when it first opened. At that time the bathrooms had no buzzer locks and you could just walk in, free-style. Now you have to ask the clerk--who is handling a million customers--to buzz you in. This is absurd. Silly. Crazy. Open the damn bathrooms!!!
Not the best place I have eaten at, the table was dirty and the food was cold when it got to me

They are fast and have good prices. It cost me about 13 for a 2-piece suit and 8 for a blazer by itself. They had the clothes ready the next day. Also the drive-thru was nice to keep dry during a rainstorm! I'd definitely take my clothes here again.

I'd actually give this place 3.5 stars if I could. The food is good, however I'm not a big pastry eater so, all I've had is their breakfast and lunch sandwiches and coffee. All three are good, but I wish they had more options in the lunch sandwich dept. I should probably give them 4 stars for having the sand to open up in Channelside. I am very grateful for that, as I live there, and the area is in great need of additional restaurants. All of the staff are very friendly and the atmosphere of the place is great. It's my local go-to breakfast joint.

This place does something magical and mystical -- you'll leave here heavier AND lighter!

(That is -- you'll feel heavier, but your wallet will feel a lot lighter.)

Stopped by here on a visit to Lumiere Place; figured it was worth a shot.  Didn't know anything about the pedigree of the chef or the place -- just that it was in the casino, I was hungry, and I was there.  Seated quickly (it was late in a Wednesday evening and pretty dead).  Server was attentive, patient to answer the questions I had, and was pretty efficient.

First thing you'll notice when you open the menu - yeah.  Pricey, even for a gourmet burger joint.  You can either build your own burger (starting with a base at around $10 and adding on for extra ingredients ranging from truffles and caramelized onions to good ol' fashioned bacon and cheddar), or pick one of the select ones.  Those come with fries, so there's a slight savings there, since fries are separate for the main burgers.

The fail here is that the burgers are about 75% the size of what you'd expect to get at the local burger hut.  That wouldn't ordinarily be a problem, except that the prices are about 25% higher than what you'd expect to pay at a gourmet/specialty burger place.  Yes, yes, this place is inside of a casino, so you'd expect it to be a little pricier, but it just seemed like it was a premium price for what turned out to be an OK meal.  

This is a place to stop by if you're going to spend a night at the casino with friends and want to have something fun and cool to eat before a night of gaming.  It's not a place to stop by after you're done and looking for something casual and cheap to end the evening.

I think the 3 stars is generous; the staff made up for this visit being kind of disappointing.  I can see where this place would be appealing; it just wasn't what I had in mind as a visitor.  Now I know better.

Beautiful facility. Clean and Nicely upgraded room. No bed bugs, lol.The breakfast was certainly not your run of the mill, gloopy mess. He eggs taste like eggs and the selection is ample. Loved the little cereal boxes and milk you can take for the little ones. There was always plenty of food when I went and the to go Seattles best coffee was genius! Most of the staff was friendly; one suggested we take their shuttle to the airport, which is across the street and then shuttle from there to one of the casinos. As we were carless, this was much appreciated. The free ice was helpful, as we kept a nice ice chest with plenty of drinks and the soaps, shower, fridge were much appreciated. The pressure on the water was a little much for my toddler but I enjoyed it. Knocked off a star because the pool was only open for a limited time. I wish I could have enjoyed maybe a few extended hours during my trip there. Pool closes at 10 and with the busy schedule we had, we never made it over there. Also, while most staff was friendly there were some glaring front desk staff that made this place seem quite stuffy and unwelcoming for us. We paid over $600 for the three nights we were there. Certainly expected a much more welcoming staff for that price. We will not be staying here in the future because to me, customer service is EVERYTHING. If I feel uncomfortable walking through the lobby to my room, why come back?
Took 20+ minutes for food even though the restaurant was empty. Burger was really really bad. Never write yelp reviews, ever, but people truly deserve a warning before going to this place.
Great Home Depot - very friendly and helpful staff.  Only gripe was I bought sweet bell peppers and banana peppers grew instead but it was a pleasant surprise.

Tip: Become a member to see many films for free!

I have seen many films at the International House. I can feel they really love film and respect the many mediums of film. Films are usually shown in the original medium in which they were recorded. This makes for a much different experience than watching the films at home. 

The theater is clean and the seating is stadium seating. They hold film festivals and show many rare and foreign films. I've been here multiple times where they have difficulty starting a film. I'm not sure if that is because of the medium or because they aren't prepared. 

Anyway, I think Philadelphia is very lucky to have the International House and I suggest becoming a member for free films and special even invites.
Delicious! Everything is so good. The shrimp tacos and carne asada tacos were so flavorful. We will be back! Not often all 4 of us love a new place! So refreshing

This place is amazing. Hardworking staff, affordable care for your pets. People take this stuff for granted, where I'm from in Georgia you would pay $1000s to get your pet fixed, vaccinated, etc. but here it's so cheap- if your living in 70117 tons of the services are even FREE!

This is the closest grocery to where we are staying. It seems to have just about everything we need, but not quite. The store is clean, well stocked, and friendly customer service  (my experience). I use this store for the staples, or if I need to pick up 1 or 2 items.

Had a great experience with Geraldine!! She was very helpful and went above and beyond to exceed our expectations! The units are really clean and secure and we would recommend this facility to others!!

GF and I stopped here for a bite for dinner. Waitress was friendly and informative and the food came out fast once we ordered. This is about all that made it 3 stars. 

I ordered the matzoh ball soup to start and it wasn't the best I've ever had. Very salty. For dinner I opted for the baked Mac and cheese appetizer for my entree and that also left much to be desired. It came out hot and bubbly but the taste just seemed.. Off. 

GF got the turkey club with avocado mayo. Nothing special - she said it pretty much tasted like a Turkey BLT and couldn't even taste the avocado.

Prices were fair for the city but we probably wouldn't be back for dinner - maybe it's just more of a breakfast/lunch place.

Great comfort food! The rib and Mac and cheese sandwich is fat kid goodness and the fried green tomato BLT that was featured on Heatseekers is to die for. Service is always good here. They give you homemade chips with an amazing dip that my husband calls "crack sauce" since you can't stop eating it. They have different specials written on the board outside. Parking can be a challenge if it's busy but it's worth the hassle to eat here.

I had an awful experience. I will never order from this Pizza Hut again. I ordered online to take advantage of the 50% off deal. As I was driving to pick up my pizza (because they don't deliver to my house 5 miles away) Christine calls me and says they don't have the crust I ordered, Italian sausage or green peppers. I have to order something else. I get there and she has prepared regular breadsticks and not cheese breadsticks like I ordered. She says whatever, she doesn't care, whatever, she's tired, she will make me some cheese breadsticks. Then, the pizza (somehow) falls on the ground. She has to start all over. And to top it all off when I get home and open the pizza box, the pizza looks all mangled. Like it's the one from the floor. But I know I saw her throw it out and I waited 15 mins for the new one. But we can't even eat it. I wish I could upload a picture of it here. Unfreakingbelievable. The breadsticks were not hot (it was a 5 min drive home). I called Christine and she did give me a full refund but we didn't get any pizza tonight. After all that. Hell, I should of just went to little Cesar's, which is right next door, to get a cheaper, faster and better tasting pizza. Corporate needs to look into this establishment ASAP.

We had a clogged drain in the kitchen.  Called one company who could come out in 2 days.  Called Friend's based on reviews here.  Nicky came out within 2 hours and snaked our drain.  He stayed long enough to make sure it was fully cleared.  Will call them again if we ever have problems.
The Oasis Bar at the Casino is awesome... The Food is delucious.. the Staff is great... our server was Alexis and she did a great job... luv this place...

I visited this location on several occasions this last week and was thoroughly disappointed on every visit. From employees too busy joking with each other to help customers, to waiting for my drink because they made the drinks and food for their regulars first to having an employee offer to help, then walked away from the counter to go do something else, which resulted in my having to bet back into line and wait again. My Vanilla Latte is what you would expect from a Starbucks, consistent and good, but the customer service will keep me from coming back.

Nice friendly dudes that are willing to lend a hand. Excellent selection of mods, both authentic and clones. My experience there has been very informative. Prices are reasonable and fair. Would definitely be going back for my vaping needs.

Not a bad experience.  I am a more savvy car buyer and always negotiate over the phone. I managed to negotiate the price down $4000 less than the MSRP after calling a few times.  Originally, they did not want to lower it buy that much but they kept at it to make the sale and called me after two hours to beat the price I had given them from another dealer.

We went on a friday evening around 5:30 and were seated outside on the covered patio right away. We ordered 2 apps and a flight. The chorizo nachos were huge and decent but the trout dip with pita bread chips is what stood out! The dip came out with 6 pieces of bread placed in a circle around the dip. I asked how much it would cost to get an order of more pita bread and guess what... it was free! score! 
Since both items were appetizers they came out in a matter of 5 minutes. All around it was a wonderful experience with good weather, great service, good food and a flight with information about each beer!
The eggs in a cup-- with either shrimp or soft shell crab is exceptional-- eggs Benedict with a twist! Chef john besh rocks!

I frequently use mega bus but after today I will no longer spend any money with the company. I was scheduled for a 2:35A.M departure from Indianapolis, IN to Chicago, IL and at 2:55 A.M the bus had still not even arrived yet. When I called customer service 908-282-7420 I received a lot of unnecessary conversation and the representative Alex was rude. He was of no assistance and instead of trying to ensure the proper service to the consumer he persisted on proving a point and attempting to argue. Please listen to this phone call and take proper action to correctly train this employee. No eta, no apology, nothing!

What a great experience. From the time I came in I felt the good atmosphere. They have crafty decorations and a well designed menu. It is an all around American establishment with top service. 

We had the wings for starters and WOAHH! Were they good. we ordered the East of Melrose flavored wings and they were better than any sweet and sour alternative. I also ordered the Mayday Velvet Hustle beer to go along with the wings and they were perfectly paired. The bold hops of the beer meshed well with the tangy souse of the wings.  I would recommend it to anyone! 

For my entree I had the Smashy Melt burger that comes with griddled mushrooms and onions and Swiss cheese. The onions add a  sweet flavor to the burger while the mushrooms make it extra tasty. I cannot say one negative thing about this place. I'm beyond pleased and will be telling everyone I know about it when they crave a burger. Burger republic has nothing on M.L. Rose.

As far as atmosphere goes, I much prefer the nicer weather so I can sit outside...the inside is a bit dated but if the food's good, which it is, that's not really a factor.  Nice location by the Monon Trail which makes it a great stopping point when out for a bike ride.

I'm not a vegetarian but their veggie options are outstanding--in fact, I order them more than their meatier options.  Make sure you order the veggie chips--they are delicious, and that includes the beets. Normally, a beet would have me spitting it out in my napkin but not here.  This may simply be testament to my belief that frying makes everything taste good, but I'm going to give them the credit.  

All in all, a great low-key place to go get a meal with friends and linger...
Best thai food in the area.  Everything was authentic and delicious.  Will definitely be back again and again.

The sushi here is amazing. Is it so delicious. HOWEVER, the service is god awful. The happy hour used to be from 5-7, but they cut it back to end at 6:30. Seems more like she just stops it when she feels like. By she, I mean the woman who has waited on us the last 2 times we have been here. I suspect she may be one of the owners, as i think its a family owned place. We came in at 6:20 tonight and she began barking at us about how happy hour is almost over. She then came over and flung the menu over and walked away. She came right back, urging us to hurry, and ripped the menu out of my boyfriend's hands before he was done making his selections. So now I'm sure he will be hungry even after we leave. Its a real shame, because this place is so good, but its not worth dealing with the owner. She should stay behind the scenes.
Book ISAAC Gonzalez. He's the real deal! I was in SB for the weekend and randomly found Chandler Salon on Yelp. Isaac picked the right vibe and style for me... great technique and super cool guy too!

This is the most deserving five starts I have ever given. While visiting New Orleans I found district donates via a hashtag on Instagram. BEST DISCOVERY OF OUR TRIP. After all the bloody Mary's, memos as, crawfish ... These donuts were so exceptional.  The store does a rotation of seven donuts and has everything from wedding cake to s'mores to maple bacon. I was a little apprehensive at first because I thought they would be over the top sweet/filling, but I am telling your, they weren't!!! District donuts does it right. Oh and after our donuts we went back and ordered a fried chicken slide and a burger slider that were just as impressive.

Recently moved to Santa Barbara and didn't know anybody. Read about the bus in the newspaper  and vowed to myself that someday I would  "Jump on the School Bus". Coincidentally met the owners Darin and Sierra a few days later and was invited to ride that  following weekend. What an unconventional way to meet people and get to know the SB area for a great price! Forget stuffy wine tours and overpriced limo services...the bus was super cool. We all met at the Mission Rose garden about an hour before the bus was officially departing to pre-party and mingle. (All different age groups on this trip) Someone was celebrating a birthday so they put up a "Happy Birthday" personalized magnetic sign on the side of the bus with her name. It definitely set the party atmosphere and added a special touch.  With the windows down and club music playing, the bus took off. We stopped off at Figueroa Brewing Co. in Buellton, Maverick Saloon in Santa Ynez, followed by wine tasting in Los Olivios, then tri-tip sandwiches at Cold Springs Tavern. One of the best days ever! When my friends from back home come to visit, I can't wait to take them on the bus.

Amazing eggs benedict, fantastic service, excellent cocktails. We went to Kelly's as a group of 4 on Saturday. Due to the long wait, we were crunched for time (reservations for another event) but decided to stay and eat fast because the reviews were so good. We informed our server about the time restriction and he was wonderful at getting our orders, making recommendations, and providing the checks in record time. We all ranked Kelly's as one of the top places we ate on our trip to Clearwater. Oh, and one more thing. The eggs benedict is off the menu due to the changing hollandaise sauces. The server will tell you what specials they have for the day so don't get your heart set on something you see on the menu outside while you're waiting.

Interesting upscale interior. Very active happy hour bar scene, sort of like a meat market for the seniors. Fun to observe!
Quality of staff is average or above.
The food is expensive and does not compete in a city known for world class Italian food that is available for very reasonable prices!
Food just didn't taste that good, average at best!

We are extremely happy with our purchase, delivery, and overall experience! I'm so happy that we follow the Yelp recommendations to try this store. Great no pressure shopping experience, great price, and an outstanding value. We'll be back soon for barstool purchases.

I go here when going to Winco is too inconvenient, or when I need a small amount of items. Even with their "just 4 u" app, prices are very high. Their organic produce selection is pathetic and most of the time, they are out of things like jalapeños - or other normal items one might be looking for. That's annoying. They're also usually out of whatever happens to be a good deal. Tonight they were out of the salsa that was on sale...so I had to pay the same amount for less than half the size. The deli selection is good, so that's why I give them 2 stars. I would give more stars if their checkers were pleasant...ever. Maybe I've just had bad luck at their store...but I've gone to this Safeway a lot and tonight's annoyances were just too much all at once. I wish their was a local grocery store in Sparks with good organic produce, decent prices and friendly people.
Love this place ! Super food (healthy, unique, fresh) and great beer in a cozy community environment

Very noisy! Every time the person in the room next to me went outside to smoke I heard their door bang shut and it shook my door as well. There is also lots of noise from the parking lot since there is always marina/park/restaurant traffic. I also, didn't like the windows in my room, they didn't want to stay closed so people walking by can see in through the slight cracks in the shutters.The room was clean and the view of the water is beautiful; and this has a great restaurant next door. This is also within walking distance to downtown Dunedin. This is a great place to stay if you don't need to get a good night's sleep.

When you first walk into Citizens Bank Park, it looks and feels grand, with huge open expanses.  Then, you realize that is the problem.  In terms of seeing a game, only a few seats on the first level are anywhere near close to the action.  The rest are pretty far away, when compared with the friendlier confines of parks like Fenway and Camden Yards.  

In addition, while there are plenty of (expensive) concession stands, the service culture has not caught up to the facilities.  At the High & Inside Pub, the bartender named Harry was downright rude, and he was just one example of a place where the employees don't seem to get that you've paid a lot of money to have a good time.

In the end, this park doesn't seem to live up to its promise.

I want to say first and foremost that Dr. Dubin's office encourages patients to leave good reviews on websites in order to be entered into drawings for free iPads and other expensive things. This seemed manipulative and ethically ambiguous to me.

I have extensive damage to my teeth due to previous medical issues, leaving me with fragile molars and infection. I also have a strong phobia of dental work, so I figured that Dr. Dubin would be right for me. I was wrong.

His staff are quick, efficient, friendly, but as I continued consultation and treatment, something seemed a bit off about them. Dr. Dubin has a MA in psychology (I am also working on my psychology degree) so I figured that would be of added benefit for my fear of dental work. I was wrong.

I was told to have an extensive cleaning done, and to pay all costs upfront. It was approximately 500 dollars, after they discounted $100 for the sedation. I went for the consult, nervous and scared, and by myself, which was a huge mistake- if you're in a state of fear, your ability to make decisions is compromised. I was in pain from infection, but they said they would delay the cleaning and treatment, as they would not do a procedure without the money upfront. This was the only dental office I encountered which was reluctant to set up a payment plan for someone with active tooth pain and an abscess.

I pay the money over two weeks, and come to the office with my fiance. I was given the sedative, and was brought to the back. I was still anxious, but I closed my eyes and did my best to help the medication work. I clearly heard what was going on. All of a sudden, a sharp pain broke me from my state- he had injected a stimulant under my tongue to help me wake up- without ever telling me what he was doing. I've worked in patient care- without exception, you tell every patient- regardless of assumed state of consciousness- what you will be doing, especially if it is painful. 

I had a massive panic attack as I felt the unexpected injection, and my fiance walked to the room as he heard me, and Dr. Dubin kept insisting I was fine, while making a superficial effort to calm me down. After I calmed down, we left the office, and went home to recover from the sedative. 

The office called and emailed me a few times to convince me to return, and I mistakenly tried to rationalize Dr. Dubin's behavior- maybe I was overreacting? After all, the staff was incredibly friendly, and the infection in my molars wasn't going away. I went back, and in doing so, explained to Dr. Dubin why I was upset about my previous visit- the sedative wasn't fully in effect by the time they brought me back, he attempted to justify his actions,

He asserted that I was too sedated (I was still able to hear everything going on), but did not deny that he administered the injection without telling me. He then worded his apology as "I'm sorry that you feel that way" instead of apologizing for his poor bedside manner, and quickly left the room to leave me with a staff member for a financial consultation.

For two molars to be crowned and an implant, they quoted me in the $15,000+ range. My teeth nearly fell out of my mouth at that point. I asked if that included what my insurance would cover, as they said the initial cleaning was not covered by insurance, and I found out that they were not a participating provider with my insurance. Admittedly, I should have called my insurance company to verify their status as a participating provider, but up until I asked directly, was not answered directly.

At this point, I was in tears- my mouth was in constant pain, my finances could NOT afford it, and I wasn't qualifying for any of their loan programs. The woman, though friendly, seemed like she was taking advantage of my fear and pain to get me to make an extremely expensive purchase- all upfront, of course. 

The final straw the broke the camel's back was when she suggested I take out a payday loan. If you're unfamiliar with payday loans, they are predatory loan agencies which give you the money upfront, but charge up to 200% to 2,290% interest. I'll let you do the math.

I left, upset, and they finally offered to contact another dentist they knew (who also didn't take my insurance) and kept asserting that my dental health was more important than my finances. From the dentist who can afford the leased building in Rittenhouse Square.

Dr. Dubin may seem like he cares about you, especially if you're in pain and need a lot of work done. If you can't afford it, they will try to pressure you into making poor financial decisions, skate around insurance questions, and dismiss you if you decide their prices are more than you can afford.

I have found a more professional dentist who has since saved me mountains of money, while treating me like a human- not an open pocket with teeth.

This place is in one my top Mexican restaurants in Indy. I love tacos and margaritas. I have been to this place twice in 2 weeks. The prices are good, the quality of the food and the amount are great and the margaritas are the bomb! The first time I sat at the bar with my boyfriend and had great customer service. The next week I took my coworkers there for lunch. We al tried different things and enjoyed each other's plates.

We booked the coastal Kayak tour around Santa Barbara on July 3rd, 2016. 

Pros: Our guide was great, very knowledgable and had lots of great facts to share. The  gear was great and kayaks themselves were well taken care of and easier to handle than others.  Was expecting just a simple Deli lunch, but was surprised to get salads, wraps, fresh fruit, chips and cookies that were all pretty good!  Kayaking under Stern's Pier was a unique perspective and fun. 

Cons: We felt that the tour wasn't really as advertised.  Website says the whole tour would go from 10-2.  In reality, we didn't start with instructions until about 10:15 and didn't get into the water until closer to 11. We weren't too worried about the delay once were told we'd be back between 2 and 3, however, we were back on the landing at 1:55, pretty disappointing. The "secluded beach" was actually the Leadbetter Beach, which is next to Santa Barbara Yacht Club...which is about 1/2 a mile from the Sea Landing. 

We did enjoy ourselves, the conditions were good, and our guide was great, but it definitely wasn't what we thought we were signing up for and would not recommend this company to others.

This restaurant is really fun. It's new in the neighborhood and was very busy when I went in-- mostly young families and police officers. Seems like people were lacking delicious and affordable breakfast options. (people from BOTH parts of West Philly, if you catch my drift!) 

The breakfast basics are definitely there. The owners are nice. and the best part was that their waitstaff was hired from the neighborhood!

Go West Philly small business!

I booked a party of 14 for the Rusty Pelican for April 23.  I was coordinating a number of out of town guests who kept revising their RSVP.  I called to change my reservation number and then showed up with a different number of people.  The staff accommodated all of that with grace and charm.  We had a lovely meal with great service.  Thanks, Rusty Pelican!

I'm completely obsessed with Crossfit Zionsville!! I've always been fit and an avid gym member but after trying out crossfit I really saw a new level of fitness. The atmosphere is like no other gym I've ever been to. Everyone supports everyone and you feel like one big family. We cheer for everyone until the last person finishes. I've never felt so accomplished and empowered after a workout like I do when I complete a workout here. I'm coming up on my 3 month mark and I feel so much stronger not only from when I started but in my whole life. I strongly encourage anyone to come try out a class. You'll love the workout and you'll definitely love the members, it's a place you will never forget.

Super bummed out. Second time at this salon and my pedicure services were great but when I got my full set my nail person kept filing at my skin and I showed visibly I was in pain and kept pulling away and now I'm left with broken skin. He saw he broke skin but didn't apologize or take any interest in what he'd done. If I do come back, I'll never go to this technician again.

The cook is so fun he comes out to explain the desserts and the different things. He makes the dressings, most the meats, soups, and the desserts by himself. The gooey butter cake is my favorite! This is a must try!!!
Love this place! Everything tastes so fresh. Ordered the sashimi sampler platter and was blown away by how great everything was.

This place is the pits. I went there with a medium-sized party (with reservations) and sat outside. The waitress screwed up nearly everyone's orders, the service took more than an hour (not counting the time AFTER we got the wrong foods it took for her to get the people who even cared to wait longer their correct orders), and the stuff we were told was "spicy" was fairly mild. My spice-phobic friends ordered a green salad, which they were not warned (but told afterward by the waitress) is "the spiciest thing on the menu." We were charged an entertainment fee and a BYO fee PER PERSON for them to give us a bottle opener. All in all, possibly the worst dining experience I've had in Philly.

They went out of their way to help (we worked with John, the retail manager).  The hours are great, and they have a giant selection of menswear.  They listen to what you are telling them and get you things based on how you like what they brought you previously (size up or down, different style, etc). If you are buying a tux or suit, they may even do some quick tailoring while you wait so you can walk out with everything you need all set to go (they did this for us as well as the person before us).  They are quite helpful on working within your budget as well, if you have one.  Worth a stop for sure!

Tried this place a few days after opening. I'd get into a lengthier review, but everyone else has taken care of that.  IMO, 5 guys is far and away the best. This burger was very dry, and not very tasty. Fries are OK. I think when all the hype dies this place will be forgotten.

Smiley's Cafe is AMAAAZZZIIINNNGGGG ! If you're looking for a place with great food and great service this is the place to go! Guarantee that you will leave this place with a smile! I'm addicted to the Sweet Blackberry Smoothie & the Baklava & his chili !  I can just keep going & going! 


OH & the prices are great (:

- Sincerely the girls at Greene Street! 

Love you Smiley

This is very impressive, and the many lighthearted aspects to the ongoing video make it fun.  I don't know that it's worth going out of your way to see, but it's worth a stop if you're within a few blocks, especially at night.  The building itself is pretty, and be sure to look up to see the numerous statues of people walking on the support beam.

My husband and I came in on a Sunday night and caught a guest chef collaboration. We ordered all 16 of the items on the mezze menu and enjoyed all of the very well blended, interesting flavors...especially the turnips, everything beets salad, the pickled celery with sour cherries, and faint anise flavored corn. The feta dip was tangy, hot and sweet at the same time. The surprising crunch in the hummus and as the other reviews mention, the pickled shrimp was really delightful. The jalapeño melon salad was my favorite light and spicy and sweet.

The highlight of the meal was the grilled octopus with a light, lemony sauce and the CRAB BEIGNETS!!!! That's right, the guest chef was from New Orleans. Justin Devillier from The Petite Grocery. The flavor, the slight crunch of the corn sauce was the perfect end to a perfect meal. 

The service was excellent per Ruby.  Would strongly recommend.

Will go there every time I visit Philly. I like how you can taste the pineapple in the water ice. (even though it taste like the can pineapple) It's also really cheap so you can get one for yourself and not have to share.

Place is very nice and clean. Service is friendly and welcoming. We had about 3 different people serving us that made us feel very welcomed. The menu had plenty of choices for the two of us.
We started the dinner with the burrata and risotto cakes. The cheese was decent. Lacked a bit of salt for our taste buds but we still ate every last piece. The risotto cakes were very heavy on the breading and lacked flavor. We next shared a salad and the tomato soup. The soup was some of the best we have ever had and was our favorite plate of the night. The salad was fresh and bright. The main dish consisted of Rigatoni for me and the wife had seafood paella. The chicken meatballs in the rigatoni were tough, dry, and not desirable. The pasta and sauce were great. The paella was tasty with a good selection of seafood.
We finished the evening with a chocolate mouse tarte. The little dessert was full of great flavor.
I would recommend Richard's to anybody looking for a great night out. Service is great. overall flavors are solid. 
Cheers Always!

If you have the choice to pick your location, this is the best pasta house! Arnold went down hill after their remodel and I drive out of my way for this location. Their pasta is actually creamy and not dry. You can actually order it to go and it's still amazing when you get home. They use plastic containers not styrofoam containers which make your food taste weird.

This theater is great, shows are always good, old style melodrama so the audience really gets into it booing and cheering the actors on. We have been to several shows and haven't been disappointed with any. Little Anthony's restaurant is a great place to eat before a show or any time your in the area.

I have been here twice and all I can say is "OMG" because the food is so good. We have had several dishes and they all have been amazing. The service has been 5 stars as well. This is probably one if not the best Japanese restaurant in the area. 

After I finish eating, my next thought is I can't wait till I can get back to try something else.

Great spot for pizza and sushi alike. 

The Margherita pizza and Cesar salad have become a staple for hubs and I. Also, ordered a large Hawaiian for girls night and it was a huge, literally, success. 

Dine in or delivery are both great options as service is prompt and friendly either route. 

Side note: Superb sushi (the sushi provider at lulus) downtown is closed on Sunday (along with most other sushi joints), so if you're having a craving run over to Lulu's!

I needed to find a place to pick up some cookies or something for a potluck and found myself in this neighborhood. Thanks to my fellow yelpers, I found this bakery. We got about pound of cookies, as well as some of their famous cinnamon rolls and sticky buns. They also had cannoli that looked yummy, but we decided we had enough. The cookies were delish and were a big hit. The buns and rolls were good, although the cinnamon roll's glaze was a little too sweet for my taste. Great local bakery.

Quaint charm can only get you so far in the restaurant business. 6 of us decided to have breakfast here this past Saturday and couldn't have been more dissapointed.  Burnt bacon and toast, hard dry biscuits, cold signature potatoes that were unevenly cooked, fruit bowl ordered but not delivered, syrup that had to be specially requested for French toast, were just the beginning. Discussion afterward revealed that 2 members of our party had eaten here before and weren't satisfied but didn't want to prejudice the rest of us in case it was just a fluke. I wish they had said something. We won't be back.

I think capital beer is pretty ok to me. I dont have any complaints other than maybe price but that doesnt really bother me that much with this place. Ill go here once a week or anytime im craving sushi its always pretty good. Chinese food is standard. Great beer selection take your pick.

Short of it:
BYOB & no corking fee. Everything is delicious, but if I had to put in order of what I thought was amazing to great: Bloody Beet Steak, Salted dark chocolate napoleon, Spice encrusted trout and new jersey risotto with lions mane mushrooms. I can't say for sure where the roasted winter vegetable salad sits within the list since it wasn't my main dish - but I would say top 3. 

The details:

The boyfriend and I decided to have one nice dinner while enjoying an impromptu weekend vacation to Philly. Neither of us had been before and this was truly a highlight of the weekend.

Bloody Beet Steak: Holy Beets. This set the tone for the rest of the meal. This was perfectly balanced - sweet, acidic, fresh, light...I wanted to bury my face into this dish. It's been a while since I've wanted to lick a plate clean. But luckily they give you brioche buns and butter in the beginning so I used that as a vessel into my mouth. 

Roasted Winter Vegetable Salad: It was a hard choice between this and the Beets for me, but luckily my boyfriend got it which was also surprising because he doesn't normally like cauliflower. So is it wrong that I was hoping that he just hated the taste so much that I could have two first courses? Unfortunately for me, he found it delicious and so I was only blessed with the tiniest of bites as he scraped up the rest of the vegetables. The bite was just as well balanced as the beet steak and to be honest, if I could eat vegetables like this more often I think I could be a vegetarian.

New Jersey Risotto with lion mane mushrooms: I'm sure this was possibly called something else, but I remember specifically the waiter mentioned that the risotto comes from Jersey and the lion mane mushrooms came from a local farm near philly. The risotto was done perfectly, and had bits of black truffle along with the lions mane mushroom. The taste of the mushroom

Spice encrusted trout: I'm always hesitant about spice encrusted things. Like, is it going to be overly salty/browned/overpowering that it destroys the flavor of which it is encrusting? But I took a chance, and I'm glad I did. The spice that encrusted the trout was coarsely ground so it gave a beautiful contrast to the meaty fish. The parsnips below were so delicious and sweet which went well with the whole dish.

Salted Dark Chocolate Napoleon: Whenever I go to restaurants, my thought is always "yes to chocolate" regardless of how full I am. This isn't your traditional napoleon, the phyllo dough was crispy thin and touched with honey sitting layered between salted dark chocolate mousse topped with white chocolate cream encircled by a caramel sauce. It was exactly what I needed at the end and was surprisingly light.

Bonus points: The chef worked at one of my favorite restaurants in NY.

Wow did some do a review and say 7 dollars a pitcher, i remember when it was 5, and dollar mugs of lager, thats still cheap though. I haven't been there in awhile, but Its one of the few joints I know that has an old style jukebox, full of good shit, where you can play a single song for a quarter. Wait they might have a new jukebox now, hmm I forget. I remember going to a Dirty Franks picnic in Fairmount Park way back when, they had lots of BBQ, lots of beer, and they had a treasure hunt in the woods for little liquor bottles. I remember being really bad at volleyball that day. I also ran into one of my college professors that day. That was kinda funny.

Succulent seafood and fresh vegetables in ample portions. I would eat here every day if I could afford it.  You must try the octopus. Perfect for both an intimate date or a big group, as the menu accommodates adventurous eaters and the simple sort and dishes can be shared or devoured individually.   
Plan in advance or prepare to wait, unless you are an early eater.  No reservations. The queen village location is the smallest, and you may have better luck snagging a spot at the NoLibs location.

Excellent food and a great value! My date and I split an empanadas order, two drinks, and a main, with dessert, and it only came to roughly 60 total. There are plenty of options and you won't be disappointed. Just remember 3 empanadas coke per order, one is plenty, two will fill you up. Highly recommend.

This is my second time staying in a Hyatt Place hotel and I remain impressed. 

My boyfriend and I got a one bed room, and it was very spacious. Definitely more than enough for two people. There was a comfortable sectional sofa, a desk and chair, large tv, full length mirror and closet, two sinks and plenty of counter space. Although the bathroom was a bit cramped, the shower stall was clean and roomy. Wifi is free.

I definitely miss the bed. I never thought I'd say that about a hotel bed. It was so comfortable and soft. I slept so well because my body would literally sink into the mattress. The pillows looked kind of lumpy but they were surprisingly just as comfortable. 

The breakfast was delicious! Definitely the best hotel breakfast I've ever had. The food was fresh and yummy, and there was lots of variety. 

There is also a cafe in the lobby that sells pastries and drinks. You can also order food 24/7 from a menu in your room.

I've been here several times over the last few years and have always walked away with a happy, full stomach. The Cuban sandwiches are perfectly pressed and are enough for a whole meal by themselves, but the pastelitos are to die for and the café is strong, so come with an empty stomach to be able to fit these delights in. 

This place was originally teeny tiny without much seating, but it seems like other people liked it as much as I did, so they've expanded their seating into another room, which is brightly decorated and cheery. Overall a refreshing, lively vibe from this joint and one happy customer!

This little gem is open 24 hours and has become one of my frequented late night spots.  The Southwestern Burrito Wrap has been my go-to lately.  The Belgium Waffles are another favorite of my family.  Corn beef hash with eggs is not the best I've ever had, but it hits the spot at 4 am after a night of drinking. 
 I can understand why the place stays hopping 24 hours.  The price is right for a decent bite to eat, day or night.

I love Roma burgers, I try to have one in every city I visit but this location butchered the Roma burger. Over cooked the usually mouth melting burger so it was tough. Over toasted the bun so it was tough.
A shame. Next time I will try a different location.

Wanted to start close to the airB&B I was staying at so I wondered down to this gem. My favorite here was the live music with pianist. The cocktail I had I believe was "The Muse" and it was delicious. Love the environment friendly paper straws too! I did try the Bleu cheese stuff dates and honestly was not a fan. Didn't taste like there was cheese in there at all and the bacon that wrapped the dates tasted too burned for my liking.

Hands down the best thai food in Nashville, or maybe that I have ever had. My brother lives in Thailand and he said first hand it was VERY authentic! Also, don't even hesitate what you're going to order - get the Pad Thai. It's not the Pad Thai you're probably used to, which is a GREAT thing. This dish leaves out the Americanized "doused with sauce" style, yet keeps all of the flavor. You may want to get there earlier because there will be a wait, as the inside only seats about 25 people. Worth the wait if there is one, the staff is also VERY kind!

I'm so glad that my friend who lives nearby Twisted Tail took me here! I will be back because I had a great experience. The service is friendly, the atmosphere is very warm and welcoming and the drink list and menu have something for everyone to enjoy. 

I was here on a Tuesday night and there was an autistic performance from Niki Sbaffoni and she was wonderful! The music really added to the southern flare of the place. 

Their mixed drink menu is amazing. Try the Kool Kat! It's made with fresh cucumbers and pear vodka. It's a perfect refreshing drink. I also ordered a cobb salad and it was delicious. It was in the appetizer section but it filled me up enough to be a full meal. The ranch dressing it was served with was a new recipe house-made and very tasty. 

Go here and you will def. want to go back too!

I hate to say it, but other reviews were right. Burgers were decent, onion rings inedible due to grease, my kid's fries needed to be pressed with napkins, and the service was terrible. Service was... terrible. Waited over an hour with a 3 year old for our burgers. I love their wings, but don't think I'll eat in there again. We actually tipped another server that took care of us. I think "Ryan" was his name. Place was not busy when we got there.  Damn it! It's so close with such a good beer selection! Sorry, "Pub"... you're almost there, but need some efficiencies put in place or a talent review.

This place is overpriced and the food is awful. We had Chicken Pot pies that were small and dried up. The doughnuts were stale. The place is also in poor condition and disorganized. This was a poor groupon and a waste of money.

Very cool and unique hotel.  A little hard to get around the hotel's maze of wings and floors.  Staff is friendly but could have more employed/working because when we asked for sheets for the hide-a-bed, it took about 45 min. for someone to deliver them to us.  Fitness room is very good!

Wow, what a disappointment. It's a pretty building in a pretty place, hence the 2 stars. The service was terrible. I very rarely leave a bad review but this place deserves it. When I booked the room it was for 2 people and their "bay breeze package" but when I got here I was told the reservation was only for 1 person. This resulted in an additional charge of over $50 to add my daughter back onto the package. Since it was my first time at the hotel and it was their error, I asked if there was a comp- 1 front desk person and 2 supervisors later I was able to get 1 free drink at the bar for a house brand drink. Really? All that work for a $4 glass of wine? When my daughter's cold got worse and then she couldn't use the additional service I just paid for, neither the hotel or the spa would work with us to rebook the service, issue a gift certificate or anything else. The room was ok, nothing special. The hot tub and pool were ok, but creepy later in the evening due to poor lighting and minimal staff. Save yourself money and stay some other place that is more customer oriented.

Awesome! Stayed here for 3 days and never had a problem. The staff are very friendly and will work with you to make your stay pleasurable. The breakfast was good but they had the same stuff every morning. My last morning there they were talking about making other food to switch things up. The rooms are very comfy. I've upload pictures of the studio suite i stayed in. I also took pics of the lobby and the kitchen area. Hope everyone enjoys their stay here like i did!

We love AJ's! The specialty food selections are outstanding. We love to get a light dinner and eat on the patio. Tonight we enjoyed soup and salads. The service experience at the deli counter is sort of hit and miss. Tonight they were understaffed.  We will be back.

Saigon is one of my favorite first choice of  Vietnamese restaurants, I have been going there for so long ! great atmosphere, good food, very clean, great service. The owner is very nice, he remembers how I want my food to be cook. One of their best plates is Cm sng, super smokey grilled pork chop over medium egg, meat loaf & grilled shredded pork. It served Yasmin's rice with pickled carrots and daikon radish, of course yummy fish sauce with hot chili pepper. definitely recommend for people who first time want to try Vietnamese food. 
They also have bubble tea if anybody is looking for some smoothie, also special Vietnamese hot coffee great

I have always gone to discount tire stores across Tucson, I regularly got my rotations done at the one on Ina west of Thornydale and let's just say they set the bar high. 
 My service at this location was average.  I walked in and there was no one in the lobby, so I had to wait ten minutes to be acknowledged. And I understand they are all working, but my experience at the other store someone always said hello. They had a 3 1/2 hour wait. Which was almost double what it usually is. Understandable. They gave me call when my car was ready, the guy handed me my keys and told me to pay. No thank you, how are you, no hello...
On my drive home I noticed a noise. So the next day I called and talked to Anthony and ask him if I could bring it in. He said yeah and to ask for him when I got there. He immediately took my car for a test drive and looked at it in the shop. All in all he fixed the problem with no hesitation and mention the was sorry they didn't fix it yesterday. 

Morale of the review: Overall this location is sub par to other locations I have visited. But ANTHONY IS THE MAN And will probably be the only reason I go back to this location.
Great traditional Mexican tacos. Favorite is their mixed alambres. Perfect for lunch! Well priced for downtown.

Samurai, has the best Sushi in Villanova. I am never disappointed when I eat there, there rolls are fresh, and unique. Their house salad the "Ginger Dressing" is always a perfect starter to the meal. My normal meal is the Deluxe Sushi Sampler, or a Bento Box both of which are amazing, I am not a tofu lover, but their miso soup is superb. The service is also great, very kind and it is very fast service. A small and quaint little restaurant, with amazing food and service . I have had Herosame, and it is nothing compared to Samurai. And I believe Samurai Sushi actually had better  sushi then Mori Moto. Thank you Samurai!

It was a pleasant surprise walking into this restaurant from the customer service to the food. If you're ever staying at the Hampton Inns and looking for great tasting Mexican food at walking distance check out El Pollo RICO. I ordered 1/4 of chicken plate and my boyfriend ordered the 1/4 combo chicken with tri-Tip we left with happy belly's. The salsa bar also carries a variety of authentic salsas from mild to hot. Enjoy!!
The place is nice and the flavors of the donuts are okay, but the donut itself is bad. It's like eating paper or a po boy bread with sweet icing on it. Donuts here aren't good. Just eye catching.

We came in looking for a Saturday night dessert and were immediately taken by the puddings. Ended up with the peanut butter after trying a sample of the sundae flavor -- both to die for. What an awesome little spot.

LOVELY little knitting shop that I was happy to discover last summer.  Forgive me for forgetting to write a review until now.

Every time I've stopped in since then, there's always a contingent of knitters purling away at a table.  The ladies at the counter are always happy to help you select yarn, patterns from the huge library of patterns in the back or to print you off a free one from their system.  They have a nice selection of monthly classes as well as private lessons and one day, when I'm not so slammed at work, I hope to take a lace knitting one.

The store is neat & tidy and the shelves are stocked with a lot of yarn selections.  As a previous reviewer noted, there is a large amount of acrylics available, but there's a lot of luxury as well.  Ah, mohair - how you call my name and fuzz my shirts during projects...

The walls are also covered in knit examples to inspire you and random knitting doo-dads to tempt you. Join the mailing list & they'll keep you updated with the latest fiber festivities.
I have been several times and continue to go back due to the good service and great food.  Great place to bring clients with a nice wine list.  Unique to Indianapolis and worth the reservation.
The root beer float donut blew my mind. It was delicious and the pop rocks on top were genius!
Just tell 'em Georger sent you. They'll take good care of you.

I've been to every sushi place in Reno and this is by far my favorite. Excellent service, great sushi, and amazing deals during the week. The staff is super friendly, attentive, and this place is always busy, which speaks volumes about the place. TV's for sports while you and all you can drink beer on Mondays? Who doesn't like football, beer and sushi on Mondays? Highly recommended.

Food: 4
Decor: 3
Ambiance: 3
Service: 2.5
Value: 2.5

The pizza is good, and the fried pizza dough is even better. However, I still find it hard to stomach spending $60+ for 2 at a pizzeria with communal seating.

Basic Italian pizza--some of the best if you know how to order well.  

Long overdue in writing this review. Have been to Lulu's a number of times--it's a close walk for us but somehow avoids some of the touristy scenes--hint they don't stand outside and solicit you to come eat there. 

So, let me give you the run down on how to order well at an Italian pizzeria: chianti, fiesta salad, pizza margherita, (both with homemade mozzarella!) finished with espresso.

Order some chianti by the glass--happy hour specials have been in action every time we go for late lunch.  Next, the Fiesta salad--perfect to share with two--is delicious with homemade fried zucchini spears, arugula and roasted red peppers. Add a pizza margherita to this order and you and your date are in Italy having an almost real Italian pizza.--sorry nothing actually comes close to the real thing, but this experience is the most accessible IMO and I lived in Italy.  At the end of our last pizza date, the very nice Italian man whose service is continental in every way (read non-obtrusive!) came to check on us.  When we asked about espresso, he looked at me as if to say, "but of course!"  (I didn't see a big espresso machine so I thought they didn't have it.)  I'm not trying to over build it--it's just going for pizza, but if you want good pizza, this guy makes his own homemade fresh mozzarella--which just makes the pizza margherita.

Okay, add to all that two things:  

1.  Great space for large crowd with teens, vegetarians, etc.  (non-fussy, not super expensive for family crowd, everyone is happy)

2.  We just ordered delivery  tonight and hello under 30 minute delivery!  Great way to serve up great salad and pizza at home with no fuss.

We love you Lulu's! Hope you stay where you are in Old City for good!

Valentine's dinner, $70 a person, Filet mignon was  on the menu when it was served it looked more like pot roast. I called the owner and told him I was disappointed with the meal and said my girlfriend told me not to say anything at the restaurant. Said I didn't want to cause a scene. I didn't enjoy the meal, he said sorry you had a bad experience and hangs up on me. I was getting heated, I agree, but not to the point of complete anger that warranted to be hung up on. I called and said I'll send a picture of the meat. He texts me a picture of (as he says) "standard grade filet". I said it's not filet mignon like was stated. In the end he wins, it's not the servers fault the meal was trash, they got my $180 dollars so good for them. I'm sure their food is amazing on any other night, but tonight was supposed to be the tops and what we got was sub par.

Besito Mexican is an absolute gem! The food, the service and the atmosphere is fantastic! Walking through the doors of Besito Mexican makes you feel as though you've been transplanted to Mexico. The vibe and atmosphere of the restaurant is very authentic. 

The food is excellent, fresh and delicious. When you visit Besito Mexican, definitely order the table side chips and guacamole. They are incredible! I ordered two appetizers, both were amazing! Be sure to start your meal with the Tacos de Camarones and Tacos de Carne Asada. For an entree, I ordered the Filete de Res al Chipotle. The meat was tender and perfectly cooked!

I ended the meal with Besito Mexican's complimentary churros. They were warm, fresh and delicious just like the rest of the meal. Throughout the meal, the server was very attentive and always had a smile on her faceI really enjoyed my experience at Besito Mexican and will definitely be going back again soon!

Like the convince of this place to the Residence Inn hotel. The food was excellent and service was prompt. The server brought desert on the house at the end of my meal, which was a nice touch. 
I will definitely be back for more of the delicious Indian food.
Wow! People in Indianapolis are the friendliest. Took recommendation of gregarious rental car guy and headed here. Great waiter and the best steak we have ever had!

Hands down, the best burger I have ever had! I rarely order burgers (no pun intended!) when I go out to eat, because they're usually low quality and not cooked to my liking; Plus, typically there are just other menu items that appeal to me more. But this one...Juicy, grass fed beef, medium rare, topped with the best bacon I have ever had, on the most deliciously grilled egg bun...And I didn't even order the burger, my dining buddy did! The burger was so large he couldn't finish it, so I got to have several bites of it myself. It's definitely what I will always remember most about Home Wine Kitchen, at least until my next visit!

For myself, I ordered the "Lunchbox," which is a revolving lunch special that, for $14, includes a beverage, lunch special of the day, and dessert. Not too shabby. The lunch special the day we were there was a tuna nicoise salad, and it was also excellent. The dessert was a chocolate cake with fresh berries that definitely did not disappoint. 

Since our visit took place during lunch on a Saturday, we ordered a couple of adult beverages with our meal. I had a fantastic cider, and he tried a beer called White Rascal that I called "the best Belgian white beer I have ever had." So yum. 

Service was attentive, and the decor was much more robust than when a restaurant called Nosh last occupied the space. However, the main dining area isn't very large (maybe 8-10 tables). I was surprised to see how busy it was for a random Saturday afternoon. There's a large back staircase you can see from the main dining area that apparently leads to a private event space upstairs. We didn't go up there, but this place seems like it would be perfect for a birthday party, shower, or other special event. Also, the location can't be beat, and with some recent closures, I'm glad to see a new restaurant in Maplewood. I just hope it's able to stick around longer than some of the other restaurants in the area did, so I can come back again and again.

I've only eaten here once for lunch, but it was excellent. The decor inside is not the nicest, but the food is very good.
I had the Shrimp in garlic sauce and it was perfectly cooked large fresh shrimp in a delicious sauce.
I would go here again.

They don't usually take reservations, but saved us a table for six for my wife's birthday.  We accidentally ended up there during their happy hour from 3 PM to 7 PM every day. It was a great atmosphere, and the food was very good. Wait staff was very attentive to our needs.

A quasi political rant and a store review all wrapped in one, so enjoy. 

Ever since Target hit the scene I really have to ask, "Who even goes to Kmart anymore?" I asked this to myself out loud the other day as I had to get my meds filled due to a sinus infection. No one looked at me odd, as there seemed to be several people talking to themselves. I now go here because of the stolid contractual war between Express Scripts and Walgreens. Thanks you two....idiots.....qausi-political rant over.

This store is harshly bright, rather dingy, and the selections, especially in the electronic section, are on the cheaper end.  On top of that, I've found the mainstream DVD and Blu-Ray movies are overpriced.  I laughed at the men's area, especially the young man's department, as they had a tv with music videos playing. I laughed because it just seemed a lame attempt to be cool and creating a shopping experience that you will find at a department store like Macy's or Dillard's. This is hard to create when everything is whitewashed. You will feel like you are in that August Burns Red's "Whitewashed."  The best WTF moment is discovering the opportunity to purchase Joe Boxer male thongs. Who knew that Kmart cared about male panty line?

One great tip is you can find patio furniture cheap during the off season and clearance days. I bought a great patio table for under $50. So, keep that in mind.

The extra star is for the pharmacy, as they filled my prescription out efficiently and with the greatest of ease. The hours are little later than Target.  No problems there and credit when credit is due!

The later 80s quote, "K-Mart sucks", remains as true as ever and who knows, you may even bump into someone who still dresses from that Tom Cruise era who cares about male panty line. One never knows?

I stopped here with my boyfriend to have a late lunch. Besides having the coolest most amazing boyfriend anyone could ever have. I also had the pleasure to be served by Tina. She was very attentive to our every need. She was a true joy to be served by.


The burgers! They were fantastic! With the never ending fries it was also a great value. 

Thank you mr Johnny rocket and Tina ! We will be back!

Our stay at the Bourgoyne was nothing short of amazing. We came for Jazz fest in May 2014 and wiill definitely be returning again  this year.
