The location and price are unbeatable and the hospitality of Jay, the inn keeper, was outstanding. Beautiful courtyard, clean rooms, and tons of charm. It's situated just beyond the loud/wild area of Bourbon, so it's pleasant to return home to. The rooms are modest with a queen bed, tiny kitchenette and bathroom but if you're visiting Nola you're missing out if your planning on spending most of your time in the room anyways. Make sure to sit and chat with Jay he is super knowledgeable about the area and will certainly leave a lasting impression.
The best taco I have ever had!  Seared Ahu Tuna Taco,  I can't wait to visit Tampa just for this place!

I have to say being a regular customer of Rouse's there is a big improvement in the customer service since it was Sav-A-Center. There are the cashier's that will look at you like you are crazy if you try to make conversation with them. Then there are the regulars that are actually nice. I went yesterday and had a cashier that was completely mute. And I loved hearing the bag boy mention how he hoped no one else would get in line so he could get a break. I do have to say the managers are great. The tall bearded wine guy is always helpful. And there is this one short guy that's always gathering grocery carts that will ask if you need help loading groceries. That is always nice!

We stopped in on the recommendation from our uber driver and this place was great. The service was on point but the food was better! The crab mac and cheese was hella good. The grilled oysters had this amazing butter park creole sauce. They even made a special poboy with half gator, half shrimp for me which was so flame. The crab cakes were also legit. The decor is that only school New Orleans vibe. Def recommend.

Cute little restaurant. Very good for Sunday brunch. We avoided the long lines of other NoLibs and Downtown places. I had the Huervos Mexicanos , very tasty. 
Attentive service. Wide menu, authentic Mexican food.
This place is delicious. Brought my 10 year old who said "Dad, I'm literally crying right now this restaurant is so good. I don't even eat vegetables and I ate everything."

Got in under the wire for their pre fixe lunch deal. Had the goat cheese and shrimp crepe to start. Must admit I've had these before at FQF,, and as usual outstanding. Wifey ordered the fire grilled pork chop with red beans and rice.  I ordered the blackened catfish. Oops, several minutes after ordering told they ran out of the catfish. Oh well, nothing wrong with a pork chop for lunch.  It was fantabulous..tender, and you could tell it was fire grilled by the grill marks and the flavor. Oh we had a curry tomato crab soup, also outstanding. Also included was a glass of wine. $20.00 bucks!!@@ are you kidding me. Going back tomorrow.
Horrible!  Don't do it!  10x10 room with no charm, a l lumpy bed and a shower I had to wear shower shoes in.
The food is ok but  service is too bad. I think I will give them ZERO STAR if I can. I dont know the women who is at front desk is boss or manager but she is so weird and rude..

Went a few weeks ago for a quick lunch. The employees there were incredibly helpful and explained how the menu works. They even let us try the different meats to see which we liked best. Everything was fresh and delicious. Try the chips and queso!!
This is one of my favorite restaurants. They have the best burgers and the most amazing unique menu and a delicious selection of craft beers. Love coming here great food great time.

I stayed here for four nights and got a pretty decent look at how things ran around the hotel. It's a nice location right outside of St.Louis but still not too busy. A walmart and a Schnucks is right across the road for all your needs. Check in was a little rough as they still had to do finishing checks on the room when I got there which resulted in a 5-10 minute wait at the desk. The pool was decent, just your basic rectangle and nothing fancy. The room itself was nice and a average hotel room. It seemed clean and the bed was comfy. I had an issue with the toliet and the deadbolt on the door at some points but nothing major. Also the water pressure in the shower was HORRIBLE. I ended up only using it once so I'm unsure if it was a one time thing or just because there was a lot of water use going on at the time. It also took about 3-5 minutes for the water to heat up and get hot. The cleaning staff was excellent and cleaned our room twice during our four nights. The free wifi was spotty. In my room I got only 2 bars and ended up resorting to use data most of the time, but other spots in the hotel had full bars.
 BREAKFAST-
On the weekends it ends at 10am and during the week it ends at 9am. I (and a few other guests) were not aware of the change (as it was not posted anywhere and when we checked in, the front desk all told us that it ended at 10am) We came in around 9:10am on a Monday morning to eat breakfast. There were still things out on the tables and one worker who was cleaning stuff. She proceeded to come out and yell and mumble to herself while cleaning up the breakfast that we were 'ridiculous' and needed to 'read the damn hours'. At this point I just grabbed the rest of my breakfast to-go and awkwardly walked out of the room. The same worker was there every morning sitting in the back 'kitchen' making phone calls most of the time and frequently forgot to upkeep the breakfast food/area. At one point I saw her mixing pancake batter in the sink...
Overall the food was average, some type of egg and meat, bread, muffins, pastries, waffles/pancakes, coffee, juice, cereal etc. it didn't taste bad, and overall it got the job done.

I guess I would stay here again. Definitely not for a long amount of time, but maybe for a one-night stop. It's nothing fancy but it will do the trick.
My brother and I ate here to celebrate my college graduation and I must say I was very satisfied. Great vibes in the restaurant, our waiter was outstanding, and the food was delish.

Wow ok I found so far the best Sicilian in the Tampa area ,finally

Pizza was excellent with thick crust base layered with a very well balanced sauce and generous amounts of Mozzarella. The end result was Sicilian that can hold its ground by some of the best I have eaten. My only bit of criticism is that at this price point $15.00 , it should be 12 slices not 9.
Props to you Joel for recreating a pizza that reminds me the Pizza homeland.

This was my first time at the C house. The service was great, our waitress was very friendly. There was a woman, that I assume was the manager, running around checking on tables including mine and filling in wherever needed. The food was pretty good.. we had their chef's cheeseboard. This was a fun choice although next time I will likely just do a board where we choose our own meat and cheese. The poutine was also pretty good. We had champagne and wine which were obviously good. I also ordered a tequila drink, Comfortably Numb, that was good and somewhat different.. it was a little smoky and citrus. My favorite part was the live music. We were there on a Thursday night and there was a guy singing and playing guitar. He played a lot of good songs and played well. I would go back.

I went here a few years ago for a cut and brow wax and never went back. The haircut was first, and the stylist didn't say a word to me (aside from the requisite how-should-i-cut-your-hair). That would be ok if she were focused, but she seemed distracted by her friends. And it would still be ok if she gave me a reasonably good haircut. But she didn't.

Then, here's the clincher: I was taken back to the spa area for my brow wax, and to my surprise I had one brow done by a student (I forget what they're called - the people who don't cut hair) and one done by a hair student who said she "really likes waxing." It took about 40 minutes and they were uneven AND they left lots of stray hairs. Most concerning was the fact that the lights were dim and they didn't use any kind of light. I do better with my own tweezers at home.

I probably could've made a fuss and gotten those girls in trouble, but I paid my money and ran.
I love Ruby! She always does my eyebrows nicely and is a nice person. Her studio is clean and elegant! Would not go anywhere else!
I've been going to this location for over four years and have never had a unsatisfied experience. I highly recommend this location!  Great rates & the customer service is amazing! 5+ Stars!!

This bar has it all. Multiple $5 city wide specials, awesome whiskey selection, cheap beers but awesome atmosphere. The bar tenders are great too. Super friendly and conversational. If you have 10 dollars in your pocket and want to have a good time in a respectable bar, come here. (Also if you're going to festival pier for a concert like we were, this place is awesome to grab a drink beforehand)

Enjoyed dinner on the back patio after a sunset viewing on the pier a couple blocks away. 

Ordered the Mega Mary for an app, and my wife and I split it. Granted, it wasn't the right time for it, but we just had to try it. Glad we did, they make their own mix and topped it with a strip of bacon, a pickled string bean, and two bleu cheese stuffed olives. Their cocktail selections were great. In fact, they had an entire page for just martinis. 

Ordered the local ravioli with chicken and the filet with kale and sweet potatoes for our mains. Got the chowder which was great, not the creamiest but I'm okay with that. The mains were very tasty and rather large...probably too large for one person. The steak was cooked to perfection. 

As if we weren't stuffed enough, we had to order another cocktail for dessert, can't remember the name but it had vanilla ice cream and tasted like a milk shake. 

The wait staff was attentive and friendly as well. You can't lose of you choose this place in Dunedin.

Benefitting from the limited options available in Bala, La Collina is the epitome of a traditional Italian restaurant.  Uninspired menu of things like chicken Parmesan, and tortellini soup.  The waiters, while pleasant, were all very old and slow,  I'll be back, but only because its the only real option for a business lunch in the neighborhood.

The staff were all very friendly, they are the ONLY reasoning behind two stars!!  I wish I had read the Yelp reviews before we booked this hotel!  We booked it because it was one of the few in our price range with free parking and it was a last min decision to visit Nashville.

Upon check in, we were greeted with a smile and warmth.  The lobby was nice and updated.  The front desk girl asked us if we preferred a floor and inside or outside room for our King (they have rooms with entrance on the inside like a hotel and on the outside like a motel-weird).  She gave us a map of how to find our room and we were on our way.

First off, there is only one elevator, it's slow and it's the only way up and down with suitcases if you don't want to carry them.  Upon entering the area with the elevators, we noticed it wasn't so nice inside anymore.  Hesitantly, we went to our room on the third floor-outside (figured maybe less foot traffic).  The door to the room was all dented and painted half assed and chipping.  As soon as we walked in the room, it smelled horribly strong of bug spray-There was no hiding it, but we tried with my body spray anyway and turned the ac/fan on right away.  We had been driving five hours, so at this point we just wanted food and to lay down for a bit.

After having dinner down the street, we came back to the room to get ready to go explore and the toilet clogged-#1 TP minimal- and it OVERFLOWED all over the bathroom floor into the foyer of the sink onto the carpet (sink is NOT in the bathroom-tub&shower are separate).  I called the front desk asking for maintenance to come with a plunger and towels and they send housekeeping with extra towels & doesn't speak English to understand what we needed, so we had to show her.  About 10 mins later the maintenance man came, unclogged and called housekeeping back up to clean. He said he had just unclogged one right down the hall, second one in less than an hour.  He was very nice and lighthearted about it, but didn't seem concerned.  Housekeeping came back up and cleaned.  Total fiasco from start to finish was about 25mins.  After all that, I called the front desk to cancel our second night in the room and booked another hotel downtown to get out of the nasty place for the next night. We couldn't cancel and leave then without losing $180!  When I asked to cancel the second night and told the lady what just happened with the toilet, she didn't even offer a discount or to move rooms-just said "ok, it's noted-please check out in the am." 

At dinner we realized this hotel is not close to ANYTHING we wanted to do, that is when we discussed booking the $300 room downtown and all of those things happening after dinner, it just sealed the deal to get away from this place.  After settling down a bit in the nasty hotel, we decided to try the restaurant in the hotel as it had good Yelp reviews. We just went down for desserts, drinks & heard live music playing. It was amazing, we recommend that place!

When we got back to our room, I turned the ac down from earlier when we entered and tried to cover the bug spray with my body spray, I noticed there was MOLD all over the vent of the ac and my husband noticed an extra "popcorn ceiling" sprayed area where it had leaked.  We didn't want to stay there so badly that we shared my one pillow I brought in fear of using theirs.  Needless to say, we didn't really sleep. Not that we could with the traffic from the highway, people walking by all night and the loud banging all around.

8am came and we were up and headed downtown to the Hyatt Place Hotel.  I tried to fix myself up enough to just hurry to leave and the plug in by the sink didn't work. Anytime I plugged something in, the gfi outlet kept "blowing".  The shower also clogged with water to my ankles when I showered the night before. 

Gotta say, I hope Marriott realizes what they bought and what they stamped their name to with this place. They tried to update it in the rooms, but it was cheap and gross. Too many shortcuts for costs and not enough class doing it.  I wouldn't stay at this hotel if it were the last one in Nashville. I'll sleep in my car. I can't believe we WASTED $180 for a night in this place. We stayed in a Crowne Plaza for $140 in Los Angeles and it was like the Mansion spa resort compared to The Inn being a dumpster behind an old restaurant.  Classless disappointment.

This place is definitely a hole in the wall. It is located by a gas station in a mini shopping plaza. That being said, the food here was delicious. I had a steak Milanese torta which was recommended by the cook. It was very tasty. The bread was fresh and the seasoning on the beef was spicy and delicious. This place is definitely worth a try.

I ate here last night for the first time, and was underwhelmed by the food. The fish sandwich I had was tasty, but the sweet potato fries tasted just wrong (like they were fried in the bad oil), and they remained uneaten on my plate. My friend said his cauliflower buffalo bites were mediocre (he's had better). Ambience-wise, it was REALLY loud, even after the waitress had the music turned down. I prefer restaurants where you don't end up with a sore throat the next day because you spent the evening shouting to be heard across a very small table. Our server was pleasant and prompt. And the decor is nice.

I grew up in the area. I have been going to this theater all my life. It is an older movie theater. This theater has comfy seats. The prices for tickets and consession are pretty expensive. That's why I don't go there much any more

I have been to Thailand numerous times, this place is OKAY.  They consistently drop the ball on authenticity/flavor for quite a few of their dishes, including pad Thai, which is sad.  It's not terrible food, it's okay tasty, but it's not anywhere close to the flavor of Thailand that I'm looking for.  If you're looking for authenticity, go to Tong Phoon in Fairview Heights.  Much better and actually cheaper....and.....AUTHENTIC!

Mike's is the place to go if you're downtown and looking to satisfy your ice cream craving. Decided to go here after the place we were originally going to had a long wait, and it was a great choice. It was my third time here, and as always I will definitely go back in the future! My parents got the butterscotch shake, sister got the mint chocolate chip, and I got the coffee fudge. Would definitely recommend all of the flavors.

Loved this tasting room. The views are ridiculously beautiful and we sat out in the sun on the most perfectly warm day sipping our $10 flight. 3 whites, 3 reds. Absolutely loved their Zin. It was the best of the list. Service was great and knowledgeable and not the least bit pushy. It's worth the walk down the pier even if you want to skip all the rest of the touristy stuff.

Ok, I accidentally discovered this place on my way to the Tea Room but they were closed on a Monday. The place was big, no actual theme going on and lacked the cozy feel. 

I ordered the Chai Latte, it wasn't the powder kind so it actually tasted good. Is it my favorite? Well, no but it was a cold day, the price was good and the location was convenient. My friend ordered an egg and cheese on an English muffin and she said it was tasty. I think I would come back again but this place needs to be more inviting and warm. 

One thing I really disliked and I dislike this about other restaurants/cafe's is poor ventilation over the stove/ovens/toasters. I hate smelling like the food that you have prepared for me or other customers. Literally, my clothes smelled like food and I was nauseous the rest of the day. 

The staff/owner was really friendly and he seemed to really know his customers which is very important.

Fun, no-frills atmosphere, right on the water, where you can watch passersby and dolphins alike, while enjoying great food and accommodating service.

Members of our dining party ranged from a picky 7 year old, to two 40 somethings and a 72 year old grandmother. Captain Bill's had menu choices for everyone in our party, and they even made some ingredient substitutions for us. 

The food arrived hot, fresh, and exactly to our specifications. Wait service and wait time were on point, and we all left the restaurant satisfied and having enjoyed the experience. We'll be back to Captain Bill's next time we visit John's pass. I hope you consider it too!

Grilled artichoke was phenomenal and the saltwater grill salad was divine. Staff was very friendly and helpful.  Definitely will be returning.  

Parking can be difficult at times, especially on a weekend.  Sitting outside is an option but not on a summer day.
Was able to make an appointment the day I called. Took my dog in for anal gland expression and a nail trim. Was in and out of the clinic within ten minutes and the cost was only $30! Very happy!

There is no denying that this place is fabulous! Service is excellent. We went for a group event with a set menu. They chicken dish was amazing. I don't think others liked the lobster risotto as much. The calamari and hummus and risotto balls were also great. The panacotta dessert was to die for.

If I could give zero stars I would. They were so rude. My order was wrong and instead of being nice and bringing me the correct food they threw together something that I didn't order again. Never going back although I hear the food is good.

I've been here many times and I always come back. Great location! The service however is touch and go. It's also noteworthy that I didn't see any African American servers or bartenders. The food is good, but not great, and I haven't seen a mouse the last couple times I've been. Enjoy!

Went back after the first time, same great atmosphere and outstanding service.
This time we tried the Chirashi and the Hako Roll, both are outstanding.
The Chirashi (gigantic!) is very tasty, the great variety let you try different fish (all delicious) and for sure, you'll not walk out hungry!
The Hako Roll, a house specialty, is incredible.
I'm quite traditional regarding food (been half Japanese, and half Italian, I grew up with incredible flavours surrounding me and I love the clean, traditional flavors) but the pairing of strawberries, unagy, and other incredible fish is so well balance, fresh, sweet, tangy that will blow your mind!!! Kudos to Tomo's chef!!
Liked this place. Veal was tender, pasta was al dente, sauce was good. Will go back.

Sushi burritos sound like a strange concept, but they are absolutely delicious! The shrimp crackers were also surprisingly good. Quick service, reasonably priced for the good-sized portions. Will definitely keep coming back!

I would totally give this a five star rating if it wasn't so busy every time I go. There are many activities for you in addition to your kids but it's almost bad if not worse than waiting in line for a roller coaster at six flags to go on the hayride. The food there is delicious albeit pricey and the people who work there are friendly and helpful.

The best thing they have going for them is the freshest of their items, which is something that is hard to come by these day in the Chinese food industry. I find that  some of their items are really good while other are lacking in the taste department. However, overall its a descent restaurant and they are just starting out; they will get better with time and experience.

Snellgrove's is a small town dinner that has very friendly staff and is family owned and managed. The meals are the perfect amount for the price.I was a little concerned that I wouldn't be full and that I was paying too much for just a chicken wrap but I was very wrong. The chicken wrap was one of the best I ever had and was definitely filling. There is a pick-up window around the back that I like for quick lunch breaks.

This place is amazing. First time here. So super cute. They have kombucha on tap, I was offered a free slice of cake as they are celebrating something to do with apples I think. Everyone was super nice, friendly and helpful. They do many things to support the community and just has a great vibe. Will come back and learn more about this fantastic little spot.

Camille has been cutting my hair for awhile now and she always does an amazing job! She listens to what you want, and is very talented... I have a fairly specific look (stacked in the back, extreme angle, side bangs) and she always does it perfectly.  In fact, now both of my roommates are going to her as well!  Plus, it's a great value.  Ask for Camille when you go in!

People were friendly and provided great customer service. We arrived before the store opened (we were still on Texas time) and were 4th in line, which would have made us fourth to be helped (with the exception of those who had appointments), but we weren't. They opened the door and said, "We made a note of who came in when so we'll take people in this order," then started calling out vehicle makes and colors without any regard to who actually got there first. They completely skipped us - didn't even have our vehicle marked on their list, and when we politely mentioned we weren't on the list, we got an "Okay," as a response. A quick and easy flat repair turned into an hour of us sitting and waiting while they helped at least 2 customers who arrived after us. Other than that, it's Discount Tire as you would expect it to be.

I come here when visiting family in the area. Not every week but often enough. Service is average, but they accommodate a lot of people quickly. Once walked in with a group of six and they didn't bat an eye. Handled the group quickly and efficiently. Sometimes they are too quick and nail color is not applied too well. I wish they could speak English to be able to communicate more easily.

We went for our anniversary. Wow!! Best steak we ever had! We had the ribeye with crabmeat and bearnaise. Perfectly cooked and seasoned! Service was impeccable, busy Saturday night but functioned like a machine! Anthony, our amazing server recommended we get different side dishes because they are large enough to share. He was spot on! We shared mushrooms and onion rings. I didn't care for the onion rings. I guess I thought they would be the thick rings. They were stringy. My husband enjoyed them. We also got the famous St. Elmo shrimp. Sooooo good! Building was beautiful, barhrooms were clean. Great time! Can't wait until we go again. I was to try the prime rib pizza.

Huge portions and great prices. I made the mistake of ordering my food spicy. I couldn't handle it. I teared up like a wimp, but took it home and finished it off with glass of milk. 
Give it a shot!

I found this place after searching for the best breakfast in Nashville.  We arrive there around 9AM on a Monday morning.  I was expecting it to be busy.  There were alot of empty tables.  I heard one of the employees say they are packed from about 930AM till 1PM and he wasn't lieing.  When we left around 1015 there was a line around the corner!  

I had the Grill Cook's Medley minus the onions and peppers.  It was very good but I did have to send it back to be warmed up.  I didn't care for the cheese not melted.  My partner had the Pecan Pancakes and said they were very good!  

We have the address saved in our GPS and when we return to Nashville on another trip across the country we will be having breakfast again at the Pancake Pantry!

While often loud and busy, the food is amazing.  Brunch is available everyday of the week and always tasty.  But I've had both brunch and lunch and they're both delicious.  Make sure to try the fresh squeezed OJ!  

If you're going on a Saturday or Sunday for brunch, be prepared for the long wait.  Seriously.  But definitely worth it!

The room is clean and thoughtfully arranged.  I'm staying for a few days, so having a little fridge is nice. I love that you get water for free in case you need it. The gym is basic but spacious, very clean and facing out over the river patio, so you can look out and watch what's going on. For me this is a big plus as I find watching tv on a treadmill depressing. The outdoor patio has comfy seating and a fire pit. Love it! Overall I am very happy staying here. 

The only downside is the food. The bar serves good snacks but you can only have flatbread for dinner so many times. They sell a decent variety of snack in the lobby 24-7 too, but again, not dinner.

Oh yea, almost forgot, the parking situation... Valet parking is expensive so if you plan to be out during the day, just park on the street overnight. You can get a spot for free 8pm-8am and it's 75 cents per hour the rest of the time.

Went here on a Saturday morning for breakfast. Seems to be popular with the neighborhood folks. The kitchen is really good, the portions are large and the food scrumptious. We had a pumpkin pancake with walnuts and a ham and mushroom omelet. Both dishes were great. The coffee is weak, tasteless and watered down, so if you're after a nice cup of java in the morning, this is not the place for you unfortunately. This alone ruins it for me no matter how good the food itself may be,

I'm giving it two stars because our waitress was rude, hurried and stressed out, which coupled with substandard coffee made for a very unpleasant experience despite the food being really good.

I'm a wing-lover, so I decided to eat here recently. In short, the wings were fine; nothing special, nothing bad or great. O! Wing Plus is a bit different from all the others. The wings are fried, and then soaked in sauce. To me, I wouldn't even call it sauce on most of them. It was more like oil, grease or the like. They didn't taste too bad. The parmesan wings didn't taste as good as they looked, but it was so-so for me. On my three visits there, I had the ten wings combo (with fries and drink). The supposedly hot wings weren't as spicy (sorry guys I've had better...). The crinkle cut fries were alright as well. I did use them to dip into the leftover wing sauce on the plate. Which brings me to a point: this is probably the first wing place that I visited that doesn't offer dipping sauce (like ranch and blue-cheese). But I got by. Plus I had the blasting Top 40 music to keep me less bored. All in all, it was A-OK.

My friend and I were strolling around New Orleans on vacation and wandered into this amazing place hungry and thirsty.  What made us choose to eat here was watching all the local police officers roll in for lunch.  It's a well known fact that the police know who has the best food in town in any major city.  Best decision we made all week!

The food is exceptional to say the least.  By far the best bread pudding I have ever had.  The chicken is mouth watering.  The staff are friendly and the owner seems to know everyone who comes through the door.  Leave your diet at the door and enjoy every bite.

I loved this place!  We drove down from Tahoe just to eat here!  The 90 miles round trip was worth it!  The food was that good!  The Chicken Basil was the best!  And they have good Boba Tea!

Don't believe the nay-sayer about this place.  The food was pretty authentic Taiwanese.  Try it and see for yourself!

All the food was good. the steak here was cooked perfectly; it was fantastic. And I am definitely going to recreated the onion compound butter at home. If you want a cozy restaurant experience definitely recommend.

First trip to Nectar, food and service was amazing. The owner visited many times. Group of six, shared the Queso and Chips with guacamole, salsa and Pepita Hummus. All great but the best was the hummus, very unique. Bowls, fish tacos and quesadillas excellent. Will be returning soon!

My family and I eat here often and I have never been disappointed. The Salsa is so fresh and amazing. The Brunch is delicious and the Mimosas are only $1.  The last time I ate here I had the crab cake with creole tomato and crawfish sauce with an egg on top (don't recall the name of the item) it was SO AMAZING! My husband had the seared tuna fish salad and he said it was fresh and really tasty. Our son and nephew both had Quesadillas. My nephew told me they were the best he ever had, even better than Taco Bell (Hey he's 5). Great place for families and pets.

Waaay down hill! This place used to be great but the selection and service has seriously declined. Nothing but tempura shrimp rolls on the menu. Really really slow service. Lunch time today with 12 people in here and its taking 10 to 13 min a roll while sitting at the bar.
This used to be my favorite place in town but i probably wont come back again. Way too many better choices in town.

I love the atmosphere and decor here.  However I was not a big fan of any of the beers I sampled.  They seem to do a lot of Belgium beers and I'm not fan of that style.  Still had a great time though!
Their wings are the best I've ever had! It takes a while because they're baked. This is the only place I go to when I'm craving wings!

Never had a bad experience here.
Pizza is always top notch. Great sauce and the blend is great. I mostly order the regular pie, but I have ordered hot subs a few times.
The chicken cheese steak was great, but my all time favorite is the eggplant parm sandwich. Perfectly fried eggplant with a good amount of cheese.
Super friendly employees. Never have an attitude. 
Can't wait to come back for more!

There are so few DECENT restaurants in this area let alone excellent ones! All I can say is wow! We had friends in from out of town this weekend and were really pressed as to where to go because they were tired and we didn't want to go into the city. Chestnut Hill has nothing worth talking about and we didn't want to go to a place with bar food.

First of all it is really beautiful inside. The atmosphere is fun, yet elegant. The female bartender is so knowledgeable. She is truly a breathe of fresh air. We started with a few of the signature cocktails which were made with fresh house squeezed juiced and mixers (unheard of) and they were delicious. No, they are not the $6 crappy drinks from the bars in Ambler, but they are not using Ocean Spray either. I had a French 75 which was knock your socks off, out of this world and my friend had a pumpkin something or other, which quite frankly I would not have ordered because I don't like sweet, but it was actually delicious and not sweet at all! The others had two tried one of the wines by the glass and a craft beer on draft. 

They have home made chips at the bar and they are so addictive I had to move them away. We did wait past our reservation by about 15 mins for the table, but I called late for our table and it was a Saturday night. We didn't mind because the atmosphere at the bar was so enjoyable.

The dining room was relaxing. the chairs were comfy. the service was friendly and good. Appetizers were all very good - Salmon Tartar, Carmelized Brussel Sprouts (never a fan-I am now-crazy but true??), grilled ceasar and a clam something or other than was incredible! Entrees were Salmon, Hanger Steak, Halibut, and Scallops ans Gnocchi - everything was perfect. Too full by dessert but we did move on too bar for...drum roll Absinthe!! 

HEADACHE next day! Such a fun night...the staff was just so much fun and everything was great. This is our new spot!

Awesome place near Sylvan Park.  The place is really neat.  Looks like a hip garage.  Lots of TV's and options for seating - bar, tables, indoor, outdoor.  I sat at the bar and was served by a great bartender named Rose (not the owner but she treats her customers like she is).  She is very knowledgable about the beers and the menu.  They have an awesome selection of locally brewed draft beers.  My cheddar/bacon burger was juicy and cooked perfectly to "medium rare."  It is hard to find a place that will give you a medium rare burger.  Waffle fries were almost as good as Chick-fila.  I will definitely be back.
Really enjoyed the Hibachi menu choices this visit. The miso is tasty, the veggies are fresh, and everyone had leftovers! We'll be coming back!
kinda boring sushi, and a little pricey. I wish we had went to the Pizzeria next door instead...

Cool place for lunch on a sunny day. Ate inside with the garage door open. Very laid back, southern atmosphere. The fried horseradish pickles were awesome. Thick cut, lightly breaded and delicious. Chicken tenders were moist and good. I'd eat here over Gus's 100% of the time. Get the pickles.

We were seated immediately by the window.  We were greeted by a young and friendly woman with great recommendations, which we took.
Stuffed mushrooms with alligator, turtle soup using the basket of buttered French bread I used to dip in.  I ate waaaaay too much of this!
After our order was taken, the appetizers were slowly and enjoyably eaten.  After a little chatter, we got all our entrees in 18-minutes.  BBQ shrimp was the best I've ever had.  Living in Slidell for 16-years, I had eaten a lot, but not like this.....I must recommend.  Three of us had perfect pasta dishes,  and my brother had Redfish Marsala,  which was also amazing.  My. Best friend. Got the BBQ. Shrimp, his wife had the catfish topped with lump crabmeat.  Hot crisp, flavorful, amazing....I mean amazing.  I am a CIA chef and know what I'm talking about, and this is the place.
A few desserts to recommend...that would be all of them, which we had.  The pecan pie was the most impressive.  You know most pies have the super sweet gel like pie filling with some pecans.  This pie was all pecans, slightly sweet, and served with a scoop of ice cream.......this proves there is a god.
I told the manager, the #2 cook and the waitress it was the most amazing dining experience, and I have had ever.
Thank you all for a once in a lifetime meal.

AAA does a terrific and professional job of installing glass in cars.  They're modern, quick to get back with a quote and get the job done in exactly how long they say they will. 

I had my car broken into a week back and my driver's side window was broken.  I called them on a Saturday afternoon and got a quote and an appointment for Monday morning.  I was busy in the morning so took the 3 p.m. appointment.  When I reached there the guy told me it'll take 2 hours (the same time he had said on the phone) and I was prepared for that because AAA is really close to the Transcend on 99th street.  So I walked down and got my coffee fix and some work done, while they fixed my car. 

Good service, would go to them when I finally decide to fix my windscreen (still waiting for a couple of cracks to complete their propagation).

The atmosphere is great! Drinks are unique. The reason I'm giving 3 stars is because I feel like the food quality had gone down hill. The last couple times I have eaten there the food has come out cold. I guess it's better to go during lunchtime instead of dinner.

This is the spot for coffee and Cubans in Pasco! A great little gem hidden away in Trinity. Every time I have been in I am greater with a smile and friendly service. Everyone seems to enjoy working there. Nice sitting area outside and inside has newspapers to read while you're sipping your cafe con leche. 

Cubans are hands down the best I have ever had. The bakery items they have in the warmer are perfect if you don't have time to wait for a sandwich.
Sarah is incredible at what she does. She is honest and tries her best to give you what you want, while trying to keep your hair healthy. Very reasonably priced. Love her!!

Feel the need to report an amazing dining experience at Hearthside after the four of us all agreed it was the best meal of the year (and it's October!). 

From the moment we walked in we were impressed. The decor is upscale and classy, yet you get a bit of a beachy vibe given all of the windows were open to let the fresh air in. 

You could hear people enjoying themselves before we even sat down, and it seemed like everyone in the place was smiling. Overall ambiance added to the positive experience, music included. 

I had high expectations of the food after hearing positive reviews, and Chef Dom did not disappoint. We literally ate almost everything on the menu (we all shared), and it was all amazing. I'd highly recommend the carpaccio as one of your starters, any/all of the pasta dishes, the scallops, the chicken, and save room for carrot cake. 

Yum. We'll be back.

Came here for lunch. The service was good but the food was underwhelming, especially for the price.

Ordered the...
1/2 dozen stuffed PJ oyster ($19)
Croque Madame with fries ($15)

The oysters were stuffed and broiled over a shrimp and crab mix. They were very salty and had very little flavor.

The Croque Madame is two pieces of bread with ham covered in cheese with an egg on top. This dish was also very salty with little flavor. The Croque Madame along with the fries was cold.

Holy crap. My favorite dessert inside my favorite breakfast? The banana goo literally oozes out from inside the giant slices of French bread. Good thing I walked here because I'll need to get up and move around when I'm done with this.

Amazingly I had never been to or heard of this place, once again yelp comes through in the clutch!!

katie's is the type of neighborhood restaurant I love. Relatively small, outdoor seating, great menu options. Crawfish Beignets? Nuff said.

The pizza is great and man is there a lot of it. I'd definitely encourage anyone in the mid city area to check this place out.

They cancelled on my 9-months-pregnant-wife and I the night before we needed them at our house to clean for the baby shower that weekend and didn't have a backup they could send us. Definitely left us hanging with no explanation and a terrible compensation offer. We actually had to push for a refund and dispute that they'd already charged us when they said they hadn't. So: they can't cover no-shows, can't manage their accounts, and don't understand how to work with a customer who depends on them. Nice.

Went here last week after not eating here for over five years. Hasn't changed a bit.

Slow service (just like France), great crepes (just like France), unpretentious setting (just like France), French music playing (just like France) and most important, cutest French waiter (just like France)!!

This isnt a date place. Its not a good place to serve a large group of people, not a good place for children and isnt the type of place if you have sooo many dietary restrictions. 

Go in, enjoy a fantastic crepe and leave. It's that simple.

Walking down Chestnut street, this place is easy to pass by so- just don't. Go on in (if there's a place to sit) and find a cute upholstered chair or spot on an old leather chair, or snag a spot on a vintage velvet seat next to the window.  Share a couch or sit at the bar and enjoy all that Tippling has to offer. 

Overall, I like and enjoy this place, like the decor, like the drinks and like the bartenders. However, the cocktail list can get a bit pricey.  Two drinks for $34.00? What did we order? The menu is quite fancy and there are a lot of offerings.  I only threw back one egg white whiskey sour (which was delightful) so I need to be sure to come back to check out the rest of the spirits. 

Service took a bit of time, which was odd, since when I was here it wasn't crowded. 

The speakeasy feel is a bit overthrown by the open windows, well lit space and open floor plan but this isn't the 1920's/1930's- prohibition era has ended at last!  Comfortable and perfect for a smaller group.  

Overall, decent place but nothing that left a lasting impression on me
Outstanding- first the service was great friendly and natural type homely feeling. Salads tasty and fresh, and French dip to die for.

This place is great! The po boys here are delish, the drinks even better!!!! The service is fantastic, our server was so cute and fun, she just had that vibe of a person you want to get a drink with and discuss... Well, anything it is fairly new and not yet established, but I have no doubt we will be coming here next trip. You can watch the parades if you come early and get a good table. If you go, ask for Dee and she will set you up right! This will be a stop we will make out next time in!!!

Goood stuff. BIG sandwiches. Good selection of chips. Super friendly staff; helpful and accommodating. I loved my turkey/avocado/bacon sandwich. They did NOT skimp on the almighty avocado. My only complaint is there isn't much seating to accommodate the lunch crowd (literally a line out the door) and our order took a bit longer than expected, however they were apologetic and threw in a cookie to make up for the delay. We'll definitely be back.

First and foremost, i am a new baby vegan and have not consumed egg or dairy or meat for almost 4 months now. I know, I know, tell me about it. 

I dined here on 07/29/17 and asked my server about vegan options. She went over the menu with me and I decided on a bowl of the Mediterranean Vegetable Bow tie pasta, sans pesto and cheese. It arrived, it was hot and delicious and filling, I paid and left. 

A couple hours later, I ended up feeling quite sick, and I wondered if it could have been something to do with my food, so I googled the nutritional information and found out that my pasta had egg in the pasta noodles, and dairy in the sauce. My waitress lied to me. 

I know it's not that big of a deal, I'm not allergic or anything, but come on. If you're not sure about the menu, ask. 

If I could give 0 stars I would. Never again BPS.

I stumbled across this awesome shop on my walk to school. I met one of the wonderful proprietors Jen. I definitely enjoyed my Soy Salted Caramel on my way to school! I look forward to seeing more decor in the space but I cannot wait to go back and try some of their food! Welcome to the neighborhood!!!!!!
Love the food- wait staff is attentive to allergies and very accommodating. The drink pours are paltry at best. The bourbon tasted watered down...disappointing aspect to the dining experience.

The staff here is friendly and seem to know their customers. It was quiet and not very busy, so ordering and food delivery was about 10 minutes.

I ordered the Suzette Crepe which wasn't very good. The sauce was warm and the strawberries ice cold. I took one bite. The waitress was very nice about it and lowered the cost, but I just couldn't eat those frozen strawberries.

I suppose this place works for some people.  Personally there are just too many other amazing breakfast places to try and if this place wants to make it, then they might need to step up their game in the food department.

Again, the hospitality saves this!

All I have to say is this place is great.  Great FOOD, SERVICE and ATMOSPHERE.  I had the pasta primavera.  Just what I was looking for!  Joe my server was awesome!  Great comunications skills, service and has such an uplifting personality.  Manager had great things to say about her employees and she even helped incoming customers with seating and menus!  Looks like she has a great crew!  

Thanks for your service and look forward to coming back when at this location.

I am the one who had the half green tomatoes served on my salad and brought it to the attention of management. The menu listed egg on the salad and there was none. The manager comped my salad and apologized. The table where we were seated was on the corner of the restaurant and I ended up with the sun full in my face. A man seated in a booth behind me was having the same problem. I turned around and sat on the other side of my table but the sun was still shining into the side of my eye and was very uncomfortable. My son's tacos looked wonderful but were served cold so that was not a good experience either. I'm not too sure that we will be going back there again.

Service in bar can be slow on the weekends so if you are in a rush, ask to sit in the dining room.  Everything gluten free is AMAZING!!! (Especially the BBQ chicken pizza).  The salads are also awesome!

What great little place. Awesome food ambiance and service. We had the specialty of the house eggs Benny with smoked salmon spinach and capers. Yummy!  Nice champagne with cranberry. Tell your friends.

The service and ambience are great, the food was fine. We ordered the nachos and the chicken grinder. Nachos were good (although I will NEVER understand why Boise puts olives on nachos). The grinder had a spicy sauce I didn't like but the husband did. The chicken on both was good. Very attentive servers, we went on an afternoon and they were extremely welcoming to our small kid. We really liked the decor of the place and the bar is huge. Husband had the Locomotive Dry Stout and was happy. They have some limited outdoor seating and offer four for $4 beer flights. Glad to have this place on the west side of town, definitely a good addition to the fairgrounds area.
Great place for big groups. Friendly service, I asked for what they recommended and they were 100 % on point. You can pretty much customize anything you order. Bathroom smells amazing, lol...

First of all, I think this might be my first Yelp review about "fast food." It's not a genre I ever eat unless I'm forced to on a road trip.  However, I am from Buffalo, NY, and am a chicken-finger connoisseur, so I decided to give this place a chance.  Additionally, it was on a road trip of sorts.  We had been at the beach all day and were halfway back home to central Tampa.

The service is amazing!  I have never seen fast-food workers who take so much pride in their jobs.  These people were drinking the Zaxby's cool-aid!  They seemed more like Disney employees than fast-food workers.  Both a female counter gal and a male (possible the manager/franchisee) went out of their way to make sure we liked everything.  

The food was a solid 4 stars, but my review overall is rounded up for the above mentioned points.  We had the chicken finger sandwiches on Texas toast.  While the chicken fingers themselves were super juicy and moist, the Texas toast was too greasy to eat them on.  I love sauce and enjoyed the variety.  We tried the Zax, hot honey mustard, insane hot and ranch.  What is missing from the sauce variety, for me, is a spicy bbq and blue cheese.  Serving ranch with hot sauce is an insult to the folks in Buffalo that created the cuisine.  Aside from the bread and sauce small issues, I really enjoyed our meal.  Additionally, it was so cheap!!  $12 and change for 2 meals with drinks.  

I am a fan!  This place doesn't quite hit all the marks of Buffalo-Inspired food, but it does a pretty good job of putting a southern twist on chicken fingers!

I have been going to this gym for years! 
Love the gang here , Theresa the manger , Jennifer the personal trainer. And the gang behind the counter.
Also great protein shakes as well !
The gym has all the equipment you could possibly need for a work out ! 
The prices are awesome and if you get the tanning package with it even better!  Why go anywhere else!

Rich A.

Great ballpark inside and out. Fantastic sight lines with an amazing view of center city. You can walk around the whole ballpark and not miss a pitch. Ashburn Alley has plenty of areas to watch the game, grab a cheese steak and beer as well. Awesome food and a great beer selection located all over. When the Phils are winning, this place is rockin. The outside brick facade is pretty cool and there's also Mike Schmidt, Steve Carlton, Robin Roberts statues outside and a Richie Ashburn and Hall of Fame announcer Harry Kalas statue on the inside. My favorite part of the park is by far the ivy covered brick center field backdrop. Go Phils!!

Ate here for the first time recently. Quaint atmosphere, somewhat dark inside. They do have a few outside tables. The octopus was fabulous!! Very tender and great flavor.
However, they need to update the menus. They have pasta with grated cheese as an option with the meatballs. When we asked for it they said, "no pasta" I pointed out that it was on the menu. The server simply said "Oh those are old menus". Also,  lunch and dinner are on the same menu. We arrived at  4:30pm and were told it was time for the dinner menu. The lunch menu offered the octopus and the "spread" sampler at one price and the dinner menu offered the same items at $2 & $3 higher. 
I would definitely go back for the octopus!!
Good not great... out of homemade biscuits so no biscuits and gravy. Utensils were dirty. Service mediocre. Probably would not come back.

I love eating here.  You get the classic diner feel along with great service and good food.  Its not open all day unfortunately, but you can get a great breakfast or lunch for a great price. They have great burgers for a couple of bucks, and if you're there for breakfast you can try a bacon and egg burger!  It's not on the menu but they made it for me at 8am and it was great.  My girlfriend and I eat here pretty regularly and we both leave full for about 15-20 bucks. Enjoy!

Wow! This place is amazing! We just moved to Nashville last month and after reading many great reviews I finally had a chance to try this place out at lunch today. It's difficult to find a non-chain ice cream shop these days. The owner takes pride in making his ice cream and gelato fresh, with many homemade ingredients and he spent the time to tell us about the flavors. My husband had the dark chocolate mint, and we were told that he even makes the mint extract that went into it. Pretty impressive! I had the bananas foster ice cream and it really was to die for with a nice (ie not fake), subtle banana flavor and the taste of homemade caramel throughout. I'll definitely be back!

In Tucson for work and it was lunch time.  This is a Small place on the side of the road in a dirt kind of lot. Looks a bit shady from the outside and definitely wouldn't have stopped if we weren't told the place was good.  I ordered 12 wings and split the flavors between the garlic Parmesan and the medium buffalo, The wings came out and i realized that it was WAY more food then expected since the wings were gigantic.  they were cooked perfect and the flavoring on both were amazing.  My friend ordered the chicken tenders and a basket of bacon cheese fries.  the fries were awesome and enough to be a meal by itself, the 12 tenders was enough food for 2 people!  overall, the food was amazing, prices were very reasonable for the quality and the amount of food, and the girls working we all friendly and nice to look at.  can't wait till i'm back for work and can stop in again!

The staff is great. They are friendly, genuine and caring. But how on earth are we supposed to relax or sleep in a room that feels like 86+ degrees. 

It was 100 degrees outside and we needed to cool off and relax after driving up from Maryland. There was no relief in our room even though the thermostat said 60. They brought up two box fans when we asked so that helped a tad but when we're staying in a $400 rm hotel, I expect a comfortable room. Even room service noticed it was extremely hot and we should keep fighting. It was cooler in the hallway.

PROs:
- 1/2 mile from Liberty Bell and attractions 
- cool hotel, different from Marriott that's right across the street 
- cool bar, food served till midnight 
- 24 Hr room service 
- pay as you drink bar in the room
- the manager was nice enough to comp us all fees outside of the room charge (parking, meals, etc)
- valet gave us cold bottled waters after asking how our stay went
- Starbucks across front door 

CONs:
- older hotel with a ton of floors 
- not the Marriott with all of its newer features like A/C
- tough to pump the A/C up to the 17th floor especially when it's a million degrees outside 
- they were willing to move us rooms but the only one available was a double bed and the air wasn't much cooler, not worth the move
- they said engineers were working it but they never came to our room 
- foyer and elevators smell old and musty
- valet-only parking is on 12th St: $48/night with in/out privileges 
- no fridge except for bar fridge, we shoved our leftover cheesesteak sandwich in there
- we woke up in the heat and couldn't wait to get out of there
- I'll never stay again

My experience here fell slightly short of expectation. At close to $50 a head just for food, I expect the best of all things. The service seemed a bit disjointed. Each course was brought out by a different member of the wait staff, which might just be my own personal pet peeve.  Secondly, our table was not wiped down after each course, something commonly done at restaurants of this calibre. Additionally, the fish dishes our table ordered (specifically the trout, and the mackerel), were a bit bland.  

On the positive side, I was blown away by the rigatoni I ordered as my main course. It was wonderfully spiced and had something in it that gave it a crunchy texture. Splendid!  The buzz was great and I loved the layout of the space. I would go back, but I would hesitate before putting this restaurant w/in the top 5 restaurants in the city, as it seems everyone else does.

First I must tell you, I was excited about visiting this restaurant. I had bought a voucher from Groupon for $50 worth of food for 4 or more people. 
However I was told since it was only 3 of us that we could not use the voucher. 
This did not make any sense because they could have prorated the coupon for 3 people at $12.50 each.
 However I believe the restaurant's motivation for allowing us to leave without the using voucher, is that they want each party to spend more money. Therefore if we used the voucher we would not go over the $50 limit.
They will also only allow certain menu items to be consumed with the voucher. Maybe Groupon shouldn't allow Erawan to advertise.
They displayed poor customer service and has not won me over!
They would not engage me in the conversation and could care less that they lost customers.

I left there and went to Banana Leaf at 1009 Arch Street. The food at Banana Leaf was excellent and the service was superb. I will continue to frequent Penang at 117 N 10th Street and Banana Leaf than spend my money at a restaurant that has no respect for their customers and has poor customer service.

I just got home from a 5 day, 4 night stay at this hotel for work. I have never been to this location before, but have found the staff and amenities at Hampton Inns to be about average. This hotel is recently renovated, which is nice, and the workout room and breakfast area were above average. I have 5 stars to this review however for one of the front desk employees, Daisy. 

The second night of my stay, I dropped an earring in the bathroom and it landed behind the sink fixture. I tried to no avail to get it out, so I went downstairs to ask if maintenance could come and see if they could retrieve it. Daisy called for backup and went up to my room with me, prepared for anything. She got a broom and different size paintbrushes to try and help in pushing the earring from the tight spot, and laid down on the floor with me with a light shining to see if we could find it. (All of this is happening at 10:30 pm, mind you). 

Together we still couldn't get it out, so she left a note for maintenance and showed them herself the following day where the earring was, all while I was in Tampa Bay at a conference for work. Maintenance had to remove a piece of wood off of the sink fixture, but they got my earring!! Big kudos to the amazing maintenance staff, and Daisy specifically for going WAY above and beyond to assist me. I will definitely stay here again when I'm in Tampa!! Hooray Daisy!

Best pizza around. You could order anything and it will come out perfect. Everything is made fresh, and the pizza is the best. The calamari is one of our favorite sides, as well as ordering the white pizza. I reccommend this to anyone looking for a delicious meal to eat!

I finally made it to Mac's on a Wednesday night for Quizzo.  I'm a huge Always Sunny fan so this place was pretty much guaranteed two stars.  Some of my friends are regulars so they know the bartenders.  The servers were really helpful in setting up our oversized quizzo team table.  I only stayed though the first round, but the questions were decent.  Only problem is that its really hard to hear the questions in the back.  I definitely think this needs a spot in the UYE Cross-City Shuffle.
I was there Friday had the muffaletta and red beans and rice.   WOW ! The food is amazing flavorful and spices abound

This place is GOOD.  Parking is a challenge, as is getting a table, both are because the place is popular.  

Organic coffees, great foods.  I really enjoyed the breakfast crepe and the fritata.  Also a wonderful latte, with a cute design.  

We were in Reno for 2 days, and went here the first day.  Liked it so much, we went back the 2nd day, despite this being a little outside of where were were staying.  I"m sure there was a starbucks closer, but this is definitely a better choice by far!

Wish they were closer to where I live!

I frequent Louis Pappas.  The menu is great, service is easy, never been disappointed with the food..the only thing is that the restaurant smells terrible either because of the plumbing/what they wipe the tables with/bathrooms or all three of those!  It cheapens the experience so I get take out.  The Greek salad with the potato salad is amazing and so are the hummus and pita chips.  My favorite is the tuna melt and the simple but delicious lettuce wraps!  The gyro is awesome but I warn you that it is easy for you to rack up the dollars here with tempting and rather expensive add on's.

Not much to say but this place didn't disappoint. Food was excellent, customer service was great and we timed it right with no wait (very unusual for this place). Put this in your list of restaurants to go to.

Beautiful wedding venue but beware booking a summer wedding. We recently attended a wedding here and we knew it would be unbearable during the outdoor ceremony given 110 degree weather but the reception inside was almost worse! The place had very few fans and the temperature on the AC box was 80! Our whole table was sweating and using the beautiful chargers for our dinner plates to fan ourselves. It is a very pretty facility but super uncomfortable for summer weddings. We also didn't see anyone in charge during the wedding checking on the details and helping the couple make things go smoothly. Wouldn't be my first choice of venues.

I have to say that I have stopped going to this Petsmart for grooming because of the staff.  Each time that I've walked into the grooming part of the store, either I am not acknowledged at all, or I am met by a blank stare until I say hello to someone. If these people are this unhappy, then they should probably find work elsewhere.  And even though my dog looks cute when they are finished, which is why I gave two stars, she almost always has scrapes and red places underneath her that look like she was burned by the clippers being too close, or too hot. Another reason I have stopped taking her there.

This place is a real deal !!!! My son has multiple food allergies & going to restaurant is so stressful!! Our server Rose she went above and beyond to make a custom menu just for my son . She made sure what he could have and they came up with a meal not on menu . Made sure that there was no cross contamination. He enjoyed his meal & we had such a peaceful, stressless & happy family dinner . Our food was excellent . The staff in general are very pleasant but Rose is very hardworking and passionate server who loves her job and takes it very serious. This will be a place that we will be visiting often specially for my son with food allergies!!! Thankyou !!
The concept of Foodery is kind of cool. Too bad the people who work there are unnecessarily rude. Rude employees = I won't be back!
Worst meal we have ever had in Nashville. Duck risotto uneatable, bones in fish, brought a wrong meal for one of our party & rude waiter.

I wanted to like this place.
I love the decor, love the couches on the porch for waiting, love the large patio and the fact that it's dog friendly.  I love the wallpaper on one wall for the banquette tables, and most of the menu looks interesting.

The problem is, that's not enough.
We arrived at 4 PM on a Saturday, and there were about a half dozen staff about and four customers at two different tables.  The hostess greeted us promptly enough, but she first tried to seat us at a table right at the front door, then the table adjacent to that in the middle of the room.  Did you recall I mentioned there were only two occupied tables in the place at the time?

When I asked for a banquette table (only one was occupied), she asked if we could wait while they cleaned off one towards the back that was a 4 top.  That was fine, we didn't ask for a 4 top but it was preferred... and that table along with the other two 4 tops that were not in the front door were dirty.  At least we noticed fairly soon after that the clan of servers cleaned off the other dirty tables, I guess preparing for dinner crowds, just makes you wonder why they waited.

So we're seated after some cleaning, and immediately upon sitting down the quietest server I've ever had approaches and asks what we'd like to drink.  The drink menu is a full page small type, so I just ordered a water while I pondered.  Thought about noting this place is only 4 months old... are you that used to regulars?  He came  back three different times as we were talking and hubby had to take a phone call... I'm not 100% sure what he said each time because again... quietest server ever.  Our receipt says his name is Oscar.

Opted for an autumn sangria ($12) as did hubby and we ordered some Pub Rolls ($9) as a starter.  The sangria was OK, but not very fruity and not overly special - esp not for $12 each.  The app was quite good, think Mexican inspired egg rolls.

About the time our appetizer arrived, a huge storm that had been brewing washed over the restaurant and completely obscured the windows... I'm so glad we had rejected that front door table.

For dinner, I had the Harvest Pig sandwich ($16) with sweet potato fries and hubby had Fish & Chips ($16).  My sandwich had way too much bread for the meat portion, and the other accompaniments mentioned were barely evident.  The fries were OK... but a bit chunky and limp for my taste.  Hubby said the fish was good, but their tartar sauce and randomly ranch sauce both are strong on dill.... which he dislikes and does seem odd in tartar sauce.

Portion sizes were generous, neither of us finished our meals but we did order the BACC to go because of some yelp mentions and the fact that I love peanut butter.  Really love peanut butter.  I asked our super quiet server was BACC stood for, and he sheepishly wouldn't say the words "Big Ass" that precede "Chocolate Cake" for this dessert offering.  The cake was the biggest disappointment, and at $12, especially disappointing.

Maybe I read the menu wrong, but I thought the cake was chocolate cake filled with peanut butter and iced with peanut butter icing.  Sounded fabulous - but not what I got.  It was definitely chocolate, and if it's possible it was super rich but not super good.  I wouldn't have thought that was possible prior to trying the BACC.  There was no hint of peanut butter anywhere, and the chocolate cake seemed blah, and the chocolate icing was joined by chocolate syrup and chocolate chips on the outside, joined by ice cream.

While it was too much even for two people, and it wasn't the worst dessert I've ever had, but it is possibly the first restaurant dessert where I've ever thrown out the uneaten portion.

Dinner above with the two sangrias was $82 plus tip.  In our world, that's a nicer dinner but not five star.  The problem is normally when you pay that you get a meal that's memorable for positive reasons, and I can't say that happened.

We will at some point go back, probably when it's warmer and probably for a burger on the patio with our pup tagging along.  Maybe I'll feel differently after that, but for now, not in a hurry for that second chance.

I can't say enough of this place!  I had lunch, again, at my favorite Chinese restaurant today.  I was in a rush so had to order something simple yet covered my favorite meats: duck, roast pork, chicken.  I was not disappointed.  Great flavor and bulls eye on the crispy skin.  I can eat here every day and twice on Sunday.  Shame they are closed on Tuesday.  The service was good.  Portions were decent for the price.  I just ordered one plate.  My usual days would have been 4-5 entrees.  Not that I am a big eater or big in stature, but I like ordering plenty.  One has to be a plate of roast pork.  I do not think i have had one bad dish in the all the times I have dined here.  The bakery is super fabulous.  I always leave with a bag of their desserts.  I just wish there were more parking on Grand.  Going again this weekend!

Based on previous experience, I chose Workshop for a meal with friends.  We reserved a table and since it was one of the last reservations of the night, the place was fairly empty.  

Sadly the kitchen was slow.  We were the last table of the night and our mains took an hour to get to our table.  I ordered the pirogies (which have changed from a month or two back).  They were fairly cold, the side vegetables weren't cooked well and it was rather ho hum.

To drink I ordered a drink I had before, the Gin Gin Mule...I think they used tonic water instead of the ginger beer.

I'll try it again but this was definitely an off night.

Wonderful experience! I broke my ballroom dance shoes just hours before I needed to wear them. They helped me find a replacement. They had excellent suggestions and knew what I was looking for. Even when they didn't have my size in stock for a few styles, they brought out recommendations that I actually liked better. Excellent experience and a life saver. Great customer service and very reasonable. Would recommend to any dancer!

Great pool, clean updated rooms.  Got a cabana by the pool and it was money well spent.  Not a huge fan of the overall layout,it didn't really flow to get from the pool to the room to the casino.  
Did I say great pool?  Several separate swimming areas, hot tub and a waterfall off the roof into the water.... nice.  Plus cabanas and after about 4 pm it's in the shade of the building.
Phenomenal customer service and staff.  Super nice!

Jenna and Noel exhibited the perfect example of impeccable service and genuine hospitality. I was driving when I got a flat tire and had to pull into the Fleming's parking lot. The roadside assistance service was taking forever so I walked into Fleming's for food and drink. The kitchen was closed at 2:00 and not opening until 4 o'clock for dinner, but Jenna and Noel happened to overhear my telephone conversation about my flat tire situation. They immediately poured me a drink and asked the Chef to open the kitchen early to cook me a meal. After they also invited me to try a new wine they were considering adding to the menu. They went above and beyond for me during a time they were not supposed to be working simply because they knew I was dealing with a stressful situation. Acts of kindness like this are rarer than gold. I never do online reviews but I could not let this story go untold. Thank you for the excellent food and service! Will certainly be back!

At the midpoint of a bike ride, we had the chicken gyros and falafel sandwich for lunch, and they were wonderful. Ingredients are fresh and flavorful, and the staff, overseen by the effusive Smiley, were consistently friendly and helpful.
Best BBQ around. My favorite spot to eat in Gallatin! Huge portions at a great price. Be aware that they don't take credit cards.

Ask yourself a question, are you going for food or a blizzard. If it is anything other than a blizzard find a different DQ. Sadly it seems to be ran by young adults not even out of high school so don't expect the beat they have to offer.

Big dining area, very clean, nice atmosphere, friendly staff. 

The House Salad was GREAT! Highly recommend. It made me realize that thing I like best about salad was BACON! 

We got a large 1/2 cheese,1/2 pepperoni...cuz we roll gangster like that. It was super yummy in our tummy-tum-tumkins. Even our ankle bitters loved it. 

We'll be back!

Came here with a couple people, there was barely anyone here. Plenty of people working, but the service was horrible. My friend ordered a margarita, they didn't put a lime in it, they didn't have salt for the rim, the counter was sticky. The place is very sparsely decorated and just seems very odd. So awful.
Finally, Berlin's Doner is adding some much needed excitement to the dismal food selection on the South Side. Both the beef-lamb and chicken are excellent whether in a sandwich, wrap, or salad.

Another perfect albeit short stay here.

It's nice to come back and see familiar faces of happy employees that remember you and your preferences.

Stayed in the main hotel with a corner room this time so I had great views of the bay and the sunset.

Rooms are impeccably clean. Service  is spectacular.  

From AJ  at the lobby bar...to Melinda and dave at oystercatchers..to Joan. .Margot and amir at armanis...the service is always terrific ..friendly..and efficient.

There's absolutely  no need to leave this resort  once ur settled in. Anything u need is at your fingertips.

I would recommend this hyatt to anyone who appreciates upscale dining and a luxury  resort.

Stopped in on a weeknight for a nice dinner when we unexpectedly had a free babysitter.  I love it when that happens!  We shared an ap of little crab claw sticks, which I know sounds incredibly unappealing but I can't remember what they called them.  Basically they left the toe on and removed the rest of the shell off the meat- and then breaded and fried.  Envision a mozzarella stick- only its crab. Delightfully easy to eat!  I wish the crab had been a bit sweeter but that's what we get in the Midwest.  

We then shared a summer salad which was full of summer veggies- different pole beans, beets, pattypan squash, peppers, and lumps of creamy goat cheese.  Oh, andt he best, most tiny yellow cherry tomatoes ever.  They were like little sweet tomato flavor bombs.  

My hubs had their meatloaf, which is supposedly a bit of a big deal.  We weren't impressed frankly.  I mean, it wasn't bad, but it wasn't blow me away good either.  And a bit dry.  My fish however was excellent.  I know they are known for good seafood preparations and they got it right on this one for sure.  Perfectly cooked and a nice light sauce.  

So happy I was able to get in here during the week. The vibe was more laid back and sitting outside was great.

I really really really hate car dealerships and having to go through the process of buying a car, but my son was desperately in need of a replacement vehicle and we came with him to help with the process.

OK, you drive up and sharks circling the chum filled waters comes to mind, but it is what is the norm for buying a car. We knew what we wanted and that helped with the process. We did not get the high pressure the other reviewers report. In the past when we have bought a car, there has been a lot of pressure to put add-ons to the bill - additional warrenties, service contracts, under coating, processing fees. This was all very straightforward with no hidden items on the final sale.

What bumps this up to four stars for me is the way they helped my son (who has virtually no credit) get the best deal with financing. I had to co-sign for the loan, but I had expected that. What made them stand out is they called me the next day and said they found a different financing at a lower rate. I really appreciate that they went out of their way to get the very best deal for us. 

I waited to write this review to see if there have been any problems with the vehicle once my son got it home. His job requires him to dive 200+ miles per day some of it over rural unpaved roads. He has had no problems with the vehicle and it has stood up to the demands that he puts on it. 

I would consider buying a used vehicle from them again.

Our first night in St Louis. Dinner at a BBQ place and desert at Ted's. Pumpkin pie for me and lemon for my wife. Wonderful!!! 

We'll be back next week before we fly out. If we weren't traveling around the state, we'd be here more.

Better than any of the Thai I have tried in or around downtown St Louis or Grand!

I'll gladly make the trek from south city to O'Fallon to get this delicious, superior and value Thai.

Having been twice, I am ashamed to admit that I am addicted to their Drunken Noodles so I have had that each visit, albeit once chicken and once pork.

The appetizers are delicious.  Have tried the spring rolls, chicken satay and chicken pot-stickers and they were all satisfying.

The waiter/waitress will ask you what level you want your heat if you get a spicy dish.  They ask you on a scale of 1 to 4.  First visit I asked for 3 and the dish was very nice.  Last visit I went 4 and while it was definitely a "sinus opening experience" the food is pleasantly hot without any of the ill side-effects later on...if you know what I mean.

The menu has over 100 items on it and while some of the other reviews complain of the vegetables being "not fresh" I can only compare Aroy with the pricey city Thai I've had in/around St Louis and I put Aroy equal of better with HUGE portion sizes at very reasonable prices.

Each visit I have found the service to be attentive and available.  Once during Saturday lunch rush and another post-lunch afternoon.

Walk-in takeout service seemed very quick for those I observed on my visits.

I've been to Thailand a few times and while you'll never beat home-cooked Thai with exported fare, I have nothing bad to say about Aroy Thai.  It's where I'll be taking my out-of-town guests and where I'll go for takeout when the urge hits. 

Looking forward to my next visit to explore more of their menu choices...unless those Drunken Noodles get me again!

We love Loose Pooch!  We are two busy working professionals and really appreciate that we can take our dog to a stimulating and safe environment for 8 hours a day, 6 days a week!  The staff are very friendly and our dog is always happy to see them.  We also signed up for the VIP program, which includes both daycare and obedience training.  We are very happy with Loose Pooch and plan to continue using their services.  Keep up the good work! :-)

So annoyed. My wife and I decided to try ITV after hearing all the buzz. Made a reservation via Open Table. They require a credit card so we've been trying to modify our reservation to accommodate a time change but Open Table won't let you modify the reservation - instead you have to call. The problem is they don't answer the phone. I suggest you try somewhere else that actually gives good service and isn't annoying. Won't bother going back.

I'm here right now and this is my hell. Worst drink in history. I mean...this margarita is  straight lime soda with a hint of urine. If I'm ever diagnosed with cancer it will be because of this place and it's awful bartenders. Most of this comment may sound like a joke but this place used to be wonderful before (I'm assuming here) it's owners changed because when this was Lola's it was dark and mysterious, hip and fun. Now it looks and smells like an old dirty motel in Vegas. It sucks guys. Plus it overcharged us for drinks.
I love Keke's! This place is delicious. I actually didn't have breakfast and decided to try lunch. The buffalo chicken wrap was amazing. Service was also excellent!
Excellent food, drinks & atmosphere! I love the strawberry-habanero margarita! It's the perfect balance of sweet & spicy. Today the special was a cactus tostada - very crisp & fresh tasting!
Dawn Patrol is one of our favorite breakfast spots in SB! We come every time we visit-their build your own hash is delicious and the coffee is solid. Everything is fresh and tasty.
Food is very good. People are very nice, doesn't feel like fast food. Pulled Pork & Ribs are great!!!!!! A special mention for George!

We were looking for a place with ramen and saw the good reviews here. A large bowl of soup with wonderful noodles. My only complaint is that there was only one small piece of pork and one small piece of bacon. Otherwise, good flavor, clean place, decent prices. Will be back!

Have enjoyed this creamery for years!  Always amazed at the variety available and speed of receiving my order - which is aways perfect!  First visited in 1961 when I was a boarder at a high school in the county and the locals wanted to proudly show off their town.  Getting to Ted Drewes was never a chore because someone was alway looking for a weekend treat.   Now that we have grandchildren in the area and we gave recently moved back to St Louis, one of the first places we choose to take our visitors is Ted Drewes!  Thanks for continuing your legacy of excellent taste and service.

So I've been here a few times over the past year or so.  And I keep saying to myself.  It'll get better.  But there is really only one word to describe this place.   Meh.

I mean nothing like a deli that is so small that literally every table is right next to the bathroom.  Which for as small as this building is, I will paddle the engineer "Angry History Teacher in the 70's style" with the Dazed and Confused like paddles, with the holes for better aerodynamics and EVERYTHING.
