But food on the other hand was not very good. We had the chips and dip and the dip tasted like it had mayo in it and should have been on a sandwich. The bread was stringy like it had hair or something in it. The nachos were gooey and not very good either. I probably won't go again especially for pick up.

Let me start off by saying I am not a burger aficionado nor to I pretend to be by any means.  I received an email from Thrillist announcing FREE burgers on 500 Degrees' opening day....it's a couple of doors down from the dance studio...I need to eat before class so let me give it a whirl!

There was no line when I arrived.  I liked the setup of communal tables and for those of you afraid to share a meal with a stranger you can grab a stool at a counter facing a wall.  After already researching the spot before I stepped in the door I knew I wanted a Combo 5 (500 Burger Medium Well - Truffle Fries - Diet Coke).  The burger was smaller than I thought it would be but it was a perfect size for me.  The brioche was a bit dry and not really flavorful and I ended up taking the top part off (too much bread).  The patty was juicy with just the right amount of pink.  Alas, I couldn't taste any of the house sauce on the burger and it was quite bland.  

The Truffle Fries...well that's another story....it was an orgasmic delight to my tongue!  I've never tasted ANYTHING like this before!  I was literally licking my fingers!  Just the right amount of salt and the dipping sauces (mayo based) were good....but just interfered with the essence of truffle slathered on the fries.  Next time, I'd skip the dipping sauces (which were included in my order).

The other thing that impressed me (besides the fries) was the employee they had cleaning cleaning CLEANING!  That's all she did was wipe down the tables and she was QUICK - picking up dropped napkins (people can be SO rude) - checking the bathroom after each customer to give a quick wipe down etc.  She was phenomenal!  

I can see this joint being a hot spot for the Boozed Up At Two AM Need A Place To Grub Crowd.  The burgers will taste delummy after a night of drinking.  I would return for the fries and did recommend that everyone I know go just for the fries!

Large restaurant with a good amount of people seated inside when I walked in. Being alone, I just sat at the front (bar style area). Ordered the pho dac biet ($8.50) and the mango boba ($3.50). The mango boba was tall and skinny. Mango taste was definitely there, but there was so much sugar and I could taste powder. The boba itself was like biting into a stiff snow ball, rather than chewy. The pho featured a flavorful broth with a lot of LEAN meat, which is hard to find in most restaurants. Soft, slippery noodles here compared to stiff in another places. They gave me as much basil as I planned to use. Overall, good pho, but skip the drink.

Every so often, I get over to Citrus Park area and drive by Ballyhoo! I have always thought it was a cute building, brightly painted and with a beach "feel" to it. But, alas, have never gone inside. That was until last night when friends suggested we try it. 

The hostess sat us down at a table in the center area of the restaurant along side the wall. Hardwood floors and "beachy" decorations including a hammerhead, a diver,  and signs are everywhere. Although I love hardwood floors, I wasn't too much of a fan of these. Maybe it was just in our area, but every time someone walked by (or in the case of a few kids, ran by) we felt it. The floor seemed give with each step taken. 

We looked over the appetizers and decided to have either the Table Side Guacamole
or Crab Rangoon. Decision was made easier when we were told by our waitress that the guacamole is no longer on the menu. A little disappointing. Crab Rangoon it was.
6 nice size rangoons arrived with a nice slaw on the side. Very tasty. 

We placed our orders- I ordered the Soy Glazed Tuna Chop Chop salad, my husband- fried oyster po'boy with homemade potato salad. They ordered Grouper sandwich with black beans and rice, and  the Oak Grilled Scallops. We all enjoyed our dinners. My tuna was rare, seared on the outside, just as requested. I should have requested nol baby corn though- not a fan of those things. Thescallops were HUGE and very good- had to have a bite!

I would definitely visit again!
Awesome carne asada tacos and salsa bar choices. The taco truck was clean and had a sheltered outdoor eating area with fans blowing on the salsa bar to keep the flies out.

I have been renting at PHL national for one year and I have to say it has slowly gone downhill. Drop off last Friday was a 20 minute wait with the line extending out to the service road and wrapping around the corner.  There were cars parked everywhere in the lot.  Pick up on Monday was a choice of 4 cars; one had no key (which makes me question how it got to emerald aisle in the first place), 2 muscle cars and a Nissan which had not been cleaned on the inside or the outside. I took the filthy car due to weather. 
 The area for returning cars was still full of parked cars, and some even blocking the exit lanes. Too many cars and not enough employees?

Went back couple weeks ago, OK OK..one -star up..see inklings of improvements. Our nice Waiter who recognized us -asked if we were ordering our favorite Aussie drink, it was a bit Cold..but thought that was nice little personable touch..

Our food came out nice, no mishaps, nothing burnt.I do see that now, the check comes with actual prices on them, instead of before  when you were rung up, nothing on receipt, cashier would just ring it up based codes . I was always skeptical about that.. I like it much better. So signs of improvement I must say..keep at it!!! Who knows, & now they have a Dinner menu..WOW!!! extended hours..Hmmmm.might have to check that out.

This is the only deli within walking distance of my office. They have a pretty big menu of most deli style sandwiches. They also sell sodas and chips. The only thing that's hard for me is, there never seems to be a go to person to order your food. Sometimes you're placing an order to a short person over their 5' tall reach in cooler, which is strange. Other times you order at the register, other times the guy in the back wake over and asks you. I really am not sure about that, I hope they can figure out the organization because it gets awkward for customers when several people are in there standing around at lunch time.

Food: great fries, all sandwiches are oversized. Soul food Friday is a thing here, but I have no idea how it compares.

Great food and service with a nice menu selection. Had the Bacon Wrapped Shrimp with the most amazing Grits (found out they have Marscapone Cheese in them). Also their Gumbo Ya Ya (with chicken and andouille) was amazing.

Ate here for dinner last night. Place was packed so sat at the bar- the bartender was friendly and helpful with suggestions. I ordered the shrimp and crabcake alfredo- it was excellent and service was prompt. Would go back if in town again.

Cheap pizzeria place, HOWEVER, it is decent/very good for the price they charge.

Good sizes and nice taste. Good place to go when you are starving and have no money. 

- Do not expect a fancy place. 
- I would recommend getting the food and then leaving

Of course we know it is not Las Vegas, but per Tripadvisor figured it would be worth going. To sum it all up, it's a castle of secondhand smoke!  We are non smokers and have gone out to clubs which had smoking and could tolerate it more than this place!

 We were very disappointed that we could not enjoy ourselves for all the smoke. Soon as some hit the door, they were lighting up cigs. SMH.. Why not invest in some of  those high power fans to vacuum some of this smoke out??? We were not the only patrons cutting our visits short because of this. 

Nice looking hotel and heard the buffet was delicious, yet sadly we will never know... Doubt we will  ever come back unless it changes to non-smoking or clear divisions of smoking and non-smoking areas. Oh well, can not win them all. Maybe if some happy competition moves in town, things would be interesting.
Delicious ice cream!! Some other food to choose from. Service a bit slow but ice cream out of this world!!!

I was wanting Mexican food and this was close to my hotel. The sugar skulls made the decor colorful. When I wasn't served chips and salsa when I sat down, I prepared myself for a different experience. I decided on a taco plate. They have 2 columns of tacos. More normal on the left side, and "upscale" on the right. $10 and $13 respectively with rice and beans. I picked a fish taco and a shrimp taco. The fish taco was good but the shrimp taco was excellent. It had corn tortillas, Anaheim pepper, perfectly cooked shrimp, cabbage and a lime cilantro sauce. I will be going back. Good food, good decor and good prices

Great food, great tasting biscuits and gravy, not easy to find. I had the southwestern wrap, which is really a breakfast burrito, very tasty. It would have been perfect if they had fresh OJ, but it's from concentrate. Otherwise great!

Very good food with the butter chicken exceptional. You can order degree of spicy to your taste. Tandoori chicken also very good. I have been here several times and have had several dishes and always pleased. Reasonable prices and though small selection of beer and wines there's enough. It's the best Indian food in the area.

CRAB RAGOONS! Need I say more? 

The highlight was the crab ragoons. These were the best of my life. They have a  large variety of Asian cuisine here. Everyone can find something they like on their menu. Also, I wanted to share that they have on stock my favorite beer from when I lived in China: Tsingtao!

It's located in the funk zone area, which is such a good spot. It's next door to the llama dog which kind of threw me off at first because I didn't realize it was two different places. 
Not the biggest selection of beer, but has a good range of different types. The seating area isn't super big, but it's definitely an enjoyable spot

Nice! Perpetual coffee refills, a good medium to dark roast. A dish of half-n-half arrives with the coffee, you don't have to ask for it. That's nothing, there's 2 kinds of hot sauce (including Verde).on the table, extinguishing the boring need to ask and wait for them as in most other breakfast places. 

But what I liked best was the "build your own breakfast" of any 4 items for $5-something.  I chose:  (1) coffee, (2) two eggs, (3) hash browns and toast, and (4) sausage patty.  Pairing-up hash browns And toast as one selection, was an act of Jerry Bob genius.  Yes, at $2.09 per cup, the overall price of a meal goes down if you make it one of the four items rather than have it separately. Ladyfriend had tomatoes as one of her items, and got a nice 4 or 5 good-sized slices and was just about thrilled.

I'm not one of those awful folks who go to these places just to chat endlessly with the poor waitresses, and if I was, I'd be disappointed here, for they're just too busy for chit chat, yet maintain a good esprit de corp. 

This is SO much better service then I was used to getting at the late, defunct Denny's on Speedway, and quieter by far than the jarring, hectic ambience at Jerry-Bob's on Speedway at Pantano.  This may be MY breakfast spot for awhile, and hope you try it, too!

Doesn't look appealing outside but you will be wowed when you enter the establishment. The decor is very authentic.  The cleanliness is average the staff is very polite and will explain everything on the menu if need be. The prices are reasonable you can get some cheap sushi $1 a piece not bad and the have rolls for $6-$7! Stop in you will be satisfied!!!! KID FRIENDLY AS WELL

Had a wonderful time at the Peppermill Hotel Casino this past weekend. Went for a convention being held there. Had a small issue with our room but Mike at the front desk took care of it right away! The buffet is incredible to say the least and the hotel and casino were beautiful. We did not have a chance to use the pool or spa services but look forward to trying them out next time.

The economy rooms are o.k. but for a few dollars more, I suggest upgrading to the newer rooms.

Thank you Mike for taking such great care of us.

I've been having a terrible time in St Louis finding a decent Chinese place that is within delivery or easy take out range of our house. This time I tried Wei Hong. I told my partner it can't be any worse than the other mediocre places we have been going. I was wrong.
The take out service was fast for a Sat night. We were there within 20 minutes of ordering and it was ready. But the dining room was empty. For a Sat night that should have been a big clue. The rest of the places in the neighborhood were busy.
The steamed dumplings could have been great. The tasted homemade and the filling was good. However, they were so doughy with a really thick wrapper too thick that it detracted from the good filling. Everything else went downhill from there. 
The beef and broccoli was inedible. The beef had an awful weird texture. Like it was boiled and was gelatinous.  The sauce on it had off flavors. We literally scraped it off our plates and threw the whole thing out.  The meat in both the general Tao's chicken and the orange beef also had weird textures. It was mushy and the coating was thick on those as well. The flavors in the sauces would have been fine, but they were gloopy.  The fried rice was fair but nothing memorable.
We won't be going back.

Nice little cozy spot. Atmosphere is casual and classy. I had the chicken skewers with rice. It was very tasty and light. Also had a margarita that was fantastic! I only like fresh margaritas and this one passed the test. Recommend checking it out.

Kelly is great! I walked in off the street because I couldn't take another minute of my hair and I got the best haircut I've had in such a long time. I could tell as soon as Kelly started cutting that she knew what she was doing and she was turning my mess into something great. I had lots of weird layers, and she saw that she needed to cut my hair from back to front, rather than the typical approach of front to back. 

She saw what she had to deal with, worked with my hair and gave me a haircut that suits my head and face shape. I barely gave her instructions except that I like having layers, I'm growing it, and it's been a while since my last haircut. 

The haircut kept its shape as it grew out. I live in Los Angeles, but was in Tucson visiting my parents when I got my haircut. It's been months since I saw Kelly, but I refuse to see anyone else in LA and I'm waiting until my next visit to Tucson to have Kelly cut my hair!

This place is great waiter's on hand. In theatre with confey recling leather seat! wide screens excellent sound and picture and no head's in your view whall watching the movie's. They all so have a full bar on hand and a bakery in the lobby. Price's are average for a movie tickets. The all so serve a full menu for lunch and dinner. Great place to eat and  watch movies!

Horrible, the service was good but the food is awful. We are put of state people who came to Nashville for the weekend to see what the hype was about. Heard the food  is good so we decided to try out some places. Not a good place to eat, disappointed

I have been a member at Mt. Laurel Future Fitness for about 3 years now and its had its ups & downs. They offer great accommodations besides just the gym (pool, hot tub, sauna, wide variety of classes, nutritionist, personal trainers, babysitters, etc.), which is why it is a bit pricey like people have previously said. To someone that takes advantage of those extra perks and visits the gym frequently, the price is well worth it. It is a rare occasion if the gym is too crowded for me. Obviously, the hours from 5-7pm when everyone is getting done work are pretty busy, which makes the parking lot a chore and a bit annoying but hey!, If you are going to work out you shouldn't mind the extra cardio.

TV channels are lacking and the connection is poor on the treadmills. Plus, the large TVs play the same advertisements repeatedly. A good option is to freeze your membership for only $5/month for those of you who had trouble canceling. All in all, its a good gym, just needs to work on a few minor things.

I'm always looking for a good breakfast sandwich when I am hungover.  I haven't found a bagel shop so my go to is Tony Jrs!  They have a great pork roll, egg and cheese on a long roll... the roll is what makes it!  And they have thick sliced pork roll... YUM!
Amazing! I wish that they didn't use foam containers for take out, but, besides that, everything was perfect.

Yesterday was my first visit to Paris Parker. I have never gone to a stylist that didn't come with a recommendation in my life until now. I was short on time and wanted to go somewhere near my home.

They told me I would see Stacey for my full highlight appointment. 

She was awesome!

She got all the brassy color out of my hair and made my blonde look natural and vibrant. 

Blonde hair isn't easy and I was expecting to have to go back a couple of times to someone new until they got it just right. I was wrong.

Stacey nailed the color and was really nice to chat with too! Also a must when hanging in a chair for hours. 

Highly recommend... Although I may regret it if she gets too booked up :)

This place is just incredible, the ambience is totally chill when compared to a lot of the French Quarter and the food is awesome. The trick, according to the extremely nice girl that waited on me, is to get there on or before 8 in the morning as they start getting really busy around 9. As a person who really needs my caffeine, it was really cool that they also give you a to-go cup for your coffee. Highly recommend this place for anyone looking for a unique and tasty breakfast experience.

Starts the job and could not get the guy to finish.  He held up the construction of my new home.  All he had to do was put in 4 10" sky tubes.  After 3 visits he had 1 complete and 2 partially complete.  The roofers could not finish their job and seal the roof up until he was done.  I left many many messages and never a call back.  Once when he answer the phone I told him about all the messages and he said he is too busy to check his messages.  DON'T TAKE ON WORK YOU CANT HANDLE.  He would tell me he was going to be at the house a certain day to complete the work and would just no show.  In my humble opinion he is a piece of work you should not do business with this company.  This is not how you treat customers.

Update - after me speaking my mind he did come back and quickly complete the job, so I added a star.

Cherie is the bomb regarding cuts and color! One happy customer.  I'm always able to make a timely appt with her.  When you first get together, she likes to be on the conservative on cut n color til she gets to really know her customer and their hair.  In the past, I've had a number of stylists who just keep cutting and cutting.  Thinking their style would look better than what their customers want.
Cherie is the opposite.  She really listens to her clients and what they want.

Not your typical hotel bar. The atmosphere is lively and offers some nice nighttimme views of the city. If you are into hand crafted cocktails give it a try.  If you prefer beer or wine then I would head downstairs to Cerulean.

Worst sushi I've ever had. After reading all of the wonderful reviews on help I headed out only to be very disappointed. We started with the tuna dumpling which was pretty good nothing impressive but the only thing edible we received. We ordered four rolls all of which the fish were no good if not weeks old and were hard to swallow and immediately made both of us sick to our stomachs. I asked to talk to a manager after trying one of each roll and after waiting 15 minutes or more for the manager he told me "it's fish of course it's fishy" and I explained I know what I ordered and am familiar with the rolls but these were not edible. He fought with me indicating I was wrong and then only agreed to give me 20% off before walking away while I was in mid sentence. I paid $48 for four rotten rolls of seafood that I did not eat. Unprofessional, not edible, please do not give them your business.

This place is pretty much the epitome of a great dive bar. The drinks are cheap, the atmosphere is unpretentious, the staff is friendly, did I mention the drinks? but seriously, where else can you get a 40 and not get a strange look from a single person in the bar?
We had raw oysters - they were great.  I had a Po boy that was pretty good, but I've definitely had better.  Everyone else the table agreed that everything was good.. but not great.

When Waitress came to take drink order, I commented that I like  light beer, she immediately responded with "we don't have light beer". I asked her what she would recommend on tap since "I like light beer". She came across as very rude. Later, when I placed my food order, I asked if they had sour cream, and again, I got a very rude response. The food is actually pretty good, despite the service. The place is very cozy and a nice atmosphere. I would probably come back just hopefully won't get the same waitress. If you are with a large group, just a heads up, they won't split the bill and they will only take up to 5 credit cards to pay the bill.  Very inconvenient especially since it's 2016! Really, you can't separate the bills?

Usually in and out within an hour. They are very thorough when diagnosing and great at following up by phone call at the least when the kids are ill.Very satisfied and plan to stay until the kids are too old for a pediatrician.

Kind of a weird hipster atmosphere, but the food here is awesome. Try the organic mango infused tea. Best tea ever and it's not even close. The pizza is easily the best in St. Louis. This place is always packed so you will be waiting a while for a table, its a little expensive and there isn't parking but this place is definitely worth a try.

We stopped in for a lunch bite. I love a tasty chicken sandwich so naturally that was my choice. The chicken was exploding with flavor and so was the bun. Not to mention they have sweet potato fries, who doesn't love those? My finance had the mahi tacos and she said they were different then the many she had sampled in the past so they were very enjoyable.She also got a sparkler to drink which she said was very tasty. If you are looking for a new place to try downtown this is the spot!

Cannot say enough great things about this place!!  The food is AMAZING - great oysters, great sushi, great pad thai, great desserts....I haven't had anything that was not outstanding.  The servers are always pleasant and wanting you to have a good experience.  It's a small restaurant in a strip shopping center but the interior is very cool.  It's a BYO but the liquor store is two doors down.  If you love sushi, you will love Hachi!
It's a great place to grab a coffee and a small meal to get your day going. Cappuccino is my favorite and so are the silver dollar pancakes. Eggs are fluffy and tasty. I definitely recommend them.

Top notch Indian!  We've had a dozen meals since we stumbled into Nirvana a week after it opened in this new location.  We have never been disappointed.  Everything we have tried has been excellent.  We love the old stand-by Tiffin, but Nirvana is more authentic and nuanced. Tiffin has been quite anglicized...very hearty and delicious, but spices are a little too restrained.  Nirvana let's it's spices loose and the result is delicious!  Unqualified positive recommendation.

Excusez-moi, was I just transported to a Parisian bakery? The Cake Bake Shop sure feels like it! The pictures Yelpers have posted just don't do it justice. It's ADORABLE. So classy and elegant, especially with the lighting and baby pink & white color scheme. Did I mention there's a twinkling Eiffel Tower in the window?? This place is like every little girl's dream place to come with her stuffed animals in tow and have tea time.

The shop is more spacious than I thought it would be - and they have a lovely patio area. If you want the full fancy experience, sit inside! 

In love with the decor, environment, and concept, but not quite the service. The young girl working the counter seemed baffled that we wanted to dine in just for coffee and some sweets, but we were told to seat ourselves and a server would come. It was slow as molasses and kind of confusing as to who was waiting on us, in all honesty. 

The espresso my friend had was apparently amazing, and we split a blueberry cinnamon scone. It was good, but disappointingly small. I was expecting a whopper of a scone to match their large cake slices. And since it's fancy, it's pricey.

Service issues aside, I want to return for tea time and get my hands on a slice of that delectable cake. Next time, I want to dress the part a little bit - they don't have a dress code and most people were casual, but I would have felt like I fit in more if I had on a sundress vs. a tee shirt and shorts.

This is one of our "go to" places in the area.  Food is always good (have had most of the items on the menu with no disappointments yet) beer selection is always new!  The staff has been pleasant and knowledgeable and the prices are extremely reasonable.  Pretty much everything you need in a place to eat and drink!

Had the privilege of partaking in Chef Ponte at a private event. He and his staff were wonderful.

Foie Gras and other appetizers were quite tasty. I don't eat beef so unfortunately, I missed the main protein for the meal. However the mashed potatoes, mushrooms and marsala sauce was delicious.

My favorite thing for the evening was the dessert. Who doesn't like chocolate? 

I hope to stop in the restaurant soon.

Katie's always has a selection of interesting lunch specials.  The sandwiches a generous and my personal favorite is the Cajun Cuban with the right mix of cochon de lait and ham.  Today we started with he charbroiled oysters which were very good and they came with lots of french bread to

Excellent food and drinks. Everything we ate was impeccable! We had the lobster tempura with rissoto and the grilled chicken pasta for entrees. The lobster crab bisque was divine and the chocolate lava cake was great. Great service as well!!

I ordered the steak bowl with some flour tortillas, the meal was okay. The tortillas was small, the bowl will be enough for you to get full for lunch. This spot would be ideal if you want to grab something on the go for lunch but you don't really care how good it taste. The steak itself is thinly cut and little or no seasoning on it. If you dine in they have complimentary tortilla chips but when I was there it wasn't refilled. It can get packed during lunch hours so if you're planning to dine in with more than four people, I suggest you come a bit early to grab some tables. Would I come back? Most likely not, I rather go elsewhere.

Dark lighting. Unique interior. Bearded staff in waist coats making bespoke cocktails. Hate it or love it, that's what your getting.

Perhaps I just had the bar menu because I didn't see any deviled eggs and the other recommended items from yelp. I did however try the octopus... Some of the most tender pulpo I've ever had! In a salty perhaps bonito broth. Smelled it as it passed by and had to order.

Trinidad sour... Try it. Had a bit of kick in the end but texture and taste, slightly sweet but not in a bad way.

Visited as part of the Philadelphia City Prohibition Tour.  This was my favorite stop.  For one thing, I've unknowingly walked by this place a gazillion times as I live a few blocks away.  Its unassuming from the street, but totally welcoming and comfy inside.  A perfect place to come for a few drinks with friends, a date, etc.  Also, the Eastside was my favorite cocktail on the tour (Gin, Lime, Cucumber, Mint).  From what I could tell, they offer expertly, and lovingly, crafted cocktails.  Service was attentive and appreciate of our compliments!  We are definitely looking forward to coming back for more cocktails and to try some of the snacks as well.  So happy we were introduced to this place!

Came here for breakfast after a night out. I had the double egg sandwich with bacon plus a side of grits. The other ladies had the veggie omelet, and western omelet. It didn't take long for the food to arrive. I enjoyed my sandwich and my side of grits were truly a side of grits. 

The western omelet was good. The mix is already made so don't ask for it with no tomatoes. Just pick them out. Our waitress was very pleasant and attentive. She made sure our glasses stayed full and we didn't want for anything. This place may be small, but the love is here. It seems like everybody knows everyone and they just break out in conversation. Very popular and people were flooding in and out. I would love to return to this place and recieve the same awesome service I got before.
This is nice hidden gem. We have never been disappointed. The staff is very friendly and willing to please. The food is very tasty and something a little outside the box from you normal restaurant.
Just a cool place for great beer, food truck and a chill crowd. Not college kids - but people who like beer and don't need a TV to carry a conversation.
Had a business lunch with friends. Service was efficient and friendly. I ordered the pulled pork tamale and it was very good. Everything ordered at the table looked good as well. Good margaritas.

Took an hour and a half for the oil change, never waited this long. Then somehow the $50 price became 80$ because my car took more oil. Never was I asked if I wanted the extra oil. I could have bought that myself. And that still hardly explains how it suddenly costs $30 more. And that's before tax and with the coupon. $100 full price for an oil change? That's a joke. People were nice though, not their fault pep boys robs you.

The Peppermill is always making upgrades to their hotel to make it look better. But if you're a non smoker, good luck on making it through without getting second hand smoke cancer. They used to have these portable air purifiers all over the casino but they have steadily disappeared one by one over the last year for some ungodly reason. Now the place reeks of smoke. Just one walk through the casino and your hair and clothes will smell like cigarettes.  It makes it unbearable to sit at any machine and play for any substantial amount of time.

This store carries many items that can't be found anywhere else, but their pricing fluctuates so much! I buy cases of coconut cream there, and the price is never the same. Last time I was charged $38, today I was charged $48! This has happened many times in the past. They do have great prices on produce, but the random pricing of items can be frustrating.
Love this place. The rooms are fantastic and so greatly decorated.   Great service . We had so much fun    Can't wait till they open more rooms

Overall, it was a great dining experience. My friends and I had 4 of their dishes and 2 desserts. We had the spicy mung bean noodle with bean sauce, lo mein, garlic sauce beef, and cumin chicken! The dishes were great- the cumin chicken was slightly too spicy. We had the macaroons and the ice cream. The ice cream was great but one of the macaroons was not delicious. 

If you're coming here for portion, you'll have to order more than you think. But you definitely get some delicious, quality, and flavor packed dishes here.
Quiet, good service, good fish, standard (boring and tasteless) app and salad, nice decor, good menu. Would go back. Would avoid the salad. Happy hour M-Th 5-7 drinks and appetizers.
Love this place. Great service. Great food. Great wine selection. Definitely go for the escargot and baked Brie. Yum!!

One of my new favorite bbq around the Bay Area.
Clean place, great food.
1 slab can easily can feed 3 or even 4 people.
Service was great and good crew, made our experience very good.

My child attended summercamp last year and everything was great. There was an issue about the activity fee, if not attending for the whole summer, and they not just work with you but answer any questions you have and they are polite about it. 
Mark in South County

I don't know if it's actually that much cheaper than places on the hill. It has a bit less atmosphere, but it is very good food. 

Don't me wrong, if you brought an Italian here they might be highly offended. Even as an American, the sauces and cheese are not what I've experienced in any other city. St. Louis has to be the only place on earth that does Italian this way. It is more than just provel cheese that is different. 

That is so interesting though. And on a budget, with kids, or on their (Monday)? All you can eat deal, you might want to come to pasta house. 

We had excellent service at this location, a deal from groupon, and a quite tasty meal. I wish they still gave slu basketball discounts, and after this season they just might. They sure wouldn't have to give them often as slu may not score 60 points often. 

A local chain that makes St. Louis "Italian" well. Not everybody in the metro can always eat on the hill. My fiancé has loved the tortellini all her life. It's hard to try anything else after you've tried it.

The owners of Cured Nails were friendly and accommodating. I only had an hour and they were able to get me in for a manicure and toe polish change.  My nails look great and Shaun was professional and easy to talk to. This salon is bright and beautiful....think lots of white, wood tones, and plants. My only complaint is that the OPI Shine 2 nail polish was additional $5 for nails and toes ($10 total). It would be nice to have signage on that price difference so I wasn't told that after I picked my polish. All in all a great experience at Cured.

Looking for the best prices on wine and the best beer selection in Tampa?  Oh, here it is!  It took me way too long to find out about Total Wine after moving to Tampa.

Their wine selection is enormous and can be a bit overwhelming, but they have a fantastic staff.  They are always friendly and willing to help you find whatever you need.  Not only do they have a great variety of excellent wine, but I find myself searching for the cheaper bottles towards the bottom of the shelves and I can still find so many great choices.  

Now for my favorite part....the craft beer section.  Holy. Crap.  I could spend hours in this area of the store.  I love beer and often can't find my favorite craft brews at most stores.  At Total Wine, I can't think of one beer that I have looked for and couldn't find.   Awesome variety and their prices are stellar.  Far better than any grocery store in the area (ahem, Publix).  Sometimes, I peruse the beer section at Whole Foods for some things to try and then go to Total Wine to find them at least a dollar or two cheaper.

I don't drink liquor as much as I drink wine and beer, but their selection of liquor is no different than the rest of the store.  You can find anything you need and I've found the prices better here than any liquor store around here.

Total Wine is a one stop shop for all your alcoholic needs.  Trust me, you'll love it.

Quick service, friendly staff, and MAN-O-MAN do I LOVE the Chick-fil-a sauce. Chick-fil-a used to be my favorite fast food chicken sandwich, that was until I found PDQ! I still think Chick-fil-a is a good sandwich, don't get me wrong, but PDQ is probably twice as good, and it is definitely not twice the price.

I still love the waffle fries and PDQ does not have Chick-fil-a sauce, but I am sure that I will be making less stops at Chick-fil-a now that I found PDQ.

Growing up in Michigan, we did not have Chick-fil-a. That being the case, I immediately became a fan upon moving to Florida. I have even gone so far as drawing cow spots on blank paper and taping them to by business suit to get my free chicken sandwich.

I always go with the #1 and cover that baby in the Chick-fil-a sauce. I also give my fries a hefty dose of salt and pepper and then proceed to dip them in the Chick-fil-a sauce. I have it down to a science. I even started making my own fried chicken sandwiches at home and took steps to make them more Chick-fil-a-ish.

Now that I found PDQ I have a huge internal conflict. I sure hope Chick-fil-a can drop the price of their #1 by a little bit, and then they may win my heart back, even though PDQ has a leg up on quality.

This is my local bar. For those of you who don't know, Tues is $2 domestics. Thursday is ladies night (not sure what that even means as I'm not a lady). This place is usually packed Thursday, Friday, and Saturday.

As far as food goes, they have a really good burger, french dip, onion rings, and pizza. I'd probably rate them in that order. I like to stop by and eat there during the day every once in a while since I usually run in to someone I know.

I can't really speak to the service there as I'm a regular and it's never an issue. I get a new beer when my current one is half full without even asking. I've never heard any complaints though, even with as crazy as it gets there on Fri/Sat.

I'm not a huge fan of the music here which is mostly country, so I sneak my jukebox picks in there when I can. Overall though, I love the good ole boy atmosphere and usually always have a great time here; which is more than I could ever say about Players or AJs.

This place has great pizza. I stopped in for lunch with a client. The restaurant is bright, airy and very modern. Everything is clean and there is plenty of room. We were seated right away. Service was quick and polite. 

The menus is extensive but not overwhelming. We each got a pizza. I went with my go to, the buffalo chicken pizza. My server recommended I get it with a side of ranch. It was a good call. The pizza had a nice kick. The chicken was still moist, which doesn't always happen on a pizza. The celery was crunch and the blue cheese was wonderful. 

I had an excellent experience and can't wait to go back with my wife
Typical boba tea place in lee lee shopping center. I had the milk tea boba and it was pretty good. I like to grab one before going into lee lee for my Asian goods

Haven't had their sushi (yet), but hibachi chicken exceeded expectations on 5 fronts: speed, presentation, taste, price, and ability to customize (I asked to make mine light on the salt). The size was impressive too.

Erin is the dopest bartender working here, she'll make your drinking experience here incredible. She gives awesome beer recommendations and knows how to make customers feel like they're  regulars within minutes of meeting them.

Great burrito featuring the best of Mexican cuisine. The food lets the ingredients do the talking rather than being overloaded by sauces, cheeses, and dips. Service is attentive, and it is an overall wonderful experience.

Our favorite stay of the 3 different hotels on our recent trip, and the ONLY room that didn't smell of mold or smoke!  Very friendly staff, great location, and very clean room. Noise on Conti Street wasn't too bad on a party weekend. Next time we'll request a room that looks out to the pool, and spend more time there! And not on Labor Day weekend! Make sure when the Bell Hops call you a cab that you all agree on the fare because ours charged us $5 more when we arrived at the airport.

this is a really great goodwill store with a good selection of all kinds of things. everything is in good shape and the prices are right. no matter if you're looking for clothes, records, books or furniture, you'll most likely find it here and if not, you'll find some other bargains ;-)

so soo yummy! simple yet delicious. I've never been to a tofu house before but this was a good first experience. The ambiance is very traditional but nice. The menu is selective but seemingly authentic to the cuisine. You can choose up to 5 levels of spiciness for your soup, but plain mild still has an amazing taste. 

The parking lot is small, but there is street parking surrounding the area also. Prices are ok for what it actually is, but honestly its delish and a nice fulfilling treat no matter what you order. I also love all of the small side dishes which come with any Korean meal.

Also, there arent any desserts which i am a fan of, but its ok.

My husband and I just had dinner there. I had seen the reviews, which were good, so we gave it a shot. I am so glad we did, everything was amazing. I had the pork... something (can't remember the name but it started with a B) and my husband had the prime rib. He is a prime rib snob and he said it was delicious, and the pork was so good. The atmosphere is great, it's a small little place, but that adds to the experience. We will definitely be going back, a lot.

I took my almost 2 year old son here to get his hair cut. My son HATES haircuts and usually cries the whole time, but not here!! Jarrod did such an amazing job cutting his hair, talking to him to keep him distracted, and was quick. He also did an amazing job cutting his hair, which has 4 different cowlicks. They have a fish tank and gave my kid a sucker at the end. In the future, it will be "A treat" going to see Jarrod again. We will most definitely be going back. Also, I thought the price of $15 dollars was incredibly reasonable.

Went into Giant on a busy Sunday to get a 12 pack of beer and 3 other items. Cashier at beer garden refused to ring out my other three items even though other cashiers have done it there before. When I asked if I am expected to go get in another line she said yes I guess so. Needless to say I cashed out my other three items and did not buy the beer from them. With grocery stores stealing business from bars and restaurants maybe they should try to be a little more accommodating.

I don't even know why I'm bothering to write a review when there are so many. 
This was my first time visiting this location I normally go to the location in South Philly. Well I was just as pleased at the reading terminal location. They had a great selection and the staff was so super friendly and helpful! I only ordered cannolis (I would have bought much more if I wasn't a broke college kid) but they were so incredible and so fresh! I'm so happy this location is much closer to me now and I will proudly continue to make the trip to reading terminal market just for these cannolis. Ps- I got the original with chocolate chips- that's the only way to get them right ?!

Gene from Chim Chimney is the man! Great customer service, excellent dustless process and an unmatched care for the customer. Gene noticed some separation in the sealer and mortar on the second story of my house while he was climbing up to inspect the chimney topper, in a place I could never have seen, but he took a picture and brought it to me so to assure that I did not experience a leak. Wow! Above and beyond the call. 

Oh yes...Chim Chimney is the cheapest price in town too.

Just get in line, no matter how long it is. The line moves at the kitchen's pace and the food is worth every minute in line. Eli's is only open Friday and Saturdays so I've been there two days for lunch. The pork is outstanding. Get the dinner and save a dollar if you want cold slaw and bean sides.

The customer service was great. Only rating this place 4/5 stars because the pita was a bit hard, which made it difficult to chew, and the setting was a bit crowded (which they obviously can't help)! But a nice thing is they deliver or you can get pick up. The smoothie was SOO good. Also, you can tell falafel sandwich had fresh ingredients! And the portion definitely met the cost. I would order from here again!

I always like the chill ambiance of this pub. It's nestled off on a quieter part of 17th street and you could actually miss the sign if you aren't paying attention. 
I ordered a dirty martini and the seared tuna salad with shaved celery and beets on Bibb lettuce and my friends had the black sheep burger with Gouda and a portabella mushroom... Both were very tasty. In fact my friend said that it was the best burger in the city!

Well, my bf and I were going to eat here for his birthday (a Sunday night) and off we went. The place is the size of a shoebox. Seriously. It is one of the smallest restaurants I have ever seen. Considering Jose Garces opened this post Iron Chef, what's his excuse? Anyway, we were informed it would be a half hour wait and had to give them our name (OK) and cell phone (odd). We were, of course, asked if we would like to sit at the bar. We went back, sidled passed a waiter or two and quickly realized there was absolutely no seating at the bar. I told the hostess we would be having a drink elsewhere, and to please keep our name on the list. So, we went and had a beer elsewhere, and about a half hour later, I asked my BF if his phone had rang at all. It had not. He called VW and was informed that they had called. We went back to VW and the hostess chirped that it was their policy to call twice. I said I had a hard time believing that as my bf's phone showed no missed calls, no messages, nothing. She said we could wait another half hour, if we liked. I almost told her to go eff herself. My bf used their bathroom and we went to Standard Tap instead. 

So the 1 star is for their total lack of space and lame waiting list procedure. 

The food I saw looked good though. 

Maybe I will go on a Monday at 4:00 or something.

Yum Yum there is no need to go without gumbo and red beans while you're in Yats.  I find that the dishes are a little salty, but it is from the sausages, and how can I complain, it is a little bit too salty, just like my yummy New Orleans food.  The prices are good and the food reminds me of being home in New Orleans.

The pizza and stix here are so so good!  The service is mediocre and the owner, I'm not a huge fan of.  I had bought a deal (groupon, perhaps - I don't remember) because I liked the pizza and had been there a few times before, but he refused to take them because his paperwork had been thrown out and he didn't know if they'd been used already.  Really?  That's my problem?  And why aren't you tracking this electronically?  I haven't been back since.

This place is absolutely amazing. We went inside to indulge a bit and the cashier was incredibly friendly and patient. He laid out all the options for us clearly, and helped us order based on our specific preferences. After we ordered, we sat and listened to the lovely jazz background music they had playing and then before I knew it (maybe 7-10 minutes) our food was coming out. Talk about fast!!!! The meats were all cooked to PERFECTION. And the fries are to die for. Highly recommend this place.

I managed to be the first in line for dinner service here recently. Once the doors opened I was quickly seated at a table for three, and they gladly accommodated my party of three when we asked to be seated at a booth instead. Overall, the service was satisfactory, albeit slightly scattered and overburdened.

I ordered the Roasted Black Garlic Tonkotsu and I quite enjoyed it. Good flavor and toppings and just the right amount of salt -- I drank the broth at the end, which is something I won't do if it's too salty. Portion size was good, as I left feeling sated, but not full.

Price wise, I don't mind paying ~$11 for a bowl of good Ramen, although I do hope they'll be able to lower the price a little in the future. I will, however, note that the drink prices are unreasonably high -- no one at my table ordered drinks because of it.

If you can get in line early or don't mind waiting, a while I'd definitely recommend trying Raijin Ramen at least once, as in my opinion it's one of the better options for Ramen in Tucson (and currently my favorite, although I still need to try others)...you might want to skip drinks in favor of a lower bill or spending the money on appetizers instead, though.

I'm glad to see a local business with good food have a successful opening. Hopefully they'll be able to expand their hours and menu (dessert options, please), as well as adjust some of their pricing after they've been open for a while.
Very good food. Reasonable prices. Big portions. Not an upscale place by any means, but we have never had a bad meal here. Their dinner rolls are warm doughy perfection.

taste-d came by with their truck to my work... they ran out of buns and fries. 
instead of offering to maybe put more toppings (Cole slaw BBQ sauce), they were fine with charging full price for the small pattie. I will say the burger was good, but surprised by the poor planning. I wouldn't go out of my way to try them again based on the this experience.
how do you run out of buns but not burgers??

I went in open minded to a place I hadn't heard positive reviews about. The reviews are correct. Broken Beaker is a disappointment. Their display is low grade and simplistic in a bad way. There is no glass to separate the consumer from the display which contains dust and cracked glass on the inside. I tried the molecule mule and it was nothing but simple syrup and lime, for $10. You can get the same thing at Marsh for less. I was told the tour was great, but was disappointed when I had to self guide myself through there back room/ distillery. The equipment has the beginning look of the Statue of Liberty as the green sets in and equipment shows continual signs on not being cleaned. Patina is not cool in a distillery. Would I recommend Broken Beaker, absolutely not. Unless major improvements are made it does not belong on Mass ave. Good Luck

This place is totally decent. I've been here once for dine-in and once for take-out. No complaints. 

What you really need to know is this: Crazy Sushi is currently offering a "two rolls for $6/three rolls for $8" opening special. Crazy sushi, crazy cheap. 

When I dined in on the first day they were in business, this special was not offered. Don't know when it will end, either. Get it while you can.

Tucked away off of South Grand at Wyoming and Spring is this little corner pub with a great Pizza.   I have to say the Pizza is well worth the wait.  Sometimes you have to wait 30 minutes, others 45, sometimes upwards of an hour but the pizza is always amazing.  

The bar area is great.  It kind of reminds me of the dives my grandfather would take me to so he could grab a beer really quick when he was out running errands for my grandmother.  Smokey, dimmely lit, but delightful and lots of character.  There's always music playing, the walls have all sorts of customer art and funny messages on them from the many visitors both in town and out of town.  I think I could spend hours just reading all of the messages in on the walls in the dining room and the bathroom.  Either way I doubt I'd stop laughing.   

Late night the place really comes alive. Each time I've been there after 9 I've always left with a great memory and a great story.  The bar always has cheap pitcher specials to take you into the night during those long shuffle board tournaments or Golden Tee rounds.  

If you're a first timer, just know that it is going to take awhile to get your pizza if you ordered it. Just sit back, have a cocktail or three, and enjoy the company you're with. That is what the Black Thorn pub is all about.

Karma is very delicious! I typically get the acai bowls, or the energy squares that they sell. I come here quite a few times in a month. The only negative thing I can say is that when I order my bowls. Sometimes it has almonds and others it doesn't, it kind of pisses me off because I love almonds, so I expect them each time, too little of a detail to ruins someone's day about but I just feel it should be a little more consistent
Not many places serve lengua tacos so those alone make me a fan.
Horn Pest Management has provided more time for myself and my family. The service is second to none. My yard has never looked better. Keep up the great work.

I would have starved in Reno, staying for one month & looking for high-quality, vegan choices if it hadn't been for WF. The "salad bar" (actually 4 lines of food divided into soup, international, gourmet, and salad) opens when the store does at 8 a.m. I found the content labels of all the items on the bars to be accurate & helpful -- soups were amazing, salad ingredients cold, hot food hot. You know exactly what you are eating and paying $7.99/lb. for it (less the weight of your plate, bowl, or take-out carton). Eating in or outdoors and using the free wi-fi =extra perks! Oh, and on Sundays, and possibly other days as well, the store puts out scrambled eggs, bacon, more brunch-y foods for a few hours. The utensils are potato-based, degradeable.

Ordered the flat bread and hummus as well as the truffle parmesan french fries for appetizers and both were great.  We could not stop eating.  My friend ordered sliders and I ordered the Portobello mushroom burger and both were amazing!!  Great portion sizes and we had more food than we could consume.  I would definitely recommend this place and I plan on eating here many more times.  Additionally, the atmosphere is much nicer than the old Epiphany restaurant.  They lightened it up a bit and it is more welcoming for groups of friends and casual meals whereas Epiphanys seemed much more of a romantic date pick.  I love that they have music now as well.

My expectations were high for this place. On service and ambiance it certainly did not disappoint. Service was impeccable to say the least. Lots of helpful food and wine pairing suggestions from all. At the end we opted for the tasting menu (truly seemed like the best way to really get a feel for the food). The wine pairings were perfect with the menu offerings but the options brought out to us were hit and miss. For example for one of our appetizers we ended up with a fried tempura dish. Although it was tasty, it seemed fairly boring for a dish at Vetri -the food mecca.

For the main course we ended up with the goat which was tasty ,but quite small.. At the end of the day I walked away slightly hungry and $400 poorer. For the price and quantity of food offered there's better dining options in the city...

I have taken my yorkie mix Jonas here several times a year for almost 2 years...he gets sooo matted I have been told his hair is like "cotton candy." The staff here are so good at giving him that puppy look I love so much. He usually gets a pretty short cut because his hair is soo matted but they are usually quick and always tell me how good of a boy he's been. They brush his teeth and clean his eyes for me too.  

They also give me advice on other things, such as which brush I can use to help STOP the matting...now if only I could find the time to brush him evvverrydaaay.

I also have my mother in law bring him in for me and then call ahead to let them know any special instructions and they always remember him from last time. 

I always trust my guy with them. Now that I have moved out of state (to PA) I still find myself bringing him here although it is a pain for me to drive back and forth- but I don't want to trust Jonas anywhere else.

I (think I) had a very good time at Dirty Frank's. I remember being happy with my drink, the decor, the clientele, and the cleanliness of the bathrooms. I can't think of anything wrong with my experience there. I definitely plan to return when I can better appreciate it.

It's like a place you'd see in the movies!
I'm from NJ and was underwhelmed by many of the shops I visited. Not that the staff or selection was bad-- no shop was particularly beautiful. However sposabella was immaculate. It felt how it was supposed to feel. Clean pretty girl sparkly and bright! 
The staff was so sweet and helpful and you can tell they actually enjoy their jobs. 
I never felt rushed or pressured. 
I can't recommend it enough. I will be dragging all my friends and family there for their big day for the experience alone!
Not to say the selection wasn't great because it is! 
I couldn't be happier to have finally had the bridal experience I've been searching for.
this place is awesome they have good food in restaurants and good gambling. prices are fair on everything and good service.

Very disappointing customer service here. Seems like the employees are too busy running around restocking shelves to actually assist customers. Looks like the issue is poor management. I prefer clothing stores that focus more on customer service than stocking shelves.
Impeccable service, terrific selection, exquisite taste. Not cheap. Not cheap at all. But if you can afford it, worth it, without a doubt.

Awesome place to get a cut! Owner nice, stylists knowledgable, especially Lona. (sorry if I spelled it wrong) I got my hair highlighted, cut and styled last Thursday and was so happy! Can't wait to go back! loved all the compliments I got all day!! :)
I stop by here twice a month for take out and try various authentic Mexican foods.  Quick service and reasonably priced.  Clean establishment.

I like their burgers, fries, fried pickles and milkshakes. I havne't tried their salads and, honestly, I don't think you should expect much from salad at the burger place. I go there for burgers, I eat burgers and I love it. They are a pretty busy place, so I try avoid going there between 12 and 2 - I don't have patience for lunch time lines.

We're new to the area, so we're exploring restaurants every weekend. My wife has already proclaimed The Roost her favorite, and that's based on many years of breakfast dining, not just in this area. They bake all their own breads and pastries. Try the raisin bread or sugar-cinnamon toast. Yum! The cornbread casserole is another dish my wife and I highly recommend. And the service was prompt, attentive and very friendly. Enjoy!

Professional and exceptional customer service provided by Christian Talamini, Paul Naegele and the Turnersville BMW team. Our 328i xdrive lease was coming to an end and we were researching our next vehicle. Christian called to check on our status a month prior to turning in the 328i. We discussed what our expectations were for a possible new lease and he said he'd get back with information. He was in constant contact and we finally agreed verbally on a vehicle and finalized the sale that night. I can't say enough about the positive experience we had with the relaxed , no pressure, personable staff and management at BMW Turnersville. Our Second purchase & We love our 330i xdrive and hope to be a valued customer for a long time.  Nicole/Terry

Last night I was having a mean craving for some saucy Italian food.  I had been to Cafe Nino once before, several years ago, and really enjoyed it.  I hadn't been back because I usually make pasta at home. However, last night I returned to this adorable, cafeteria-style Italian restaurant.  

When I walked in the man who worked behind the counter greeted me with a huge smile, he was so excited to see me and was beyond helpful.  He described all the dishes and even let me taste test the very juicy Chicken Marsala before I made my final decision. I decided on the Veal Parmesan because I wanted something covered in marinara sauce, I absolutely love marinara sauce.  As a side I choose the beef lasagna, imagine my excitement when he told me that my options for sides were pizza or lasagna! The meal was topped of with a giant piece of bread that was toasted on the spot and another layer of marinara sauce, of course! 

Everything was so yummy!! My craving was totally satisfied! The Veal was tender and perfectly breaded; the sauce was a bit sweet and very savory.  The lasagna practically melted in my mouth and the bread! I had to tell my roommate that she was only allowed one more bite of the bread because she was trying to steal it from me.  Another fabulous part about Cafe Nino is the portions are huge! I had lunch for the next day and it was just as tasty. Not to mention how affordable it was!  I will definitely be making Cafe Nino a regular go-to spot from now on!

I visited here after all the other salons in my area close early on Friday. I also waited to write the review after a few days just to make sure my nails didn't chip. 
I got a pedicure done by Leo, there wasn't much of a wait and he got right to work. Very relaxing. I do not put Acrylic on my nails so I can't speak for that. The place was clean, quiet atmosphere. Not very big though.  I was greeted by staff, very friendly, didn't talk amongst themselves when they did my nails. 
I did take some pictures hopeful that helps someone else. I give it 4 stars because my toes look great and the place was clean (from what I saw).
Some notes:
-Might want to bring your own polish, crappy selection and old
-The pedicure wasn't exactly speedy but I was in no rush
-It is on the small side...
-I did not visit the bathroom or backroom so I can't speak for that. 

Despite the lack of stars they're still getting a good stream of business.  ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

It was worth the hype! The breakfast was amazing I ordered the catfish eggs and grits! The server said, "I will add a biscuit, you don't come here and not get a biscuit". Real life the biscuit was amazing! They are none for their fried chicken, so I ordered a wing on the side! Amazing!!!
Chaos. Food barely warm. Cooks cannot keep up.. This place needs competent cooks. Never coming back.

I'll give it a 3.5  but I rounded up because it wasn't a bad experience, service was good and fast.

The burger was good but not great, maybe a little bit too salty . I wish it was a little more pink for a medium-rare that I ordered. I liked the truffle fries, but it was nothing special. The hamburger bun is pretty good I thought. They have a pretty nice selection of fountain drinks... but that's really not that important ha. When compared to Five Guys.. I would say this is way better and less messy, but a little bit more expensive for how small the burger is. I would still take a burger from Village Whiskey any day and pay the extra premium.
Amazing. This place should be on the top of everyone's list. It's by far the best restaurant in SB. Amazing kaseiki meal and service.

I got the best haircut from Kirstin. She even took the time to teach me properly blow drying technique and what type of brush to use. She also taught me the easiest way to get those messy waves with a curling iron. I walked away with a cool trendy haircut and the knowledge on how to keep it looking good.

We stopped by because we couldn't decide where to eat and passed by this place. Now I'll be honest this place looks sketchy but the food and service is top notch. I love French toast and no one makes good French toast. These guys do. The decor is dingy as hell but I came here to eat so it don't bother me no none
The ladies here are so sweet and my nails look amazing! Thanks for the pampering! I will be back next time I visit Clearwater!

Stewy, Blake and the Forst Builders crew provide exceptional customer service, are dependable, knowledgeable and always right on schedule. I have worked with many contractors over the years and am highly impressed with Forst Builders. They are honest people and will not try to sell you something that you do not need. They also put in the extra time to explain their products and are happy to address your questions or concerns along the way. I recommend them to all my clients because they are the best in town!

BEST sushi ever!!!! I'm addicted! Always fresh and very unique options! Seriously, it's the place to be!! 
talk about YUMMMMMMMY!!!! ...& They're open for lunch too!! Dinner opens up @5pm.. Get there early cause this place is popular! ...wait time!? No worries!! You can chill on the front patio enjoying the amazing sake! Hot or cold!!

After rolling back to my hotel room at 5am I passed out and woke up starving and needing something quick before catching my flight back to Seattle.  Texted a local colleague who said she'd be right over to take me to a little sandwich shop that was amazing.  

I got the cuban press and ate half in Florida and the other half in Minneapolis/St. Paul airport as everyone kept coming up asking where I got it.  This will definitely be a spot I seek out again next time I am in Florida.

Love the updated seating...so roomy, assigned seats, recliners.  Very comfortable movie going experience.  On our last trip there, however, we witnessed a group of kids stealing candy...a lot of candy, from the counter because it is out in the open, instead of in a case.  We said something to them and they put it back. About 2 minutes later they took it again and walked away.  The "adult" with them started cursing at us for telling them not to steal.  The management did nothing except tell us to stop arguing.  Disappointing to say the least since the concessions cost a fortune and my own kids got to witness people stealing and getting away with it while their parents tell them no candy, it's too expensive.

I come to the peppermill often to Oceano for the Sushi.  I attended my first Yelp event at the Game Lab and had a blast.  It well very good and organized.  For the regular yelpers we got stuck with the left over food which was cold. But over all a great event. Thank you

As far as the Game Lab, the prices were average from what I seen around town. Good place to allow the kids to blow off steam while the parents do some gambling.  

P.S.  if you haven't had the all you can eat sushi at Oceano please do its awesome.  The atmosphere is to die for.  Try Oceano sushi and the BLTA Rolls.
Great burger! I had the bbq burger which had tons of flavor. Burger comes by itself, so don't forget to add an order of fries. Great location!

Seriously, this company is as good as it gets when it comes to expertise and finesse in the DJ industry. My wife and I had our wedding a month ago (December 2014) in Solvang, and finding the right DJ had been our highest priority. She believed from the beginning that this could make or break the party, and after seeing how perfectly it went off, I see that it all really did hang in that balance. I admit that I was stuck in pricing from the 90s and didn't plan to spend what we did on this aspect of the wedding, but now I know I'd easily pay much more for the quality we received. (Side note: we skimped on the video people and got what we paid for).

Gavin deejayed the event, but the overall company gave us real peace of mind from our very first phone call. Their online planning tool taught us what events we'd need music for, and they even provided all of the music and equipment for the ceremony. 

On our RSVP form, we had asked our guests, "What song is guaranteed to make you get up and dance?" - a question we weren't sure we'd ever get answered, let alone use at the event. However, their responses flowed in, and we sent them along to Gavin. Not only did he use every song - which kept our floor filled all night - but he mixed them so expertly that the beats seemed to match song to song to song in short intervals. The requests from guests weren't even all dance-friendly, but he made them danceable!!! We really had a pro dance party there thanks to him. 

Above all, it must be mentioned that our event was no typical affair for a deejay. I wish I could say we made it easy on him, but at least 5 different people had surprises that Gavin had to keep secret and straight from the next.  This could have led to several miscues and mistakes - but not on Gavin's watch. He nailed every single cue with the perfect song intro or mic placement.  All of this while playing master of ceremony. 

Gavin, Carly, and team, we cannot thank you enough for what you did for us. People are still talking about the wedding almost a whole month later, and everyone wants us to know that we had the greatest DJ.  We are so lucky, and could not be more grateful. 

THANK YOU!!!!

Ew. I don't know what upsets me more, the borderline gross food or how much I had to pay for it. We waited forever to get into this place which served me a relatively tasteless burger on an incredibly soggy McDonald's quality bun and the saltiest fries I have ever eaten. Yes, truffle oil is delicious, but pouring it over burned, greasy fries does not a delicious, 16 dollar meal make. We won't be back.
Solid burger.  Especially from a chain.  Smash fries are great.   Hagen Daz milk shakes.  Yes please

I was in town for a wedding this past weekend and my husband and I needed a place to grab breakfast. We loved Henry's so much we came here twice! I had a breakfast bagel sandwich and the breakfast burrito. Both sandwiches were delicious and fresh! The coffee is hot and strong. The staff at Henry's are friendly. We will definitely return when we are in the area.

Nobody greeted us when we came in and waited to be seated. 7 minutes later we're sitting, ordered coffee but 5 more minutes to have to ask for setups. So the service didn't impress me. Our waitress was friendly enough and did check back on us. The food is meh. Not bad but nothing special. A decent amount for the price if you're hungry. Parking is limited. Good coffee. If you're in the area it may be worth a try.

I was in Tucson yesterday afternoon and the weather was awful. Hotter than Hades! Needed a coffee, but needed to keep cool. Walked into this cafe and felt right at home. Had a Vietnamese iced coffee down up, sat down and relaxed. This is a great little spot with excellent service and coffee. I look forward to coming back.

We visited this location while on vacation in New Orleans. "Sunshine" made fudge, sang, and entertained us the whole time. My kids kept saying how this was the best fudge they have ever had. It was smooth and delicious. Not at all dry or grainy like other places. 
I was very impressed with the customer service as well. We bought several flavors to take home. It is too difficult to pick just one! 
I would definitely recommend stopping in.

Crepes were fabulous! The location is slightly odd, but I guess that is the nature of Philly. Caramel Latte was delicious and a very good bang for your buck. They also serve juices from Rijuice which were very refreshing. I would recommend this to any Philly new comer.
